    1391,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/5303795759',
    '{"id":"01KF132KFDCDRQW1NMYBF9MG5K","title":"VITAL // New North Monthly Check-In","summary":{"notes":"## **Project Updates and Deliverables**\n\nThe team delivered key content and updates in January, focusing on event pages, social media setup, and ongoing website enhancements.\n\n- **28 points of work were completed in January**, including two podcast episodes, one blog post, and social posts for D Tools and Lidapalooza, all scheduled using Publer for efficient publishing (06:48)\n    - The Vital Instagram account was set up and already gained initial followers, including Matt Bernath, showing early engagement.\n    - The Lidapalooza landing page is functionally ready with calendly widgets integrated, pending final copy edits and a repositioning of the event booth on the floor map as requested by Steven Frydrych.\n    - The homepage now features **three new or updated banners**, directing visitors to key pages, enhancing user navigation and event visibility.\n- The **financial services page design was sent for review** and will move to development once approved, showing a clear handoff process for timely implementation.\n- Ongoing tasks include producing a video testimonial from a Zoom recording and managing routine monthly site updates, ensuring steady content flow and quality maintenance.\n\n## **Podcast and Social Media Performance**\n\nPodcast downloads dipped slightly due to seasonal trends, while social media activity focused on building Vital’s brand presence.\n\n- **Podcast downloads reached 74 for the January 5th episode**, maintaining decent engagement despite a typical holiday slowdown in business podcast listening (11:02)\n    - YouTube views also declined but shorts remain the main traffic driver, highlighting the effectiveness of short-form content in audience reach.\n    - Upcoming content includes a session recording scheduled for February 2nd, with coordination underway to prioritize fast review and publishing.\n- Vital’s **Instagram page was created and initial posts, including pinned carousels, are live**, with a content schedule extending through February to build momentum (12:51)\n    - Growth strategy involves starting by following accounts already connected to Matt personally, then expanding to targeted technology integration companies, which replaced the broader luxury home services focus.\n    - Cross-posting between Matt’s personal Instagram and the Vital page will be used early on to drive followers to the company account, leveraging collaboration features to maximize exposure.\n    - Login access and Facebook page linkage are planned to ensure smooth management and consistent brand presence across platforms.\n\n## **Strategic Planning and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe leadership team adopted shorter sprint cycles and flexible planning to improve agility and focus on achievable goals.\n\n- **Matt Bernath shared that the team is shifting from quarterly plans to six-week sprints**, aiming for more nimble execution and quicker adjustments throughout the year (03:41)\n    - This approach modifies the EOS framework they already use, emphasizing smaller \"pebbles\" rather than large quarterly \"rocks,\" to maintain momentum and responsiveness.\n    - The annual off-site planning session in Scottsdale allowed for open discussion and fewer preset agendas, fostering team alignment without surprises.\n    - Matt anticipates a busy calendar through May, requiring a more selective approach to commitments, with a default \"no\" to new requests to maintain focus.\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Refinement**\n\nVital refined its target audience to technology integration companies to sharpen messaging and improve market fit.\n\n- The company moved away from the broad \"luxury home services\" category due to its lack of precision, focusing instead on **empowering technology integration businesses to scale**, which better matches their expertise and product offerings (13:28)\n    - This strategic shift affects social media targeting, content creation, and outreach lists, ensuring messaging resonates with a clearly defined audience.\n    - Baylee Gunnell and Igor Zagradjanin are managing content and follower targeting to align with this refined positioning, using curated lists and follower analysis for efficiency.\n    - Matt trusts the team’s judgment on follower selection beyond his personal network, aiming for growth without overburdening leadership with approvals.\n\n## **User Experience and Technical Considerations**\n\nMinor technical fixes and usability improvements are planned to enhance site functionality and social media integration.\n\n- The Lidapalooza landing page will have the booth map adjusted so Vital’s booth appears centered, improving event navigation and brand prominence (10:02)\n- Instagram bio will include a clickable link via the standard \"link in bio\" method, ensuring easy user access to Vital’s website and resources (15:47)\n- Coordination is underway to link the new Instagram page to Vital’s Facebook company page, ensuring consistent branding and easier social media management (19:19)\n- Login credentials for social accounts will be provided to Matt to maintain oversight and facilitate seamless collaboration.\n\n## **Business Environment and Team Culture**\n\nThe team reflected on the seasonal work rhythm and personal time, emphasizing balance and strategic pacing.\n\n- The holidays naturally slowed client activity, giving team members like Igor and Baylee a week off to recharge, which supports sustained productivity during busier months (00:05)\n- Despite common new year motivation myths, Matt and Baylee noted little change in local gym traffic, humorously highlighting real-world morale.\n- Matt shared personal reflections on balancing a packed work schedule with family time, while Baylee enjoyed a scenic Pacific Highway trip during her break, underscoring the importance of downtime.\n- The team’s informal exchange about winter snow conditions and local weather added a human touch, reinforcing close relationships beyond business.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vital Instagram","Lydapalooza landing page","podcast analytics","six-week sprints","social media strategy","annual planning"],"overview":"- **Project Deliverables:** 28 tasks completed in January, including podcasts, blogs, and social media content, enhancing audience engagement.  \n- **Podcast Metrics:** January 5th episode had 74 downloads, typical of holiday slowdowns; focus on short-form content drives YouTube traffic.  \n- **New Planning Approach:** Shift to six-week sprints for agility; busy calendar requires a selective commitment strategy through May.  \n- **Target Audience Shift:** Focusing on technology integration companies enhances messaging clarity and market fit, improving outreach efforts.  \n- **User Experience Improvements:** Adjustments planned for the Lidapalooza page and Instagram link to enhance navigation and resource access.  \n- **Work-Life Balance:** Team emphasized the importance of downtime during holiday season for sustained productivity throughout busier months.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide clickable link update for the Vital Instagram bio (15:55)\nContinue scheduling and publishing social content on Vital’s Instagram through February (13:11)\nWork on revising and updating Lydapalooza landing page per Steven’s feedback, including Vital booth relocation on map (06:48)\nSupport expedited review and publication of February 2 podcast session recording upon receipt from May (12:23)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend updated financial services page design for review and proceed to development after approval (06:48)\nManage ongoing monthly web and social media tasks, including podcast and blog posting (06:48)\nAdjust social post strategy transitioning content posting to Vital Instagram from Matt’s personal page and manage collaborator posting setup (16:35)\nProvide Matt with Vital Instagram login credentials and connect Instagram with Facebook company page (18:52)\n\n**Matt Bernath**\nReview and approve financial services page design update when received (06:48)\nSubmit February 2 podcast episode recording to Baylee for publishing (12:23)\nMonitor first wave of follower interactions on Vital’s Instagram and provide feedback if necessary on follower lists (14:35)\nUse personal Instagram to cross-promote Vital Instagram posts to increase follower migration (17:52)\n\n**Steven Frydrych**\nProvide final copy edits for Lydapalooza landing page and confirm Vital booth location on map (09:50)\n\n**May Castillo**\nDeliver February 2 session recording for podcast to Baylee by Friday and notify team for review (12:23)\n"},"duration":23.18000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"id":3,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":4,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":5,"name":"May Castillo"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Is around the corner.","index":0,"end_time":1.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, a little hectic.","index":1,"end_time":3.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1.12,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"How about you?","index":2,"end_time":4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.28,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, super great.","index":3,"end_time":7.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Things definitely slow down, like just as an agency during the holidays because our clients are out.","index":4,"end_time":12.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor got to take a week off.","index":5,"end_time":15.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I took a week off.","index":6,"end_time":16.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, just got to spend time with.","index":7,"end_time":17.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"With family too.","index":8,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So always nice just to get a break because now where everybody''s wanting to set goals and like really hit the ground running.","index":9,"end_time":28.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re busy, we don''t go to events.","index":10,"end_time":30.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But definitely a lot busier now.","index":11,"end_time":32.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Isn''t it kind of funny?","index":12,"end_time":34.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":33.47,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"The end of the year, no one cares and then a one week difference.","index":13,"end_time":38.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.59,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Everything''s urgent.","index":14,"end_time":40.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We have to do it now.","index":15,"end_time":41.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.55,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"It''s the new year.","index":16,"end_time":42.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.55,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Like you didn''t know it was going to be the new year last week.","index":17,"end_time":44.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.35,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":18,"end_time":47.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":44.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Everybody waits until afterwards.","index":19,"end_time":49.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s like joining the gym January 1st instead of the end of December.","index":20,"end_time":54.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.59,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Just.","index":21,"end_time":55.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.62,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I know you just start when you''re ready to start.","index":22,"end_time":59.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"I know you get just a wave of motivation.","index":23,"end_time":64.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":59.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":66.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":65.94,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"My gym''s been empty.","index":25,"end_time":68.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s so weird.","index":26,"end_time":69.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":68.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was like expecting it to be packed.","index":27,"end_time":71.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m like, where is everyone?","index":28,"end_time":72.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Nobody''s motivated this year.","index":29,"end_time":75.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":74.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That might just be in my neck of the woods, but.","index":30,"end_time":78.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":75.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s strange.","index":31,"end_time":81.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":80.75,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":32,"end_time":83.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":82.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I haven''t really seen any change either.","index":33,"end_time":85.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":84.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And my, my gym is always crowded, so I was expecting to see like just pain.","index":34,"end_time":91.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":85.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But it''s.","index":35,"end_time":92.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":91.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I mean, it''s as crowded as it is as it ever was.","index":36,"end_time":94.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":92.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yep.","index":37,"end_time":98.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":97.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Crazy times.","index":38,"end_time":98.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":98.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, how are you doing?","index":39,"end_time":100.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Matt and me?","index":40,"end_time":101.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Back to a new year.","index":41,"end_time":104.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got some good goals and gotta spend time with your families.","index":42,"end_time":109.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t really do.","index":43,"end_time":115.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":112.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Well, I shouldn''t say I don''t really.","index":44,"end_time":116.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":115.77,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t do resolutions, but I do kind of like a little bit of a vision for the year.","index":45,"end_time":121.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":116.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I''ve actually been pushing that off.","index":46,"end_time":124.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":122.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I think I''m doing that this weekend.","index":47,"end_time":125.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":124.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I haven''t really nailed that down.","index":48,"end_time":129.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.97,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But.","index":49,"end_time":129.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":129.17,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But yeah, we.","index":50,"end_time":130.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"For me, the holidays were like, very chill.","index":51,"end_time":134.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":131.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then like we launched right into 2026.","index":52,"end_time":138.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":139.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"As soon as January 5th came, like, we all met for strategy session.","index":54,"end_time":143.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":139.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":55,"end_time":143.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Steve already told you.","index":56,"end_time":144.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.99,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But yeah, like, I feel like we just got launched right out of the gate and when I look at my calendar, I''m busy through like May, which is crazy.","index":57,"end_time":154.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh my goodness.","index":58,"end_time":155.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":154.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Basically, like, my default answer from now on is no.","index":59,"end_time":159.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.43,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Like I''m just no.","index":60,"end_time":160.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.63,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s my default answer, no.","index":61,"end_time":162.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.75,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And I''m normally not a no, but my default answer is no.","index":62,"end_time":165.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":162.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":63,"end_time":166.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":166.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Catch me.","index":64,"end_time":167.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"After me.","index":65,"end_time":168.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":66,"end_time":171.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":170.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What do you do for your strategy.","index":67,"end_time":173.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Meeting, we go off site.","index":68,"end_time":177.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":173.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So in this case, we were in Phoenix, which is great.","index":69,"end_time":181,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":178.52,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Scottdale, and we got an Airbnb and all of us were chilling in the Airbnb for a few days and we took two, two full days for, for our annual planning.","index":70,"end_time":191.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And we have kind of like a format that we go through.","index":71,"end_time":193.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"This year was a.","index":72,"end_time":195.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":194.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There was less structure intentionally and, you know, more just time to talk about different things.","index":73,"end_time":202.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":195.72,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then we, you know, we.","index":74,"end_time":203.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There were.","index":75,"end_time":204.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":203.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There''s always a few changes.","index":76,"end_time":205.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":204.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I always drop a couple of bombs and then, you know, the team catches up.","index":77,"end_time":208.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"This year there weren''t that many bombs dropped, but.","index":78,"end_time":210.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":208.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But yeah, we, we plan out the year and, and kind of break it down into our goals for the next.","index":79,"end_time":217.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"This, this year we''re taking on a six week sprint rather than.","index":80,"end_time":220.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":81,"end_time":222.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re doing six week, like six week rocks.","index":82,"end_time":225.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":222.79,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, that''s really cool.","index":83,"end_time":227.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So do you follow EOS somewhat?","index":84,"end_time":230.309,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re modifying it a little bit because it''s worked really well for us.","index":85,"end_time":237.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230.309,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But I think now that we realize we need to potentially be a little more nimble.","index":86,"end_time":242.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, six week sprints are better than quarterly for us.","index":87,"end_time":245.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think that makes sense.","index":88,"end_time":247.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Especially if they''re not like huge rocks.","index":89,"end_time":252.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know how you define those.","index":90,"end_time":253.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We, we follow EOS too.","index":91,"end_time":255.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":253.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got our rocks for the quarter and some of them we finish early and some of them take the entire quarter.","index":92,"end_time":261.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess we''ll call these pebbles.","index":93,"end_time":265.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":262.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Pebbles.","index":94,"end_time":266.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love it.","index":95,"end_time":270.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":96,"end_time":272.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we''ll.","index":97,"end_time":273.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll get into it.","index":98,"end_time":274.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got some good updates for you today.","index":99,"end_time":277.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ve got a bit of.","index":100,"end_time":281.999,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think this is the first time you''ll see our new design slides too, so nothing too crazy though.","index":101,"end_time":287.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.999,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, my God.","index":102,"end_time":288.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.88,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Bailey, I have to tell you a story that you''re going.","index":103,"end_time":290.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.44,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"You''re going to crack up.","index":104,"end_time":292.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.16,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So you guys sent me that package.","index":105,"end_time":294.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":106,"end_time":295.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":294.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s the, the.","index":107,"end_time":298.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":296.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The hat.","index":108,"end_time":300.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Right.","index":109,"end_time":300.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.03,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The hoodie.","index":110,"end_time":301.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.31,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The beanie.","index":111,"end_time":301.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The beanie.","index":112,"end_time":302.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":113,"end_time":302.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":302.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And it has the logo mid on it.","index":114,"end_time":306.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":303.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Do you know what mid means to teenagers?","index":115,"end_time":308.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Is there something, I don''t know, like, not awesome?","index":116,"end_time":313.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":310.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, mid means not awesome.","index":117,"end_time":315.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.39,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":118,"end_time":315.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.35,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And so I''m unpackaging this thing and my daughter''s like, my 15 year old''s like, why did somebody send you a hat that says mid?","index":119,"end_time":323.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":316.27,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Are you actually going to wear that?","index":120,"end_time":325.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I''m like, I was, but now I''m not, so.","index":121,"end_time":329.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And it''s a, It''s a nice beanie.","index":122,"end_time":331.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":329.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"A really nice beanie.","index":123,"end_time":332.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But yeah, she.","index":124,"end_time":334.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.82,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"She was like, dad, you can''t.","index":125,"end_time":335.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":334.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"You can''t wear a hat that says mid.","index":126,"end_time":338.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s, like, not okay.","index":127,"end_time":339.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.14,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So, yeah, mid means like, average.","index":128,"end_time":342.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, no, we knew that when we ordered it.","index":129,"end_time":344.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":342.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We were just like, ah, this is funny.","index":130,"end_time":346.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":344.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, everybody''s gonna think we''re sending some silly message.","index":131,"end_time":351.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It was pretty.","index":132,"end_time":352.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":351.34,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"It was pretty funny.","index":133,"end_time":352.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.1,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I thought you would find that entertaining.","index":134,"end_time":355.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"No, that''s awesome.","index":135,"end_time":356.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You gotta get the teenagers to tell you that it''s.","index":136,"end_time":359.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That you can''t wear it.","index":137,"end_time":361.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":360.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so we''ve got just some updates on some of the things we finished this last month, as well as what we''re working on, and then just some things that we need your feedback on, and then some podcast and social updates as well as just our next steps.","index":138,"end_time":385.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But anything else you all want to add to this.","index":139,"end_time":387.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":385.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t have anything on my agenda.","index":140,"end_time":392.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.56,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I feel like we''ve been in a pretty good swing.","index":141,"end_time":396.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":394,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s not.","index":142,"end_time":396.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve been doing a lot of stuff, but we communicate a lot on Slack, so we got good stuff going on.","index":143,"end_time":403.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I''ll kick it over to Igor to talk through these.","index":144,"end_time":405.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks, Bailey.","index":145,"end_time":409.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":408.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hello, everyone.","index":146,"end_time":409.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":409.16,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So in January, we have delivered so far 28 points, including the items from the list.","index":147,"end_time":419.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":411.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we distributed two episodes, one blog, and created social posts for D Tools and lidapalooza.","index":148,"end_time":429.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":420.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We also scheduled those on Publer.","index":149,"end_time":432.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":429.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We set up the vital Instagram account and I saw, Matt, that you already followed back.","index":150,"end_time":439.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":433.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So thank you very much.","index":151,"end_time":441.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":439.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, the Light of Palooza page, just a few edits regarding the copy and also there''s another one with Steven.","index":152,"end_time":454.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":443.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"You mentioned that you wanted the vital booth to be in the center of the like window map.","index":153,"end_time":461.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":454.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we also fix that tomorrow.","index":154,"end_time":464.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":461.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The homepage was updated with three banners leading to the three new slash updated pages and the event backdrop was revised.","index":155,"end_time":477.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":465.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, definitely keep us in the loop on this one, Matt.","index":156,"end_time":480.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":477.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We want to know how it went.","index":157,"end_time":484.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":480.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then what we are working on.","index":158,"end_time":490.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":488.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Still the financial services page.","index":159,"end_time":493.53,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":491.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I just sent it a couple of hours ago for you to review the updated design.","index":160,"end_time":501.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":493.93,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then when it''s approved, we''ll move on to development, then the video testimonial from the Zoom recording, and just regular monthly management tasks.","index":161,"end_time":514.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":501.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":162,"end_time":516.179,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.699,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"One quick question for you.","index":163,"end_time":517.939,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":516.339,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I wasn''t clear on this earlier and I should have asked, are you.","index":164,"end_time":522.979,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.979,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The blog posts to the website, is it something that we''re being charged points for?","index":165,"end_time":527.779,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":523.059,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Because I know that''s something we used to have Abner just do on our other site.","index":166,"end_time":532.739,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.179,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So we have it looped into like a monthly management task.","index":167,"end_time":538.019,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.019,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we have like this catch all manage web.","index":168,"end_time":540.899,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.179,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s going to cover like adding the blog posts, adding all of the podcast episodes, and then just like any simple changes that you want to make.","index":169,"end_time":551.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.139,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":170,"end_time":553.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.18,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":171,"end_time":553.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I understand it may be confusing.","index":172,"end_time":556.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":554.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"In our previous agenda design, it was just differently, differently presented.","index":173,"end_time":563.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":557.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So here I was just thinking of, even if it''s not, even if you''re not charged points, I think it should just be on the list.","index":174,"end_time":571.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":563.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So you know what was done this month.","index":175,"end_time":574.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":571.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, perfect.","index":176,"end_time":575.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.34,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":177,"end_time":575.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":575.22,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Cool.","index":178,"end_time":577.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":576.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then, yeah, waiting on your comments on this one and I think that''s it.","index":179,"end_time":586.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":578.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Any questions?","index":180,"end_time":588.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":587.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":181,"end_time":591.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So just from, from my in being informed, the Light of Palooza landing page is now done.","index":182,"end_time":599.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.54,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Or it will be done as of tomorrow.","index":183,"end_time":601.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":599.67,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Basically, functionally, it''s done.","index":184,"end_time":605.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":602.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Stephen just had like.","index":185,"end_time":607.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":606.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"2 comments on the copy.","index":186,"end_time":613.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":612.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the calendly links are there, the calendly widgets are there.","index":187,"end_time":617.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":614.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also his third comment was regarding the.","index":188,"end_time":622.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":618.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So if you go to the Lytapalooza landing page, there''s this floor map and there vital is like on the right hand side of the map.","index":189,"end_time":634.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":622.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we just want to.","index":190,"end_time":636.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":634.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Steven commented that he wants to just move the entire map a bit to the left so that vitals booth can be in the center of the map.","index":191,"end_time":645.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":636.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s the only three updates that he wanted done.","index":192,"end_time":651.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":646.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":193,"end_time":652.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.06,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, so that sounds great.","index":194,"end_time":654.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I know Steven''s on top of it.","index":195,"end_time":655.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I just was curious, that''s all.","index":196,"end_time":657.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So then, just an update on how your podcast has been doing over the last 30 days.","index":197,"end_time":667.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can see some spikes from when episodes were published and overall downloads are down a little bit, which I think is pretty typical during the holiday season.","index":198,"end_time":682.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.99,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"People are not listening to podcasts, or at least not business podcasts quite as much during this time of year.","index":199,"end_time":689.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that''s not super surprising to me.","index":200,"end_time":692.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But this one, January 5th wasn''t, wasn''t too bad.","index":201,"end_time":697,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"74downloads is still pretty good.","index":202,"end_time":698.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then this one only just got published this week, so I expect that one to probably to go up a little bit.","index":203,"end_time":704.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":699.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, yeah, YouTube views are down a little bit too.","index":204,"end_time":711.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Again, I would expect that with the holidays and I''ll probably pick up again here soon.","index":205,"end_time":716.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then you can just see most of your traffic is still coming from shorts, so that''s always great.","index":206,"end_time":723.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then we can get them to come to your.","index":207,"end_time":725.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your longer form content.","index":208,"end_time":727.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":726.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, most of these are your shorts.","index":209,"end_time":730.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, oh, just before we go on to this next thing, are there any podcast episodes you have coming up soon that we should keep an eye out for.","index":210,"end_time":742.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":734.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, I think we''re asking.","index":211,"end_time":744.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":743.5,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Bailey, we will need your help with this because we have a session recording this Friday that has to go live on February 2nd.","index":212,"end_time":753.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":744.82,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"So I will submit the episode to you guys on Friday and give you a heads up in the channel so we can review next week.","index":213,"end_time":759.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":753.66,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":214,"end_time":761.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":760.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just let us know when you.","index":215,"end_time":763.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":761.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You submit it and we''ll make sure to work on that one extra fast.","index":216,"end_time":766.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure.","index":217,"end_time":767.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":218,"end_time":768.61,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":767.97,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":219,"end_time":772.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just some updates on social.","index":220,"end_time":774.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":772.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We got your vital Instagram account created and the top posts are published as well as those pinned carousels.","index":221,"end_time":783.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":774.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then got lots of stuff scheduled throughout the end of February.","index":222,"end_time":787.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But did you have any questions on this?","index":223,"end_time":790.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":792.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you guys for doing this.","index":225,"end_time":794,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So.","index":226,"end_time":795.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":794.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So Grow with Vital with no dots was not available.","index":227,"end_time":798.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Do you know Igor?","index":228,"end_time":802.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, it wasn''t.","index":229,"end_time":804.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":803.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":230,"end_time":805.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":804.64,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":231,"end_time":805.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.16,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So empowering.","index":232,"end_time":810.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":808.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We''ve moved away from luxury home services because we''ve recognized that it''s a little too broad.","index":233,"end_time":814.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.76,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So what we''re doing is technology integration companies or technology integrators.","index":234,"end_time":821.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":816.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So let''s change that.","index":235,"end_time":825.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":822.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So empowering technology integration businesses to scale.","index":236,"end_time":831.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":826.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And.","index":237,"end_time":835.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.37,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And I love that we have the website and stuff there.","index":238,"end_time":838.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.01,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So in terms of getting followers, are we like, what''s the.","index":239,"end_time":842.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"What''s the strategy there to get.","index":240,"end_time":846.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":844.33,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Get people like to follow us instead of just Matt?","index":241,"end_time":850.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":846.38,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we wanted to get some content published on there first.","index":242,"end_time":856.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then every week we would put together a list of people that will.","index":243,"end_time":861.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Will start following.","index":244,"end_time":862.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I think we talked about maybe having you review that probably for the first couple times to make sure it all looks good and then we can just roll with it if that sounds okay.","index":245,"end_time":874.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":865.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":875.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.09,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And that''s list of people who follow me personally.","index":247,"end_time":878.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":875.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And you''re just gonna be following them or how do you get that list?","index":248,"end_time":881.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.49,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, I think maybe we start with the people who are following you personally.","index":249,"end_time":887.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":883.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll go after those people first and then from there we can.","index":250,"end_time":890.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we have like so many lists that we''ve created.","index":251,"end_time":894.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":890.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like we probably can just try and find their Instagram accounts of people who, who we know are in your target market.","index":252,"end_time":902.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Love it.","index":253,"end_time":903.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Maybe make that easy.","index":254,"end_time":908.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":906.81,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"If they already follow me, I don''t feel the need to approve anything.","index":255,"end_time":912.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And beyond that, I don''t know what value I would add in looking at any other list.","index":256,"end_time":919.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So if you feel the need to have me approve them, let me know.","index":257,"end_time":922.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":919.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But I trust your judgment on, you know, whether they''d be good or not.","index":258,"end_time":928.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I suppose it''s better to follow them and see if they Follow us versus just try to filter it too much.","index":259,"end_time":937.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":260,"end_time":938.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":261,"end_time":938.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean we have.","index":262,"end_time":939.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we have lots of lists that we can use.","index":263,"end_time":941.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll just get started on that.","index":264,"end_time":943.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":265,"end_time":944.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.21,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Love it.","index":266,"end_time":945.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.65,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":267,"end_time":945.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.25,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":268,"end_time":947.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":947.17,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Bailey, is there a way that you can make our page, the link, I mean, clickable?","index":269,"end_time":952.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":947.57,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we should be able to do that.","index":270,"end_time":958.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll.","index":271,"end_time":958.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll look into that afterwards and see what we can do to get that updated.","index":272,"end_time":962.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If the link is in bio.","index":273,"end_time":966.25,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":964.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":967.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":967.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It should be like clickable.","index":275,"end_time":970.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":967.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s the only way to have actually to have it clickable on Instagram.","index":276,"end_time":973.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":970.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":277,"end_time":977.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.13,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":278,"end_time":979.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":979.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And I suppose you''re already doing it, but at the moment the link that we have at the bottom on our page links to Matt''s Instagram.","index":279,"end_time":988.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":979.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It should link to this one.","index":280,"end_time":991.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":990.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Right?","index":281,"end_time":991.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":991.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":282,"end_time":993.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":992.82,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you for now.","index":283,"end_time":994.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.18,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yes.","index":284,"end_time":996.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":995.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also another.","index":285,"end_time":997.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":996.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How would you like to proceed now that.","index":286,"end_time":1001.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":998.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So regarding the social posts for blogs and everything else.","index":287,"end_time":1006.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1001.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we''re adding.","index":288,"end_time":1009.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1007.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Because you mentioned that you would like to decrease the number of posts.","index":289,"end_time":1014.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1010.03,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Right.","index":290,"end_time":1015.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1014.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"On your personal Instagram.","index":291,"end_time":1016.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1015.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So are we going to just switch like what we would post on your Instagram?","index":292,"end_time":1023.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1017.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just switch to Violo''s Instagram, of course.","index":293,"end_time":1025.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1023.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"In like third person.","index":294,"end_time":1027.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1025.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"What do you think?","index":295,"end_time":1031.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.59,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Strategy wise, go before I give my feedback.","index":296,"end_time":1034.809,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1031.87,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"What do you think is the best strategy?","index":297,"end_time":1036.449,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.809,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, Bailey, please.","index":298,"end_time":1042.409,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1041.409,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, I was just gonna say I would probably mostly focus on the.","index":299,"end_time":1048.249,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.409,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The Vital page now.","index":300,"end_time":1049.649,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.249,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think a few posts on your personal page here and there is totally fine.","index":301,"end_time":1053.009,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.649,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like we''re trying to grow your Vital page.","index":302,"end_time":1055.329,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.089,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But you can like co post or I don''t know the right word for it but like you can share them together or like we can tag your personal page and some things if you want a little cross pollination.","index":303,"end_time":1067.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.369,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But I would put most of the focus on this new page.","index":304,"end_time":1070.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what my sense tells me.","index":305,"end_time":1075.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1072.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The only gotcha for me is that we really don''t have any followers on the Grow with Vital page.","index":306,"end_time":1081.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And so anybody who follows me personally is not going to see that stuff.","index":307,"end_time":1086.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.92,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I think we should do a lot of cross posting initially to drive people from my personal page to Instagram or to the company page.","index":308,"end_time":1095.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.51,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Right.","index":309,"end_time":1096.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.07,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I don''t know what that looks like.","index":310,"end_time":1098.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1096.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Maybe I''m not even using my terminology, but it feels like posting stuff on the Vital page and then calling to it somehow through my personal page is maybe the right answer.","index":311,"end_time":1109.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1098.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, just a post as collaborator practically.","index":312,"end_time":1114.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1110.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":313,"end_time":1115.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.28,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So there would be like Matt Burnett and Vital.","index":314,"end_time":1120.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1115.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So it''s like two.","index":315,"end_time":1121.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1120.4,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Two people posted.","index":316,"end_time":1122.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1121.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Cool.","index":317,"end_time":1123.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.36,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1124.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1123.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then People.","index":319,"end_time":1125.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1124.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":320,"end_time":1126.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1125.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"They would see vital Instagram through your Instagram and then hopefully follow it.","index":321,"end_time":1131.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1126.12,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Got it.","index":322,"end_time":1132.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.32,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Okay.","index":323,"end_time":1133.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Other quick questions.","index":324,"end_time":1135.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.8,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"How do I get access to.","index":325,"end_time":1138.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Not.","index":326,"end_time":1139,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.64,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Not that I''m going to be managing any of it, but it feels like I should probably at least be able to have this as, like, one of the options to log in from my Instagram.","index":327,"end_time":1145.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s one.","index":328,"end_time":1147.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.48,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then two.","index":329,"end_time":1147.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1147.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Do we need to make a connection now?","index":330,"end_time":1149.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1148.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Now that we have a company page, do we need to make a connection between this Instagram page and our company page on Facebook?","index":331,"end_time":1156.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1149.84,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we can give you the login information.","index":332,"end_time":1161.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s pretty easy.","index":333,"end_time":1162.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then, yeah, we should connect them to your Facebook.","index":334,"end_time":1168.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''ll also probably want to update, like, the social links on your website to go to this Instagram page.","index":335,"end_time":1175.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":336,"end_time":1176.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1175.55,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":337,"end_time":1182.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any.","index":338,"end_time":1182.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1182.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Anything else on this?","index":339,"end_time":1183.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1182.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, it''s great.","index":340,"end_time":1185.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1185.15,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":341,"end_time":1186.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1185.95,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And you''ll make that link clickable by doing a link in bio, right?","index":342,"end_time":1190.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1187.47,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":343,"end_time":1191.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1191.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":344,"end_time":1195.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1194.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s a pretty simple update.","index":345,"end_time":1197.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, yeah, that''s everything for our agenda today.","index":346,"end_time":1201.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1198.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll work on making those updates to the Instagram page and the other updates to that website, the Light of Palooza page.","index":347,"end_time":1211.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And I think we''re looking pretty good.","index":348,"end_time":1213.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good luck with all your events this next month, too.","index":349,"end_time":1216.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re going to have a very, very busy February.","index":350,"end_time":1219.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s bonkers.","index":351,"end_time":1221.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1219.66,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So crazy.","index":352,"end_time":1222.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1221.3,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And do you, like.","index":353,"end_time":1224.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Totally separate topic.","index":354,"end_time":1226.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Is Utah gonna get, like, a reasonable amount of snow this year or, like.","index":355,"end_time":1231.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.46,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"What''S the snow been?","index":356,"end_time":1231.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1231.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like this here, it''s terrible.","index":357,"end_time":1233.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1231.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"And then I saw some video of Park City, like, had no snow.","index":358,"end_time":1238.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1233.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So.","index":359,"end_time":1238.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1238.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is it really that bad?","index":360,"end_time":1239.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.9,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, it''s super bad.","index":361,"end_time":1241.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s super bad.","index":362,"end_time":1243.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ve got.","index":363,"end_time":1244.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1243.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re, like an hour away from Park City and we have a little bit of snow, but, like, not enough to go skiing.","index":364,"end_time":1252.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1246.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s bad.","index":365,"end_time":1254.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re supposed to be hosting the Olympics.","index":366,"end_time":1256.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"In a couple of years.","index":367,"end_time":1258.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1257.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know.","index":368,"end_time":1258.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1258.41,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"That''s so crazy that I''m sure they''ll figure out some way of seeding the skies to get snow.","index":369,"end_time":1265.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1259.13,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But, yeah, it''s.","index":370,"end_time":1266.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1265.45,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Last year, I didn''t.","index":371,"end_time":1269.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1267.85,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We.","index":372,"end_time":1269.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I was too busy.","index":373,"end_time":1270.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We didn''t go snowboarding, my daughter and I, and so this year we were going to plan to go, and I''m like, hey, worst case, you, Utah''s gonna have some snow.","index":374,"end_time":1276.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1270.05,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"But.","index":375,"end_time":1277.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1276.62,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That''S not the case.","index":376,"end_time":1279.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1278.78,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"So fingers crossed we''re enjoying the nice weather here in California.","index":377,"end_time":1282.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1279.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I don''t know if you are, but it''s been, you know, beautiful.","index":378,"end_time":1285.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.74,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So I guess it''s a trade off, but I would like to see some snow.","index":379,"end_time":1288.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1285.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I just.","index":380,"end_time":1290.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I took a week off and we drove up the Pacific highway and.","index":381,"end_time":1295.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, it was so nice.","index":382,"end_time":1296.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The weather was way warmer and.","index":383,"end_time":1299.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":384,"end_time":1300.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.22,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"When did you do that?","index":385,"end_time":1302.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1301.94,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Just last week.","index":386,"end_time":1303.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, and that was.","index":387,"end_time":1305.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1304.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"That was like, the nicest week we''ve had in a month.","index":388,"end_time":1308.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"So.","index":389,"end_time":1308.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.42,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, the.","index":390,"end_time":1309.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.66,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"The timing of that was perfect for you guys.","index":391,"end_time":1311.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.14,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, there was, like, no traffic either.","index":392,"end_time":1313.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, I think everybody had done all their holiday stuff, and it was awesome.","index":393,"end_time":1320.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s so cool.","index":394,"end_time":1321.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1320.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And did you time that perfectly?","index":395,"end_time":1323.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1321.86,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Because they had just opened the one back up.","index":396,"end_time":1325.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1323.5,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We.","index":397,"end_time":1326.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I guess.","index":398,"end_time":1327.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1326.96,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Where did you go from?","index":399,"end_time":1328.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.24,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"From where to where?","index":400,"end_time":1328.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.04,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":401,"end_time":1329.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Part of the one was closed, so we had to.","index":402,"end_time":1332.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We went.","index":403,"end_time":1332.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We went up to where it was closed, and then we had to go around, so we missed some of it, but still got to see a lot.","index":404,"end_time":1338.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1332.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, you got to.","index":405,"end_time":1340.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.36,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Did you stop by the elephant seals?","index":406,"end_time":1341.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1340.32,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Oh, we missed the elephant seals.","index":407,"end_time":1344.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Really?","index":408,"end_time":1344.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1344.4,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"I know.","index":409,"end_time":1345.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1345.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We.","index":410,"end_time":1346.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1345.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, right there.","index":411,"end_time":1347.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1346.12,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"You drove, like, by Hearst Castle?","index":412,"end_time":1349.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.2,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"There''s elephant seals there.","index":413,"end_time":1350.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.08,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, well.","index":414,"end_time":1351.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1350.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, we missed stuff.","index":415,"end_time":1353.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1351.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There was not enough time.","index":416,"end_time":1356.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1354.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":417,"end_time":1356.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1356.41,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Good, good.","index":418,"end_time":1359.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.89,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Well, glad you enjoyed a little bit of California.","index":419,"end_time":1362.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s very nice out there, so.","index":420,"end_time":1365.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1363.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":421,"end_time":1366.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.17,"speaker_name":"Steven Frydrych | VITAL"},{"text":"Thank you all.","index":422,"end_time":1367.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.69,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"We''ll see you guys.","index":423,"end_time":1368.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1367.53,"speaker_name":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":424,"end_time":1368.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"See you.","index":425,"end_time":1369.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":426,"end_time":1370.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1369.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Success.","index":427,"end_time":1370.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1370.01,"speaker_name":"May Castillo"}],"dateString":"2026-01-21T21:00:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/5303795759","participants":["concierge@growwithvital.com,brent@growwithvital.com,steven@growwithvital.com,matt@growwithvital.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,fernando@growwithvital.com,may@growwithvital.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","concierge@growwithvital.com","brent@growwithvital.com","steven@growwithvital.com","matt@growwithvital.com","fernando@growwithvital.com","may@growwithvital.com","igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF132KFDCDRQW1NMYBF9MG5K","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Outlined delivery of 28 content points in January, including blogs, podcasts, social assets, and website updates.","Confirmed Vital Instagram page is live with content scheduled through February and engagement strategies planned.","Agreed to shift focus toward six-week sprints over quarterly rocks to increase agility in 2026 planning.","Aligned on updating web and social metadata to reflect new positioning: ''technology integration businesses''.","Scheduled next podcast launch for February 2; Bailey confirmed expedited production upon submission Friday."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We just got launched right out of the gate and when I look at my calendar, I''m busy through like May.","speaker":"Matt Bernath | VITAL"},{"quote":"In January, we have delivered so far 28 points, including the items from the list.","speaker":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"quote":"We got your vital Instagram account created and the top posts are published as well as those pinned carousels.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","planning","social","podcast","marketing"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-vision","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-26T23:11:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Project Updates and Deliverables**\n\nThe team delivered key content and updates in January, focusing on event pages, social media setup, and ongoing website enhancements.\n\n- **28 points of work were completed in January**, including two podcast episodes, one blog post, and social posts for D Tools and Lidapalooza, all scheduled using Publer for efficient publishing (06:48)\n    - The Vital Instagram account was set up and already gained initial followers, including Matt Bernath, showing early engagement.\n    - The Lidapalooza landing page is functionally ready with calendly widgets integrated, pending final copy edits and a repositioning of the event booth on the floor map as requested by Steven Frydrych.\n    - The homepage now features **three new or updated banners**, directing visitors to key pages, enhancing user navigation and event visibility.\n- The **financial services page design was sent for review** and will move to development once approved, showing a clear handoff process for timely implementation.\n- Ongoing tasks include producing a video testimonial from a Zoom recording and managing routine monthly site updates, ensuring steady content flow and quality maintenance.\n\n## **Podcast and Social Media Performance**\n\nPodcast downloads dipped slightly due to seasonal trends, while social media activity focused on building Vital’s brand presence.\n\n- **Podcast downloads reached 74 for the January 5th episode**, maintaining decent engagement despite a typical holiday slowdown in business podcast listening (11:02)\n    - YouTube views also declined but shorts remain the main traffic driver, highlighting the effectiveness of short-form content in audience reach.\n    - Upcoming content includes a session recording scheduled for February 2nd, with coordination underway to prioritize fast review and publishing.\n- Vital’s **Instagram page was created and initial posts, including pinned carousels, are live**, with a content schedule extending through February to build momentum (12:51)\n    - Growth strategy involves starting by following accounts already connected to Matt personally, then expanding to targeted technology integration companies, which replaced the broader luxury home services focus.\n    - Cross-posting between Matt’s personal Instagram and the Vital page will be used early on to drive followers to the company account, leveraging collaboration features to maximize exposure.\n    - Login access and Facebook page linkage are planned to ensure smooth management and consistent brand presence across platforms.\n\n## **Strategic Planning and Workflow Adjustments**\n\nThe leadership team adopted shorter sprint cycles and flexible planning to improve agility and focus on achievable goals.\n\n- **Matt Bernath shared that the team is shifting from quarterly plans to six-week sprints**, aiming for more nimble execution and quicker adjustments throughout the year (03:41)\n    - This approach modifies the EOS framework they already use, emphasizing smaller \"pebbles\" rather than large quarterly \"rocks,\" to maintain momentum and responsiveness.\n    - The annual off-site planning session in Scottsdale allowed for open discussion and fewer preset agendas, fostering team alignment without surprises.\n    - Matt anticipates a busy calendar through May, requiring a more selective approach to commitments, with a default \"no\" to new requests to maintain focus.\n\n## **Brand Positioning and Messaging Refinement**\n\nVital refined its target audience to technology integration companies to sharpen messaging and improve market fit.\n\n- The company moved away from the broad \"luxury home services\" category due to its lack of precision, focusing instead on **empowering technology integration businesses to scale**, which better matches their expertise and product offerings (13:28)\n    - This strategic shift affects social media targeting, content creation, and outreach lists, ensuring messaging resonates with a clearly defined audience.\n    - Baylee Gunnell and Igor Zagradjanin are managing content and follower targeting to align with this refined positioning, using curated lists and follower analysis for efficiency.\n    - Matt trusts the team’s judgment on follower selection beyond his personal network, aiming for growth without overburdening leadership with approvals.\n\n## **User Experience and Technical Considerations**\n\nMinor technical fixes and usability improvements are planned to enhance site functionality and social media integration.\n\n- The Lidapalooza landing page will have the booth map adjusted so Vital’s booth appears centered, improving event navigation and brand prominence (10:02)\n- Instagram bio will include a clickable link via the standard \"link in bio\" method, ensuring easy user access to Vital’s website and resources (15:47)\n- Coordination is underway to link the new Instagram page to Vital’s Facebook company page, ensuring consistent branding and easier social media management (19:19)\n- Login credentials for social accounts will be provided to Matt to maintain oversight and facilitate seamless collaboration.\n\n## **Business Environment and Team Culture**\n\nThe team reflected on the seasonal work rhythm and personal time, emphasizing balance and strategic pacing.\n\n- The holidays naturally slowed client activity, giving team members like Igor and Baylee a week off to recharge, which supports sustained productivity during busier months (00:05)\n- Despite common new year motivation myths, Matt and Baylee noted little change in local gym traffic, humorously highlighting real-world morale.\n- Matt shared personal reflections on balancing a packed work schedule with family time, while Baylee enjoyed a scenic Pacific Highway trip during her break, underscoring the importance of downtime.\n- The team’s informal exchange about winter snow conditions and local weather added a human touch, reinforcing close relationships beyond business.","outline":null,"keywords":["Vital Instagram","Lydapalooza landing page","podcast analytics","six-week sprints","social media strategy","annual planning"],"overview":"- **Project Deliverables:** 28 tasks completed in January, including podcasts, blogs, and social media content, enhancing audience engagement.  \n- **Podcast Metrics:** January 5th episode had 74 downloads, typical of holiday slowdowns; focus on short-form content drives YouTube traffic.  \n- **New Planning Approach:** Shift to six-week sprints for agility; busy calendar requires a selective commitment strategy through May.  \n- **Target Audience Shift:** Focusing on technology integration companies enhances messaging clarity and market fit, improving outreach efforts.  \n- **User Experience Improvements:** Adjustments planned for the Lidapalooza page and Instagram link to enhance navigation and resource access.  \n- **Work-Life Balance:** Team emphasized the importance of downtime during holiday season for sustained productivity throughout busier months.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nProvide clickable link update for the Vital Instagram bio (15:55)\nContinue scheduling and publishing social content on Vital’s Instagram through February (13:11)\nWork on revising and updating Lydapalooza landing page per Steven’s feedback, including Vital booth relocation on map (06:48)\nSupport expedited review and publication of February 2 podcast session recording upon receipt from May (12:23)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nSend updated financial services page design for review and proceed to development after approval (06:48)\nManage ongoing monthly web and social media tasks, including podcast and blog posting (06:48)\nAdjust social post strategy transitioning content posting to Vital Instagram from Matt’s personal page and manage collaborator posting setup (16:35)\nProvide Matt with Vital Instagram login credentials and connect Instagram with Facebook company page (18:52)\n\n**Matt Bernath**\nReview and approve financial services page design update when received (06:48)\nSubmit February 2 podcast episode recording to Baylee for publishing (12:23)\nMonitor first wave of follower interactions on Vital’s Instagram and provide feedback if necessary on follower lists (14:35)\nUse personal Instagram to cross-promote Vital Instagram posts to increase follower migration (17:52)\n\n**Steven Frydrych**\nProvide final copy edits for Lydapalooza landing page and confirm Vital booth location on map (09:50)\n\n**May Castillo**\nDeliver February 2 session recording for podcast to Baylee by Friday and notify team for review (12:23)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"9995deb0-0f67-4254-b7f2-1634c69462aa","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
