    '{"id":"01KFEGEKERC60M11060KK51F7M","title":"NEACH Payments on Tap Content Plan","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Audience Positioning**\n\nThe meeting established a clear content plan focused on targeting **C-suite executives at banks, credit unions, and fintechs**, differentiating from more tactical shows by emphasizing strategic issues like ROI and risk management (05:40).\n\n- **Elyssa Morgan confirmed** the content will focus on **planning, execution, risk management, and revenue generation**, distinguishing it from Joe’s tactical approach (06:19).  \n- The brand positioning stresses understanding the **external, internal, and philosophical challenges** payment leaders face, building trust by offering actionable plans to help them avoid failure and stay competitive (07:18).  \n- Igor Zagradjanin highlighted the importance of the **theme statement** as the primary hook for the podcast on platforms like Spotify and Apple Podcasts, requesting detailed feedback for precise messaging (11:32).  \n- The podcast will be a **video series with no live audience pressure**, aimed at **decision makers and industry experts**, ensuring content clarity and focus (10:21).\n\n## **Podcast Format and Production Workflow**\n\nA consistent production framework mirroring the successful Wrestling Payments show was confirmed, with adaptations for Payments on Tap’s brand and audience (13:13).\n\n- The episode structure includes four parts: **setup, struggles, wins, and takeaways**, giving a clear narrative arc for guests and listeners (15:15).  \n- Production assets include **full audio/video episodes, short clips with captions**, social media posts primarily on LinkedIn, show notes, and thumbnails, supporting multi-channel repurposing (12:16).  \n- A dedicated **Riverside production space** separate from Wrestling Payments will be created to streamline scheduling and administration (14:38).  \n- Alyssa Morgan will record the **outro once**, with production team support for directing, editing, and analytics, ensuring consistent branding and quality across episodes (21:33).\n\n## **Branding and Design Direction**\n\nThe team agreed on a distinct visual identity for Payments on Tap that is lighter and more fun than Wrestling Payments, aimed at reflecting the podcast’s approachable yet strategic tone (23:40).\n\n- The preferred logo features a **white base with water-droplet or foamy bubble effects**, evoking the “brewery” theme subtly without looking dark or wrestling-related (24:18).  \n- Meg Norlund and Carlos favored a **lighter opacity (about 10%) on the bubbles** for a cleaner look, with adjustments planned to match the overall white color scheme (24:25).  \n- Thumbnail and video package designs will lean towards **white backgrounds and lighter colors** to clearly distinguish Payments on Tap from Wrestling Payments (26:07).  \n- The team plans to soften or remove bold quotation marks on quote cards to better fit the visual vibe and prevent jarring contrasts (28:40).\n\n## **Tone and Intro/Outro Style**\n\nThe group decided to shift the podcast’s tone away from purely business-like to a more relaxed, casual style that still respects the executive audience but encourages candid conversations (17:20).\n\n- Alyssa and Meg agreed the intro/outro should evoke the **feeling of a casual conversation in a brewery or similar social setting**, creating a comfortable listening atmosphere (17:55).  \n- Meg suggested using **creative sound effects like bar noises** for a short, fun intro rather than a spoken intro, respecting listeners’ limited time and keeping engagement high (19:44).  \n- The outro will be recorded by Alyssa personally to maintain authenticity while the production team handles animated visuals for consistency (21:33).  \n- The theme statement and outro text will be revised to better reflect this vibe before final approval and publication (11:32).\n\n## **Technical and Administrative Setup**\n\nThe team outlined necessary technical and account setup steps to ensure smooth launch and ongoing operations (32:22).\n\n- A new **Buzzsprout podcast account** will be created for Payments on Tap, requiring Alyssa’s help to connect a **personal Apple ID** for publishing, as company Apple IDs typically don’t work for this (32:22).  \n- Meg and Baylee will coordinate with IT to avoid using personal Apple ID credentials, ensuring proper security and management (32:53).  \n- Riverside recording software and production workflows will mirror Wrestling Payments, ensuring familiarity and efficiency for participants (13:41).  \n- Alyssa will receive upgraded production space support to facilitate better audio/video quality for recording sessions (22:00).\n\n## **Next Steps and Feedback Cycle**\n\nThe team confirmed a feedback-driven approach to finalize content plans, branding, and production elements promptly (30:37).\n\n- Baylee will send the **content plan and designs** for review, incorporating feedback on the **theme statement, intro/outro tone, and visual elements** (31:09).  \n- Music and background sounds for intros will be sourced and tested to align with the desired relaxed but professional vibe (31:09).  \n- Iterative adjustments to logos, thumbnails, and quote cards will reflect the group’s preferences for lighter colors and subtler visual effects (26:07).  \n- The production team will prepare Riverside setup and scheduling tools while Alyssa handles podcast publishing credentials for a **near-term recording start** (31:09).","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Content Plan","Brand Positioning","Payments on Tap","Podcast Design","Intro Outro Scripts","Content Repurposing"],"overview":"- **Content Focus:** Target C-suite executives, emphasizing ROI and risk management, distinct from tactical shows.  \n- **Podcast Structure:** Four-part episodes include setup, struggles, wins, and takeaways to create a clear narrative.  \n- **Visual Identity:** Lighter, fun branding with white backgrounds, designed to differentiate from Wrestling Payments.  \n- **Tone Adjustment:** Shift to a relaxed, conversational style with casual intro/outro to enhance listener engagement.  \n- **Technical Setup:** Establish new Buzzsprout account, ensure efficient Riverside recording workflow for quality production.  \n- **Feedback Process:** Iterative review of content and branding elements to finalize plans before recording begins.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare content plan document with team for comments and revisions (04:00)\nAdjust theme statement and intro/outro scripts based on meeting feedback and send updated versions for review (19:30)\nProvide additional logo and design variations focusing on white bubble motif and thumbnail options including white logos (25:00)\nLighten or redesign quote marks in video package to match softer aesthetic requested (29:00)\nPrepare and send final content plan and design assets for client review; assist with music/sound effects for episode intros (31:30)\nSet up new Riverside production space and create submission form specific to ''Payments on Tap.'' (14:50)\nCreate Buzzsprout podcast hosting account for Payments on Tap show (32:00)\n\n**Elyssa Morgan-NEACH**\nReview and provide feedback on updated content plan, intro/outro tone, and branding post-meeting (30:00)\nRecord podcast outro once production space and setup are ready; communicate readiness with production team (21:40)\n\n**Meg Norlund - NEACH**\nCoordinate internally re: Apple ID connection for Buzzsprout through IT to avoid personal IDs (32:30)\n\n**Carlos**\nProvide feedback on logo design lightness and color variants (24:15)\n"},"duration":33.79999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":1,"name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"id":4,"name":"Carlos"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello, Megan.","index":0,"end_time":138.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Hello.","index":1,"end_time":140.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":139.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"How are you?","index":2,"end_time":141.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":140.45,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m fine.","index":3,"end_time":142.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":143.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Well, thank you.","index":5,"end_time":145.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can''t believe January is almost over.","index":6,"end_time":150.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Come on.","index":7,"end_time":152.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"There''s like nine more days.","index":8,"end_time":154.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s not that bad.","index":9,"end_time":155.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.45,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It feels like it has flown by.","index":10,"end_time":159.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.53,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":11,"end_time":162.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And they say January is the longest month.","index":12,"end_time":165.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.05,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, I think March is March for me.","index":13,"end_time":169.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Feels like it never ends.","index":14,"end_time":171.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.53,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I live where it''s, like, pretty snowy, so it''ll kind of hint at spring, and then all of the sudden snow, it''s.","index":15,"end_time":179.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.05,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, it''s rough.","index":16,"end_time":181.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Hi, Alyssa.","index":17,"end_time":182.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.53,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Hey, Carlos.","index":18,"end_time":183.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Hey, everyone.","index":19,"end_time":189.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I believe we haven''t met Elisa.","index":20,"end_time":192.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.07,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So it''s nice to meet you.","index":21,"end_time":193.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Igor.","index":22,"end_time":195.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":193.91,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I''ve seen your emails come in here and there.","index":23,"end_time":198.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":195.03,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"So nice to see you.","index":24,"end_time":199.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":198.15,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I''ve not turned on yet my camera because I am having a morning, but.","index":25,"end_time":204.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":199.51,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not doing it.","index":26,"end_time":208.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":207.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Alyssa will be the host of Payments on Tap.","index":27,"end_time":212,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.44,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, I know, I know.","index":28,"end_time":216.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"She''s done a few under wrestling payments already.","index":29,"end_time":220.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.76,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":30,"end_time":223.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.32,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We''re very excited for this new show.","index":31,"end_time":225.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":228.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, Alyssa.","index":33,"end_time":229.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":228.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hey, everyone, too.","index":34,"end_time":230,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know I''ve met you a couple times, Alyssa, but it''s been a while, so we''re super excited for your show.","index":35,"end_time":236.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":230,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m excited.","index":36,"end_time":237.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":236.48,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Go.","index":37,"end_time":238.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s do it.","index":38,"end_time":241.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, we can just get into.","index":39,"end_time":243.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think the main thing we wanted to go over today is what''s called your content plan.","index":40,"end_time":249.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So in this content plan, we have just, like, some important foundational items, like your theme statement, who your target audience is, the designs, things like that.","index":41,"end_time":264.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''d love your feedback as we go along so we can make adjustments to make sure everything''s looking the way you want it to.","index":42,"end_time":272.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I will go ahead and share my screen.","index":43,"end_time":277.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just give me one sec.","index":44,"end_time":278.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":292.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.19,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, like I mentioned before, these are the things we''ll go over.","index":46,"end_time":294.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we do like to have everything, like, in a document, so we can always reference it later.","index":47,"end_time":301.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you do have any feedback, let us know.","index":48,"end_time":304.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":301.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We want to make sure this is what you''re looking for.","index":49,"end_time":306.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":304.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll send this to you afterwards, too, so you can leave comments on it as well.","index":50,"end_time":310.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.789,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If there''s anything else you would like us to adjust.","index":51,"end_time":313.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is your content plan.","index":52,"end_time":317.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We have a lot of things in here, and it''s really helpful just so we have a blueprint for everything moving forward, because we templatize everything.","index":53,"end_time":325.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we''ve been doing wrestling payments for a long time.","index":54,"end_time":328.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re able to stay consistent because we have a documented plan.","index":55,"end_time":331.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then just starting with our foundation, we have your ideal listener or your ideal customer.","index":56,"end_time":340.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":332.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And Megan had kind of mentioned to us it''s similar to the audience of Wrestling Payments, but we.","index":57,"end_time":346.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s going to be more of like the C Suite.","index":58,"end_time":349.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It sounds like the executives at a bank.","index":59,"end_time":351.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we have a couple things noted in here, but it seems like they''re probably dealing more with like ROI and just like higher level issues.","index":60,"end_time":364.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s not going to be more like, so tactical.","index":61,"end_time":367.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":365,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It seems like what Joe''s doing, you''re more like thinking of strategy and things like that.","index":62,"end_time":371.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":367.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like, just had a quick glance at this.","index":63,"end_time":374.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Is there anything you maybe add or adjust?","index":64,"end_time":376.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":374.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I think that makes a lot of sense.","index":65,"end_time":380.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":379.02,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"That is the differentiation, I guess, between what I''m trying to do and what Joe''s doing.","index":66,"end_time":384.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":380.78,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"He''s more boots on the ground, how things are working, the mechanics of staff, I guess.","index":67,"end_time":388.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":384.38,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And mine''s more planning, execution, risk management, kind of revenue generation.","index":68,"end_time":397.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.1,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"So, yeah, this all makes sense.","index":69,"end_time":398.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":397.66,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"No, this looks great.","index":70,"end_time":402.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":401.39,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":71,"end_time":404.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then here are just some examples of a content brief.","index":72,"end_time":409.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":405.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like two topic ideas you could do for a podcast.","index":73,"end_time":412.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":409.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, you''ve already done several episodes on Wrestling Payments, so I think you''re going to be great.","index":74,"end_time":418.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We always like to include this though, especially for people who''ve never done this before.","index":75,"end_time":423.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":418.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But just like having a, a direction for where you''re going with an episode.","index":76,"end_time":428.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":423.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then I will kick it over to Igor to talk about your brand positioning and messaging.","index":77,"end_time":436.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":431.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":78,"end_time":438.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thank you, Bailey.","index":79,"end_time":439.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.73,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically this is what sets you apart from the rest and so what makes customers listen to your podcast and choose you ultimately.","index":80,"end_time":450.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So they have a lot of choices in the market and you want to use the brand story?","index":81,"end_time":457.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Actually, we use the brand story framework to kind of explain the customer''s path and their struggles.","index":82,"end_time":465.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So there are payment leaders, executives, as Bailey said, C suite influencers at the banks, credit unions, etc.","index":83,"end_time":473.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"They have various challenges, external problems, internal problems, philosophical problems.","index":84,"end_time":480.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then they find your company and from your content, from your podcast, they see that you understand the pressure they''re facing.","index":85,"end_time":489.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then they find you to be an authority on the topics you present.","index":86,"end_time":493.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That instills trust in them.","index":87,"end_time":496.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"They.","index":88,"end_time":497.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"You give them a plan basically and call them to action.","index":89,"end_time":500.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then through all of that, you help them transform and experience success and avoid failure, like falling behind competitors.","index":90,"end_time":509.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then find a clearer payment strategy, smarter prioritization, etc.","index":91,"end_time":516.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.49,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"There''s a lot of text on the screen.","index":92,"end_time":520.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":518.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We will send this over to you.","index":93,"end_time":522.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.97,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But yeah, is there like anything at a quick glance that really resonates with you or you think we should tweak a Bit.","index":94,"end_time":528.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":522.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"At the top.","index":95,"end_time":536.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.02,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"No, I haven''t read everything, but from what he explained in summary, it seems good.","index":96,"end_time":542.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.7,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":97,"end_time":545.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So then we will go ahead and hop into here what''s called your content program.","index":98,"end_time":552.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So essentially it''s like all the different ways that you can use the podcast to create pot to create content.","index":99,"end_time":562.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is why we love podcasting, is because you can have a single conversation and repurpose it into so many different ways.","index":100,"end_time":570.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":563.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So when we say owned experiences, that''s things that are like living on your website or like on your personal LinkedIn.","index":101,"end_time":580.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like there''s a lot of things you can do to repurpose a podcast from short clips.","index":102,"end_time":585.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You have your show notes, you have web pages, you could do blog posts.","index":103,"end_time":590.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ve even seen people.","index":104,"end_time":591.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"When I''m saying like amplified, that could be like doing a paid media campaign or things like that.","index":105,"end_time":598.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s really just getting the word out more.","index":106,"end_time":601.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I know you guys have had a newsletter, so podcasts are great because you can start simple and spread it in so many different ways.","index":107,"end_time":608.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, then I''ll kick it back to Igor to talk about your program specifically.","index":108,"end_time":617.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":109,"end_time":618.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.74,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So your content program.","index":110,"end_time":620.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This.","index":111,"end_time":621.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There are a few things that are the most important we want to focus on.","index":112,"end_time":626.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So like the theme statement, Payments on Tap is a podcast for bank, credit union and fintech execs who want big picture insight on modernization, competition, fraud and consolidation without the operational weeds.","index":113,"end_time":640.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then the next paragraph is just about what the.","index":114,"end_time":644.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Each episode delivers candid, future focused conversations that help you clarify priorities, ask better questions and stray ahead of what''s next.","index":115,"end_time":655.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then the format, a video podcast series.","index":116,"end_time":662.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Basically structurally the same as what we do for wrestling payments.","index":117,"end_time":668.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So niche prospects like decision makers and influencers at bank, credit unions and fintechs, fintech and payment leaders, industry experts, technology providers, regulatory voices.","index":118,"end_time":681.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The format is recorded and yeah, there''s no pressure to perform live with an active audience, which is cool.","index":119,"end_time":688.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then on the next slide.","index":120,"end_time":691.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, I''ll just.","index":121,"end_time":693.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just one thing on this, the theme statement.","index":122,"end_time":695.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Igor said it''s really important.","index":123,"end_time":696.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":695.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you don''t give us feedback on anything, this is the one thing we do need feedback on because this is what''s going to be on like Spotify and Apple podcasts when people click on your show.","index":124,"end_time":707.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So definitely this is the one I would spend some time reviewing to make sure, like it says exactly what you want it to say.","index":125,"end_time":713.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, this and also I think, Bailey, that we also need feedback on, correct me if I''m wrong, the intro and the outro, because this is something we created off the top of Our heads.","index":126,"end_time":729.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But still this is something that you may want to actually personalize.","index":127,"end_time":733.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":128,"end_time":734.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":733.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So there''s two really important things.","index":129,"end_time":736.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":130,"end_time":737.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But we''ll come to the intro and outro right now.","index":131,"end_time":741.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.23,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the primary assets, these are pretty similar.","index":132,"end_time":745.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s not the same to what we do for wrestling payments.","index":133,"end_time":749.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the full podcast episode, audio and video with pre recording, intro and outro, then short form videos.","index":134,"end_time":762.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Actually one short form video with plus without captions and then a couple of short form videos, clip style videos with some highlights that will be published on socials.","index":135,"end_time":777.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"LinkedIn to be precise.","index":136,"end_time":779.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Social images like quote cards and one thumbnail and article with detailed show notes including social media posts or LinkedIn.","index":137,"end_time":791.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, any questions or like anything you''d want to adjust here.","index":138,"end_time":796.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The short form videos, that is TikTok style as well, right.","index":139,"end_time":803.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.51,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And like Reels sizing that 1080 by 1080 or 1080 by 1920.","index":140,"end_time":809.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.63,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, those like clip style videos, that''s what those are.","index":141,"end_time":813.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":809.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":142,"end_time":814.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":814.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And this is just briefly on what''s expected from you.","index":143,"end_time":824.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just like with the wrestling payments.","index":144,"end_time":827.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So we need access to you for scheduling and availability for sessions.","index":145,"end_time":833.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Basically you know everything about the recording equipment, branding, materials, venue, the feedback loop.","index":146,"end_time":844.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":835.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So it''s basically the same.","index":147,"end_time":848.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The same thing that we''re doing already.","index":148,"end_time":850.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then we will provide the reverse side if I''m correct.","index":149,"end_time":857.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Recording software.","index":150,"end_time":859.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Of course you can count on our production team for directing, recording and editing the video series, post production, analytics, feedback, implementation.","index":151,"end_time":874.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yes, I was just going to.","index":152,"end_time":878.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.41,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Ask on that note for do you want a separate Riverside production space for this show or do you want to keep it in the same space?","index":153,"end_time":885.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can you do it similar to the way that you separated out wrestling payments and meet you but create a space for payments on tap?","index":154,"end_time":894.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":155,"end_time":894.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.14,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":156,"end_time":896.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":895.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do we need a different client form though or do we just specify which podcast it is?","index":157,"end_time":904.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":898.22,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''ll probably have a different submission form.","index":158,"end_time":908.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":905.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":159,"end_time":909.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.62,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And this is just an exam example of the structure of the episode.","index":160,"end_time":920.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I''m sure that you''re familiar with with it as I think you''re using similar thing for wrestling payments.","index":161,"end_time":929.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.03,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So first comes the setup, the first part that aims to set the stage, then the struggles.","index":162,"end_time":937.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So what obstacles did the guest face, what problems they saw and what prompted them to change or explore new solutions.","index":163,"end_time":946.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then of course the wins and finally the takeaways, the last part of the episode.","index":164,"end_time":952.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, this is the sample script that you can use to structure the episodes.","index":165,"end_time":966.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.49,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So basically I''m sure you have experience with all of this, but in case you do need some inspiration or help?","index":166,"end_time":975.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This can be pretty useful.","index":167,"end_time":977.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yes, this is the intro and outro I mentioned.","index":168,"end_time":986.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":983.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this is something I created based on all the input from the meeting we had with Megan and Carlos.","index":169,"end_time":995.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But please feel free to give feedback on this, to personalize it to.","index":170,"end_time":1004.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Whatever you feel like will contribute to the show.","index":171,"end_time":1009.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And we have the highlighted here.","index":172,"end_time":1013.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So LinkedIn at profile name.","index":173,"end_time":1015.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This is because we weren''t sure, but Megan, you mentioned in our last meeting that actually we''re gonna use niche LinkedIn for both for wrestling payments.","index":174,"end_time":1025.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And so I think we''re good on this.","index":175,"end_time":1027.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So follow us on LinkedIn @niche.","index":176,"end_time":1030.929,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.63,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Right.","index":177,"end_time":1031.329,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.929,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then we have that covered.","index":178,"end_time":1033.169,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1031.409,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It will be niche.","index":179,"end_time":1034.769,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.729,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Is this the.","index":180,"end_time":1035.649,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.769,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The intro, like the wrestling payments?","index":181,"end_time":1038.769,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.529,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s like, welcome to wrestling.","index":182,"end_time":1040.289,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.769,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":183,"end_time":1040.889,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1040.449,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we''ll need to work on this because we want this to be a little.","index":184,"end_time":1044.849,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.889,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think, Alyssa, you can correct me if I''m wrong, but a little bit more fun.","index":185,"end_time":1048.889,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.248,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I mean, we''re playing on this great theme.","index":186,"end_time":1051.409,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.889,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And when I''m reading this, this sounds very.","index":187,"end_time":1053.249,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1051.409,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It just sounds very business oriented and not as fun.","index":188,"end_time":1058.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Like, it doesn''t match the vibe of like, the brand elements, that sort of bar vibe, the fun conversations on.","index":189,"end_time":1068.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Even though we''re.","index":190,"end_time":1069.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.3,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"We''re touching heavier topics.","index":191,"end_time":1071.219,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And Alyssa, if I''m wrong there, you can let me know.","index":192,"end_time":1073.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.219,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I think this sounds a little businessy.","index":193,"end_time":1074.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.14,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I agree.","index":194,"end_time":1075.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.18,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I think the audience, that''s probably what led you to be like this.","index":195,"end_time":1079.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.82,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"But like, it''s almost like we want to take them out of the stuffy executive boardroom.","index":196,"end_time":1084.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1079.7,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Right.","index":197,"end_time":1085.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1084.71,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And put them in a space that''s comfortable to have casual conversation.","index":198,"end_time":1089.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1085.07,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And that''s usually when the best conversations happen.","index":199,"end_time":1092.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1089.27,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"That''s kind of the idea.","index":200,"end_time":1093.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1092.63,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"It is very much tied into our payments on tap.","index":201,"end_time":1097.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1094.47,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Just so you guys know, we do networking, receptions, payments on tap after our large events.","index":202,"end_time":1102.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1097.67,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And we usually pick either a brewery or this year we''re going to try and do DraftKings.","index":203,"end_time":1107.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1102.95,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"So it definitely does tie in even to, you know, brewing, I guess you could say ideas in payments or strategy and payments.","index":204,"end_time":1114.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.35,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Whether you want to tie that to, you know, draft beer or, you know, you can do coffee.","index":205,"end_time":1120.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.93,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"We could spin it different ways.","index":206,"end_time":1122.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1120.81,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"So I don''t know that we necessarily have to act like we''re all sitting around drinking a pint while.","index":207,"end_time":1129.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1122.01,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"While we''re doing this.","index":208,"end_time":1130.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.17,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But yeah, same feeling as you, Meg.","index":209,"end_time":1134.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1130.25,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"100%.","index":210,"end_time":1135.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1134.93,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Just again, yes, we want the folks who are in the boardroom making decisions, driving forward strategy, but we want to give them a place to not feel they''re working while they''re listening in.","index":211,"end_time":1145.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1135.81,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":1147.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.15,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think that you captured something earlier.","index":213,"end_time":1150.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1148.51,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Gosh, we''ve gone through so many slides now, but there was something about the brewery without the noise or something.","index":214,"end_time":1158.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1152.27,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"There was, like, a line that was earlier that I think was more aligned with what I was thinking for this here.","index":215,"end_time":1165.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The statement, yeah, maybe the best conversation at a brewery.","index":216,"end_time":1170.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.23,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, that kind of aligned with what Alyssa had just said there.","index":217,"end_time":1174.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I think minus the noise also kind of hones in on.","index":218,"end_time":1178.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.91,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Minus the external noise on these topics as well.","index":219,"end_time":1181.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.03,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So I think we could do some play on words there.","index":220,"end_time":1183.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that sounds great.","index":221,"end_time":1186.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that makes a lot of sense.","index":222,"end_time":1187.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1186.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And, yeah, maybe we can tweak it a little bit before we send it back to you, see if it''s more on point.","index":223,"end_time":1194.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1187.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Another thing I''m noticing podcasts do more frequently is just having, like, some sound effects in the intro rather than a speaking section.","index":224,"end_time":1205.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s just creative choice.","index":225,"end_time":1207.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, you can have an intro like this, or you can keep it really simple and just get right into the episode.","index":226,"end_time":1212.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I kind of like that.","index":227,"end_time":1215.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.83,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think Wrestling Payments, the vibe works really well because of the announcer voice, but I wouldn''t actually be opposed to just getting into it.","index":228,"end_time":1223.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.87,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"These are people, you know, their time is money.","index":229,"end_time":1226.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.55,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So, yeah, jumping in faster, and they''ll know what the topic is based on, title, and, you know, the.","index":230,"end_time":1232.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"The story we put around the episode.","index":231,"end_time":1234.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, but we could still make it fun, like having some.","index":232,"end_time":1237.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Some bar noises or something before it gets in there.","index":233,"end_time":1241.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1238.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But then it''s only a couple seconds long.","index":234,"end_time":1243.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1241.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just another thing to think about is we also could direct to Alyssa''s LinkedIn.","index":235,"end_time":1252.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1247.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, we''d say you can follow us on.","index":236,"end_time":1255.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1253.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On LinkedIn @niche, and also Alyssa Morgan, like, if you also want to direct people there.","index":237,"end_time":1260.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1255.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think just for clarity and simplicity, we''d probably just keep it for Niche, and then she can share out on her page.","index":238,"end_time":1268.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.1,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":239,"end_time":1269.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1269.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":240,"end_time":1272.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1271.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll then just tweak the outro, and we''ll plan on doing some cool sound effects for the intro, if that sounds good to you.","index":241,"end_time":1279.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1273.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then do you want us to hire someone to do the outro?","index":242,"end_time":1284.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or, Alyssa, do you want to record it yourself?","index":243,"end_time":1287.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Again, just personal preference.","index":244,"end_time":1289.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1287.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We don''t care which way you go.","index":245,"end_time":1291.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.34,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think it''d be great if Alyssa would be comfortable recording it.","index":246,"end_time":1296.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t mind.","index":247,"end_time":1297.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1297.02,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I think it''s easy enough.","index":248,"end_time":1298.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1297.9,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"It''s fine.","index":249,"end_time":1299.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1298.9,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And then is this something that will just piece in, or will I be doing the outro?","index":250,"end_time":1304.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1300.46,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Outro.","index":251,"end_time":1305.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1304.54,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Every time you''ll Just record it once.","index":252,"end_time":1308.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll.","index":253,"end_time":1309.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll have, like, a.","index":254,"end_time":1309.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":255,"end_time":1310.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1309.98,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, just once.","index":256,"end_time":1311.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1310.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":257,"end_time":1311.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll get some cool animated text on the screen, and it''ll.","index":258,"end_time":1315.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1311.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll use the same one every time.","index":259,"end_time":1316.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1315.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":260,"end_time":1317.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1316.9,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t mind doing that.","index":261,"end_time":1318.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1317.42,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":262,"end_time":1320.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1319.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just have to set up my studio.","index":263,"end_time":1322.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1320.42,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I need a better studio.","index":264,"end_time":1323.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1322.42,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":265,"end_time":1324.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1324.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s get you a new production space first.","index":266,"end_time":1329.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1325.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll just start everything clean on a new one, and then you can go crazy.","index":267,"end_time":1334.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":268,"end_time":1338.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Next for my favorite part, which is the designs.","index":269,"end_time":1342.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1338.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll just get, like, some of your.","index":270,"end_time":1344.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s.","index":271,"end_time":1346.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1345.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t think the right link.","index":272,"end_time":1348.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1347.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let me grab it really quick.","index":273,"end_time":1350.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think that was our mood board that we looked at when we first started chatting.","index":274,"end_time":1356.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1350.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bailey, actually.","index":275,"end_time":1358.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1357.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":276,"end_time":1358.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.419,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s the same.","index":277,"end_time":1359.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1358.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I just put it below.","index":278,"end_time":1361.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1359.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":279,"end_time":1362.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1361.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, so that we have.","index":280,"end_time":1364.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Takes you to the wrong part of the board.","index":281,"end_time":1366.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":282,"end_time":1367.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, there it is.","index":283,"end_time":1369.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, there it is.","index":284,"end_time":1370.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1369.19,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I just left it with everything above.","index":285,"end_time":1373.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Because then we also have references that we mentioned in our last meeting so that we can go back to some of them if you feel like it.","index":286,"end_time":1380.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.19,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":287,"end_time":1382.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll start off with the COVID art.","index":288,"end_time":1384.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1382.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You don''t need to make decisions right now unless you feel very passionately about things.","index":289,"end_time":1389.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1384.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So starting off with kind of like the original logo you sent over switched it up with more white, so it''s different than wrestling payments.","index":290,"end_time":1399.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1389.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Added a fun one with, like, the water droplets, and then this one also has some water droplets.","index":291,"end_time":1406.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1400.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll zoom in a little because it might be hard to tell with the white on white.","index":292,"end_time":1410.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1406.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, a couple options.","index":293,"end_time":1412.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1410.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, are any of these resonating with you more than others?","index":294,"end_time":1415.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I would like to stay away from the dark vibe, since that is very wrestling paymentsy feel.","index":295,"end_time":1425.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1420.31,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I like the last one.","index":296,"end_time":1429.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.83,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know how you feel, Alyssa.","index":297,"end_time":1430.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.39,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t.","index":298,"end_time":1431.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.67,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I immediately thought, like, foamy bubbles, but now I''m thinking, does it look too raindroppy?","index":299,"end_time":1436.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1431.75,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I. I actually liked that one as well.","index":300,"end_time":1442.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1439.59,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"It does look a little raindroppy, but, I mean, it''s also like when the foam overflows and comes.","index":301,"end_time":1450.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1442.79,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Like, I see the big pieces, I''m like, oh, that''s like, you know, when it comes down the side of the glass.","index":302,"end_time":1454.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1450.34,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yes, I like it.","index":303,"end_time":1456.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.58,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It looks kind of fun.","index":304,"end_time":1457.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1456.74,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Maybe a little more faded, like, by, like, 10%.","index":305,"end_time":1461.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1458.58,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":306,"end_time":1465.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you like the white?","index":307,"end_time":1466.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know why I picked 10, but, yeah, I like that one the best as well.","index":308,"end_time":1472.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1466.54,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I believe the logo does a lot of work already, so having it white, I. I''M I''m feeling as well.","index":309,"end_time":1479.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1472.62,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"And I do like the.","index":310,"end_time":1480.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1479.59,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The effect on the background just maybe a little lighter.","index":311,"end_time":1485.75,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1480.95,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":312,"end_time":1487.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1486.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''ll.","index":313,"end_time":1487.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1487.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll maybe just give you a few other options based on this one then.","index":314,"end_time":1491.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1487.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this.","index":315,"end_time":1492.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If this is the direction you''re wanting to go, we''ll probably adjust some of these other designs to, like, match that a bit more.","index":316,"end_time":1500.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, for example, you.","index":317,"end_time":1502.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1500.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''ll see a couple different designs.","index":318,"end_time":1504.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The clipart, this one, like, already has that kind of, like, water droplet vibe on there.","index":319,"end_time":1508.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.52,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can see all the different logos and things on there.","index":320,"end_time":1512.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1509.24,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''d obviously, like, change these to be more on par with the COVID art.","index":321,"end_time":1518.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":322,"end_time":1518.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other notes on these?","index":323,"end_time":1520.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1518.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like the idea of the bubbles with the sound effect too, because I think that kind of vibes.","index":324,"end_time":1528.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1522.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Well, yeah, yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1533.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got this arrow too.","index":326,"end_time":1535.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.9,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I thought that was, like, a fun addition.","index":327,"end_time":1537.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1535.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Cool.","index":328,"end_time":1543.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.82,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I love this logo.","index":329,"end_time":1544.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1543.26,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"I love it.","index":330,"end_time":1544.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1544.22,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, I love it so much.","index":331,"end_time":1545.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1544.66,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Really good one then.","index":332,"end_time":1547.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1545.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"These are pretty similar.","index":333,"end_time":1548.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1547.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just a different dimension.","index":334,"end_time":1550.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1548.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll hop over here to thumbnails.","index":335,"end_time":1554.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Similar idea, but we can change it to the.","index":336,"end_time":1558.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1556.01,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The white version so it matches.","index":337,"end_time":1560.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1558.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But, like, aside from that, any other tweaks you''d want to make to these?","index":338,"end_time":1564.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1560.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I like that.","index":339,"end_time":1567.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.29,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"When I''m looking at this, I am not thinking wrestling payments at all.","index":340,"end_time":1572.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1567.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That''s a nice distinguisher.","index":341,"end_time":1575.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.93,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''m not thrilled about the niche logo in the two color down there.","index":342,"end_time":1580.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I''d almost like to see that.","index":343,"end_time":1581.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.37,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"All white.","index":344,"end_time":1582.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.49,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"White, yeah.","index":345,"end_time":1583.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.5,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":346,"end_time":1583.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1583.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Or if.","index":347,"end_time":1584.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1584.02,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Do you want to keep this in blue or do you want us to go white with these as well?","index":348,"end_time":1588.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Can we see it in white as well?","index":349,"end_time":1590.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.06,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":350,"end_time":1591.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1590.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just like an all green logo, then if it''s white.","index":351,"end_time":1595.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1591.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All white, probably.","index":352,"end_time":1596.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1595.78,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, no, probably the.","index":353,"end_time":1599.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1596.98,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"Yeah, okay, let''s.","index":354,"end_time":1601.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1599.54,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s see.","index":355,"end_time":1602.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1601.46,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think we''d probably, by brand guidelines, have to stick with a black one, but let''s take a look at it and see.","index":356,"end_time":1607.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1602.42,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And if you need local variations, Bailey, just let us know.","index":357,"end_time":1610.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll look.","index":358,"end_time":1613.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1611.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think we have some, but yeah, we can get you a few other variations here.","index":359,"end_time":1616.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1613.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you.","index":360,"end_time":1616.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"What do you think about these, like, water droplets kind of like going on top of the image?","index":361,"end_time":1622.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1616.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Will that translate with the white?","index":362,"end_time":1625.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.789,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think we can.","index":363,"end_time":1627.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.75,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''m not a designer, but I''ll ask them.","index":364,"end_time":1630.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1628.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Alyssa, how are you feeling about this?","index":365,"end_time":1633.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.11,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Going over the picture?","index":366,"end_time":1638.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.45,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"It''s a little interesting.","index":367,"end_time":1640.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1638.73,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":368,"end_time":1641.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1640.97,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"We can get rid of it if you don''t like it.","index":369,"end_time":1646.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1644.49,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re not gonna hurt our feelings.","index":370,"end_time":1647.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1646.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":371,"end_time":1648.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.69,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":372,"end_time":1649.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1648.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I will say for it to be like the beer, it ha.","index":373,"end_time":1653.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1649.93,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"The droplets have to be white.","index":374,"end_time":1654.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1653.09,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"So when you see it on blue, it just doesn''t look like beer anymore, you know?","index":375,"end_time":1658.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1655.21,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"No.","index":376,"end_time":1658.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1658.57,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yes.","index":377,"end_time":1659.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1658.93,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":378,"end_time":1659.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1659.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s water droppy instead.","index":379,"end_time":1660.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1659.69,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree.","index":380,"end_time":1662.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1660.97,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Carlos, can we see a version with and without?","index":381,"end_time":1665.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1662.21,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, for sure.","index":382,"end_time":1668.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1666.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":383,"end_time":1670.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then we''ll hop over here to your video package.","index":384,"end_time":1672.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1670.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So these are the things we''ll use for like a full episode or that one really nice edited video.","index":385,"end_time":1680.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1672.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The short video.","index":386,"end_time":1681.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1680.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''ve got a couple different renderings here.","index":387,"end_time":1684.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1682.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, I''m sure you''ve seen these similar things on, like the niche episodes, but like anything standing out or things you''d want to adjust.","index":388,"end_time":1694.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, kind of fun seeing a different use of these, like, kind of water droplets on these.","index":389,"end_time":1699.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I really like line two, number one.","index":390,"end_time":1703.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1701.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I think the logo is really popping on that.","index":391,"end_time":1706.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1704.31,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And yeah, the standard in that.","index":392,"end_time":1711.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1709.35,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That whole line, I''m.","index":393,"end_time":1712.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I like that.","index":394,"end_time":1713.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1712.55,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":395,"end_time":1714.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1713.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Pain.","index":396,"end_time":1718.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1718,"speaker_name":"Carlos"},{"text":"It''s hard with the dark because if we''re going light, my.","index":397,"end_time":1723.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1720.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"My brain is like, no, those are not options so much.","index":398,"end_time":1726.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1723.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1727.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1727.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I have to say with the quotes, I struggle a little bit with that.","index":400,"end_time":1735.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1728.96,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"With the quotation marks.","index":401,"end_time":1737.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1735.52,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I like.","index":402,"end_time":1740.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1739.6,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"If you look at the last row, first one, maybe there''s a way of lightening up those quotation marks.","index":403,"end_time":1745.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.36,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They''re so jarring.","index":404,"end_time":1746.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.75,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":405,"end_time":1748.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1747.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do you.","index":406,"end_time":1749.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1749.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can try lightening them up or would you prefer just getting rid of them altogether and just having it be text on the screen?","index":407,"end_time":1756.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1750.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you could match it to like the vibe of the drops, that would be less, like in your face, I think.","index":408,"end_time":1763.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.15,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"But I. Yeah.","index":409,"end_time":1765.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.19,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"This is something I struggle with with wrestling payments as well.","index":410,"end_time":1767.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1765.95,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"They just sort of like, they pop in a weird way for me.","index":411,"end_time":1770.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1767.99,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And it''s always like just one version of it.","index":412,"end_time":1772.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.72,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s not like the closed loop quotation.","index":413,"end_time":1775.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1773.08,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"So kind of.","index":414,"end_time":1776.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.28,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":415,"end_time":1777.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1776.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I prefer the big question that''s in the dark.","index":416,"end_time":1781.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1777.8,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That layout.","index":417,"end_time":1783.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1781.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":418,"end_time":1784.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.64,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"As opposed to this.","index":419,"end_time":1786.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1785.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":420,"end_time":1787.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then I just want to get clarity.","index":421,"end_time":1789.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Do we want to keep any in the dark blue or do we want to try and just go all white moving forward?","index":422,"end_time":1797.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1789.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"My thought is closer to the white because there''s so much gray on the wrestling payments and it will feel very like inverse, I think.","index":423,"end_time":1808.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1799.61,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":424,"end_time":1809.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":425,"end_time":1811.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1810.65,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"And I do have a hard stop, by the way, at 10:30, so I''m not sure how much more we have.","index":426,"end_time":1814.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1811.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re.","index":427,"end_time":1815.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1814.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re really close to being done.","index":428,"end_time":1816.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1815.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think, like, these are the last designs to show you.","index":429,"end_time":1820.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So these are the.","index":430,"end_time":1820.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1820.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The quote cards.","index":431,"end_time":1822.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1821.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can do the same thing with those quotation marks like you were talking about and just go all white.","index":432,"end_time":1828.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1823.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any other notes on these?","index":433,"end_time":1834.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1833.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":434,"end_time":1837.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1837.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I want to just make sure, Alyssa, you''re comfortable with this and we can.","index":435,"end_time":1840.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1837.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You can take a look at it after the fact too, and give us feedback to you.","index":436,"end_time":1844.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.57,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"You''re not.","index":437,"end_time":1845.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.89,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"It''s not like right now is your only chance.","index":438,"end_time":1847.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.01,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I just want to make sure this is like, sort of what you''re comfortable with, this approach.","index":439,"end_time":1851.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1847.85,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":440,"end_time":1853.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1852.06,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"I think it''s more like the vibe in terms of, like, intro, outro, stuff like that that I want to see aligned.","index":441,"end_time":1860.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1853.66,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"And we talked about it.","index":442,"end_time":1861.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1860.22,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"Megan, you and me are on the same page with that.","index":443,"end_time":1863.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1861.18,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"So when it comes to branding and colored and all of that stuff, that''s all you guys.","index":444,"end_time":1868.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1863.38,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"She''s comfortable.","index":445,"end_time":1869.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1868.5,"speaker_name":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":446,"end_time":1869.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1869.1,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1870.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1869.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":448,"end_time":1872.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1871.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, so just to wrap up for the process, we''ll follow the same thing as we do for wrestling payments.","index":449,"end_time":1881.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So basically.","index":450,"end_time":1882.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1881.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, and so next thing, we''re gonna give you the content plan and the designs to get feedback from you.","index":451,"end_time":1891.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1883.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So any changes you want to make to the theme statement or the outro, let us know.","index":452,"end_time":1895.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1891.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll work on making updates to the designs based on what you''ve already told us in the call, and then we can send those over for you to get us any other feedback.","index":453,"end_time":1903.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1895.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll start working on finding, like, some music and background, like, sounds for stuff, and just work on wrapping up designs, getting your Riverside set up.","index":454,"end_time":1914.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1904.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re going to create a buzzsprout account for you.","index":455,"end_time":1918.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1915.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Alyssa, one thing we''ll need your help with is connecting the Apple ID to buzzsprout.","index":456,"end_time":1924.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1918.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"That''s something we just can''t do.","index":457,"end_time":1925.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1924.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, it has to be connected to a personal Apple ID in order for it to connect.","index":458,"end_time":1930.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1925.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we''ll be able to start recording really soon.","index":459,"end_time":1933.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1930.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":460,"end_time":1935.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1934.43,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re really excited.","index":461,"end_time":1936.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1935.07,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s going to be an awesome show.","index":462,"end_time":1939.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1937.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But any other questions for us?","index":463,"end_time":1941.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1939.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Billy, do you know if Joe set his Apple ID up to his personal one?","index":464,"end_time":1946.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1942.35,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Because I think we have some Apple IDs for the company.","index":465,"end_time":1949.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1946.55,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"I didn''t realize that it was based on personal.","index":466,"end_time":1951.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1949.31,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"That would have been before I started with you.","index":467,"end_time":1957.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1953.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I''m not sure and I think the process might have changed.","index":468,"end_time":1961.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1957.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":469,"end_time":1962.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1961.48,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we can try to use a business one.","index":470,"end_time":1967.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1964.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I just know people have had trouble doing that.","index":471,"end_time":1969.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1967.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if you can.","index":472,"end_time":1973,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1972.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, just CC myself and we''ll get Joan unplugged our IT person as well, just so we don''t have to use her personal stuff.","index":473,"end_time":1979.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1973,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Okay.","index":474,"end_time":1979.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1979.16,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, Great.","index":475,"end_time":1981,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1979.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We will stay in touch.","index":476,"end_time":1982.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1981.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, great to see you all today.","index":477,"end_time":1984.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1982.77,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks so much, guys.","index":478,"end_time":1985.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1984.77,"speaker_name":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"text":"Really appreciate it.","index":479,"end_time":1986.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1985.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Looks great.","index":480,"end_time":1987.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1987.25,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll see you.","index":481,"end_time":1989.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1989.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"See you.","index":482,"end_time":1990.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":483,"end_time":1990.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1990.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":484,"end_time":1991.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1990.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":485,"end_time":1992.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1991.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89692468724?pwd=HXPJWu7yb5maQ8zWnfm4b5XLcf8BNH.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com,cortiz@neach.org,mnorlund@neach.org","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","cortiz@neach.org","mnorlund@neach.org"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFEGEKERC60M11060KK51F7M","organizer_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.95,"bullets":["Aligned on targeting C-suite audience seeking strategic insights beyond operational details.","Confirmed podcast structure will mirror Wrestling Payments but in a lighter, more casual format.","Settled on visual direction favoring lighter, foam-inspired aesthetics to differentiate branding.","Planned single, reusable outro recording by host Elyssa to personalize and simplify production.","Agreed to launch support tasks including Riverside setup, Buzzsprout account, and creative tweaks."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We want to give them a place to not feel they''re working while they''re listening in.","speaker":"Elyssa Morgan-NEACH"},{"quote":"I think we''ll need to work on this because we want this to be a little bit more fun.","speaker":"Meg Norlund - NEACH"},{"quote":"We’re really excited. It''s going to be an awesome show.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["launch","branding","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-26T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Audience Positioning**\n\nThe meeting established a clear content plan focused on targeting **C-suite executives at banks, credit unions, and fintechs**, differentiating from more tactical shows by emphasizing strategic issues like ROI and risk management (05:40).\n\n- **Elyssa Morgan confirmed** the content will focus on **planning, execution, risk management, and revenue generation**, distinguishing it from Joe’s tactical approach (06:19).  \n- The brand positioning stresses understanding the **external, internal, and philosophical challenges** payment leaders face, building trust by offering actionable plans to help them avoid failure and stay competitive (07:18).  \n- Igor Zagradjanin highlighted the importance of the **theme statement** as the primary hook for the podcast on platforms like Spotify and Apple Podcasts, requesting detailed feedback for precise messaging (11:32).  \n- The podcast will be a **video series with no live audience pressure**, aimed at **decision makers and industry experts**, ensuring content clarity and focus (10:21).\n\n## **Podcast Format and Production Workflow**\n\nA consistent production framework mirroring the successful Wrestling Payments show was confirmed, with adaptations for Payments on Tap’s brand and audience (13:13).\n\n- The episode structure includes four parts: **setup, struggles, wins, and takeaways**, giving a clear narrative arc for guests and listeners (15:15).  \n- Production assets include **full audio/video episodes, short clips with captions**, social media posts primarily on LinkedIn, show notes, and thumbnails, supporting multi-channel repurposing (12:16).  \n- A dedicated **Riverside production space** separate from Wrestling Payments will be created to streamline scheduling and administration (14:38).  \n- Alyssa Morgan will record the **outro once**, with production team support for directing, editing, and analytics, ensuring consistent branding and quality across episodes (21:33).\n\n## **Branding and Design Direction**\n\nThe team agreed on a distinct visual identity for Payments on Tap that is lighter and more fun than Wrestling Payments, aimed at reflecting the podcast’s approachable yet strategic tone (23:40).\n\n- The preferred logo features a **white base with water-droplet or foamy bubble effects**, evoking the “brewery” theme subtly without looking dark or wrestling-related (24:18).  \n- Meg Norlund and Carlos favored a **lighter opacity (about 10%) on the bubbles** for a cleaner look, with adjustments planned to match the overall white color scheme (24:25).  \n- Thumbnail and video package designs will lean towards **white backgrounds and lighter colors** to clearly distinguish Payments on Tap from Wrestling Payments (26:07).  \n- The team plans to soften or remove bold quotation marks on quote cards to better fit the visual vibe and prevent jarring contrasts (28:40).\n\n## **Tone and Intro/Outro Style**\n\nThe group decided to shift the podcast’s tone away from purely business-like to a more relaxed, casual style that still respects the executive audience but encourages candid conversations (17:20).\n\n- Alyssa and Meg agreed the intro/outro should evoke the **feeling of a casual conversation in a brewery or similar social setting**, creating a comfortable listening atmosphere (17:55).  \n- Meg suggested using **creative sound effects like bar noises** for a short, fun intro rather than a spoken intro, respecting listeners’ limited time and keeping engagement high (19:44).  \n- The outro will be recorded by Alyssa personally to maintain authenticity while the production team handles animated visuals for consistency (21:33).  \n- The theme statement and outro text will be revised to better reflect this vibe before final approval and publication (11:32).\n\n## **Technical and Administrative Setup**\n\nThe team outlined necessary technical and account setup steps to ensure smooth launch and ongoing operations (32:22).\n\n- A new **Buzzsprout podcast account** will be created for Payments on Tap, requiring Alyssa’s help to connect a **personal Apple ID** for publishing, as company Apple IDs typically don’t work for this (32:22).  \n- Meg and Baylee will coordinate with IT to avoid using personal Apple ID credentials, ensuring proper security and management (32:53).  \n- Riverside recording software and production workflows will mirror Wrestling Payments, ensuring familiarity and efficiency for participants (13:41).  \n- Alyssa will receive upgraded production space support to facilitate better audio/video quality for recording sessions (22:00).\n\n## **Next Steps and Feedback Cycle**\n\nThe team confirmed a feedback-driven approach to finalize content plans, branding, and production elements promptly (30:37).\n\n- Baylee will send the **content plan and designs** for review, incorporating feedback on the **theme statement, intro/outro tone, and visual elements** (31:09).  \n- Music and background sounds for intros will be sourced and tested to align with the desired relaxed but professional vibe (31:09).  \n- Iterative adjustments to logos, thumbnails, and quote cards will reflect the group’s preferences for lighter colors and subtler visual effects (26:07).  \n- The production team will prepare Riverside setup and scheduling tools while Alyssa handles podcast publishing credentials for a **near-term recording start** (31:09).","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Content Plan","Brand Positioning","Payments on Tap","Podcast Design","Intro Outro Scripts","Content Repurposing"],"overview":"- **Content Focus:** Target C-suite executives, emphasizing ROI and risk management, distinct from tactical shows.  \n- **Podcast Structure:** Four-part episodes include setup, struggles, wins, and takeaways to create a clear narrative.  \n- **Visual Identity:** Lighter, fun branding with white backgrounds, designed to differentiate from Wrestling Payments.  \n- **Tone Adjustment:** Shift to a relaxed, conversational style with casual intro/outro to enhance listener engagement.  \n- **Technical Setup:** Establish new Buzzsprout account, ensure efficient Riverside recording workflow for quality production.  \n- **Feedback Process:** Iterative review of content and branding elements to finalize plans before recording begins.","action_items":"\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nShare content plan document with team for comments and revisions (04:00)\nAdjust theme statement and intro/outro scripts based on meeting feedback and send updated versions for review (19:30)\nProvide additional logo and design variations focusing on white bubble motif and thumbnail options including white logos (25:00)\nLighten or redesign quote marks in video package to match softer aesthetic requested (29:00)\nPrepare and send final content plan and design assets for client review; assist with music/sound effects for episode intros (31:30)\nSet up new Riverside production space and create submission form specific to ''Payments on Tap.'' (14:50)\nCreate Buzzsprout podcast hosting account for Payments on Tap show (32:00)\n\n**Elyssa Morgan-NEACH**\nReview and provide feedback on updated content plan, intro/outro tone, and branding post-meeting (30:00)\nRecord podcast outro once production space and setup are ready; communicate readiness with production team (21:40)\n\n**Meg Norlund - NEACH**\nCoordinate internally re: Apple ID connection for Buzzsprout through IT to avoid personal IDs (32:30)\n\n**Carlos**\nProvide feedback on logo design lightness and color variants (24:15)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"56da9d10-03e0-46a4-b45b-354bf1bce189","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
