    '{"id":"01KFH2VAS9XD7K4CGM7RSQHHQH","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Distribution**\n\nThe team successfully delivered **15 content points this month**, including the **Rustamirani episode** and LinkedIn carousel posts approved by **Gab** (06:19).\n\n- The only active task beyond monthly maintenance is **campaign management**, with **23 points currently in progress** this month.\n- A compilation video using last year’s episodes is pending **Tim’s recording of intro and transition parts**, expected to resume in the next meeting.\n- Upcoming priorities include distributing the recently uploaded **Spotify audio episode** and scheduling the **full video episode for next Thursday** on Spotify.\n- The team plans to confirm with **Gab**, returning Tuesday, on missing CES episode videos and raw material for completion.\n- There is potential to create a **thought leadership blog** tied to podcast episodes, starting with the upcoming one, to enhance content reach and brand positioning.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance**\n\nThe mid-December campaign reached **40,000 impressions**, generated **95 clicks**, and produced **1 lead** so far, focused on **LinkedIn (MOFU)** and **AdRoll (awareness)** platforms (10:49).\n\n- **Contextual targeting** on AdRoll outperforms retargeting by reaching broader, interest-based audiences rather than website visitors, as explained by **Baylee**.\n- The campaign targets financial services, with **Vice Presidents showing the strongest engagement**.\n- Campaign budget is planned to continue until **March**, aligned with the upcoming law effective date, to maximize awareness.\n- Downloads of the campaign guide are low, with only about **2-3 downloads reported**, but the main goal is to boost awareness and prompt outreach to the company.\n- The MOFU campaign was shifted to focus on **conversions via website form fills** to improve lead quality and efficiency, following **Christina’s request** about 10 days ago.\n- Creatives with **lighter white backgrounds clearly outperform dark blue ones**, guiding future design choices.\n- Despite good reach, click-through rates are low, attributed to creatives and copy, prompting plans for a **creative refresh and messaging optimization** to improve engagement.\n- The team will also **exclude irrelevant audiences** to improve targeting quality and efficiency.\n- A phase two campaign meeting is scheduled next week, where messaging and targeting refinements will be discussed collaboratively.\n\n## **Strategic Planning and Future Campaigns**\n\nThe team is monitoring the **HR2808 campaign’s performance** before launching new campaigns, including one for the **Total IP Addresses product** (17:35).\n\n- **Christina** emphasized the need to evaluate current campaign results before deploying new tactics, ensuring resource focus and data-driven decisions.\n- The team expressed readiness to support future campaigns once HR2808 insights are available.\n- This phased approach reflects a cautious, data-driven marketing strategy to optimize budget and maximize impact.\n\n## **Operational and Communication Challenges**\n\nTechnical and scheduling issues impacted meeting participation and content production (07:30).\n\n- **Tim’s connection issues** delayed recording tasks, creating dependencies in video compilation.\n- **Gab’s absence until Tuesday** affects access to necessary media assets for CES episode finalization.\n- The team agreed to follow up with Gab after her return to maintain workflow continuity.\n- **Christina’s laptop and connection issues** highlight ongoing challenges with tools and platforms, affecting remote collaboration quality.\n- Transition to **Google Meet for Active Prospect** is anticipated, potentially affecting future meeting stability.\n\n## **Creative and Audience Insights**\n\nData-driven creative decisions are shaping campaign optimizations to increase engagement and lead generation (14:27).\n\n- The clear preference for **lighter, white-background creatives** informs upcoming design standards.\n- Insights into audience engagement reveal that while many see the ads, fewer click, indicating a need for better messaging alignment.\n- Ongoing testing and refinement will focus on improving click rates and form fills by aligning creative style and copy more closely with audience preferences.\n- The team plans to maintain a balance between awareness and lead generation to support both brand recognition and conversion goals.","outline":null,"keywords":["Fireflies","Zoom integration","CES episode","LinkedIn campaign","contextual targeting","lead generation"],"overview":"- **Content Delivery Success:** Delivered 15 content points this month, focusing on recent episodes and social media posts.  \n- **Campaign Insights:** Mid-December campaign achieved 40,000 impressions, 95 clicks, and 1 lead; shifts needed for better engagement.  \n- **Strategic Planning Emphasis:** Evaluating HR2808 campaign results is crucial before launching new tactics, ensuring focused efforts.  \n- **Operational Hurdles:** Technical issues impacted meeting participation and production; follow-up on content tasks is essential post-absence.  \n- **Creative Optimization:** Lighter creatives perform better; future designs will align messaging to improve click rates and conversions.  \n- **Audience Engagement Focus:** Balancing awareness and lead generation is key; ongoing testing to enhance effectiveness in campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Christina Bila**\nInform Tim about recording requirements for compilation video and confirm his availability (07:30)\nVerify and report on the number of guide downloads via Salesforce and LinkedIn; follow up with Sean if needed (13:10)\nUpdate marketers after internal phase two campaign discussion early next week (16:45)\nCheck with Gab on Tuesday regarding CES episode videos and raw materials (09:57)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nFollow up with Gab on pending CES materials once she returns to office (09:57)\nSend full campaign performance report to Christina for review (17:14)\nPrepare and implement creative refresh and audience refinement based on campaign performance insights (15:40)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSupport explanation of campaign targeting techniques and optimize campaign according to Christina’s feedback (11:55)\nContinue monitoring campaign awareness and engagement, supporting potential improvements in creative and messaging (13:38)\n"},"duration":19.360000610351562,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"Christina Bila"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, hey, hey.","index":0,"end_time":211.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, look at fireflies.","index":1,"end_time":213.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s here now.","index":2,"end_time":214.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Now it''s working.","index":3,"end_time":216.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":217.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Not sure why it didn''t work last week.","index":5,"end_time":220.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.84,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Did you change any settings?","index":6,"end_time":222.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, no.","index":7,"end_time":224.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I just tried to connect Zoom and Fireflies, but then it said, I cannot connect it.","index":8,"end_time":229.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":224.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And I was like, okay.","index":9,"end_time":231.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then I told you that, yeah, I need to work on it, and then it just appeared magically today, so that''s cool.","index":10,"end_time":238.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.12,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Technology, man.","index":11,"end_time":241.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hi, team.","index":12,"end_time":251.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":250.58,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Hey.","index":13,"end_time":253.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.74,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"How are you?","index":14,"end_time":256.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.14,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great.","index":15,"end_time":259.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":258.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I feel like my camera is not working correctly.","index":16,"end_time":263.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.75,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So does your system have a hard time because you guys mostly use teams, right?","index":17,"end_time":270.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":18,"end_time":271.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":19,"end_time":271.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":271.67,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Zoom.","index":20,"end_time":272.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.95,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes.","index":21,"end_time":273.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.91,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":22,"end_time":274.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.39,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"It''s horrible for me.","index":23,"end_time":277.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.07,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I mean, I don''t even like teams, but I feel like overall, my laptop is just not that great.","index":24,"end_time":283.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":277.11,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I''ve had, like, two different laptops already, but it''s still, like, every time they get me a new one, I''m like, oh, maybe it''ll be great.","index":25,"end_time":290.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.27,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then I use it for a month, and then something always happens.","index":26,"end_time":294.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":290.69,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So I''m like, I don''t know at this point what''s happening, so.","index":27,"end_time":297.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":294.33,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":28,"end_time":297.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.09,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But at the new Active prospect, I believe they use Google.","index":29,"end_time":305.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":298.53,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Google Meet, so that''ll be interesting.","index":30,"end_time":309.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":306.53,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I''ve never used it before.","index":31,"end_time":310.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.13,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":32,"end_time":311.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I think Gab is out of office, and I don''t know.","index":33,"end_time":316.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":313.97,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Tim is joining us today, by the way.","index":34,"end_time":319.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":317.09,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Sorry, I feel like my connection is bad.","index":35,"end_time":322.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.89,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I feel like every time you speak, it''s kind of like.","index":36,"end_time":324.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.17,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I''m gonna turn off my camera for a little bit and see if that works.","index":37,"end_time":328.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.09,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, just let us know if we cut out or anything.","index":38,"end_time":332.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":336.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":335.65,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay.","index":40,"end_time":338.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.05,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":338.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.49,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Gab is out, and I don''t know if Tim''s going to join us, but we can get started.","index":42,"end_time":342.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.77,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":43,"end_time":343.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":44,"end_time":345.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Oh, by the way, welcome back, Bailey.","index":45,"end_time":348.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.84,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I feel like I haven''t seen you since last year, so it has been.","index":46,"end_time":352.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.4,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"It''s been a minute.","index":47,"end_time":353,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I was on vacation and then traveling, and I know Gab and Tim have been out, so.","index":48,"end_time":358.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good to be back.","index":49,"end_time":360.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":359.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":50,"end_time":362.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":361.56,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":51,"end_time":364.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":363.16,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay, so let me share my screen real quick.","index":52,"end_time":371.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":371.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":371.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then can you see it?","index":54,"end_time":376.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":55,"end_time":379.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":379.36,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":380.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":57,"end_time":381.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.44,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Let''s start with what we did this month.","index":58,"end_time":388.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.28,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"15 points have been delivered so far this month, including the distribution of episode Rustamirani.","index":59,"end_time":398.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.96,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also this is something we did, I think, this Monday or Tuesday.","index":60,"end_time":404.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.01,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab approved it.","index":61,"end_time":405.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the LinkedIn carousels for the episode.","index":62,"end_time":409.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bet Sullivan.","index":63,"end_time":410.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":64,"end_time":414.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.97,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And at the moment, the only active task we''re having is.","index":65,"end_time":423.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":415.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I mean, like, except for the monthly maintenance task is this one.","index":66,"end_time":430.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.73,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The campaign management and this is something we are going to talk more about in detail.","index":67,"end_time":438.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.39,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So A total of 23 points are in working status for this month as of this moment.","index":68,"end_time":446.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":69,"end_time":448.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.03,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And yeah, Tim somehow remember in our last meeting, Christina, how he just froze and then just disconnected and then he disappeared from the meeting right before this slide.","index":70,"end_time":461.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.11,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And now again he''s not here.","index":71,"end_time":465.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":463.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, hopefully he will.","index":72,"end_time":469.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"What do you need from.","index":73,"end_time":471.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":469.99,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay, I will let him know actually because I have a meeting with him.","index":74,"end_time":477.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.79,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Hopefully.","index":75,"end_time":477.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.11,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay.","index":76,"end_time":478.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":477.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s.","index":77,"end_time":480.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":78,"end_time":480.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.2,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s okay.","index":79,"end_time":481.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.76,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s basically a compilation video video for.","index":80,"end_time":485.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.08,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Based on last year''s episodes.","index":81,"end_time":488.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":486.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, we are basically waiting on him to record some intro I think part and also the in between parts, between the.","index":82,"end_time":498.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The guests parts.","index":83,"end_time":500.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":84,"end_time":500.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":500.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":500.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":501.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.8,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But you don''t have to bother him with this.","index":87,"end_time":505.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":502.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Like we can.","index":88,"end_time":506.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We can talk about it if he appears in the next meeting.","index":89,"end_time":509.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.52,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Good.","index":90,"end_time":510.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.46,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And then these are the upcoming priorities.","index":91,"end_time":517.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We will distribute.","index":92,"end_time":520.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So Gab noticed.","index":93,"end_time":522.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab.","index":94,"end_time":523.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab notified me that she uploaded the audio episode on Spotify and then gave a green light to distribute videos on YouTube and also next Thursday the video on Spotify full video episode.","index":95,"end_time":545.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.18,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So that will be done next week.","index":96,"end_time":548.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.59,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then regarding the CES episode, this is basically something we wanted to ask Gap.","index":97,"end_time":557.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":549.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this is.","index":98,"end_time":558.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This should write back key.","index":99,"end_time":559.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":558.75,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This is.","index":100,"end_time":560.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sorry, this is my.","index":101,"end_time":561.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"My typo.","index":102,"end_time":562.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":561.99,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So the link back is sent.","index":103,"end_time":564.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bailey, I think you mentioned it didn''t work.","index":104,"end_time":567.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.65,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":105,"end_time":568.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also the.","index":106,"end_time":570.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.57,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The videos that Gap said she.","index":107,"end_time":573.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"She was uploading, I don''t think we actually got them.","index":108,"end_time":577.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then I think Becky also when she comes back to the office, I think she will also send some.","index":109,"end_time":584.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":577.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Some and then we can.","index":110,"end_time":585.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.37,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think that will be like raw material completed.","index":111,"end_time":589.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But yeah, maybe you can.","index":112,"end_time":591.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.97,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Or we can.","index":113,"end_time":591.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We can check this with the Gab on Monday.","index":114,"end_time":594.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.85,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is she.","index":115,"end_time":595.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Is she in the office on Monday?","index":116,"end_time":596.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"She is going to be back on Tuesday.","index":117,"end_time":599.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":597.26,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I double check actually.","index":118,"end_time":602.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":601.42,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, Tuesday, not Monday.","index":119,"end_time":604.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":603.26,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay.","index":120,"end_time":605.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay, that''s fine.","index":121,"end_time":607.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":606.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Then we will check about this with her.","index":122,"end_time":610.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And yeah, also another question for her that we can also leave for next meeting since we mentioned in our last meeting that sometimes we can do a blog for the podcast episodes and then maybe, maybe this episode is a good opportunity to write like a mix of thought leadership blog tied in tied with into what varisc does and also some highlights from the episode.","index":123,"end_time":645.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.579,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah.","index":124,"end_time":646.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":645.53,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then now we come to the campaign report.","index":125,"end_time":655.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So as you know we launched the campaign in mid December and this was our overall monthly budget for all the campaigns and for both platforms so far the campaigns generated 40,000 impressions and 95 clicks, one lead overall.","index":126,"end_time":674.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.02,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And that was of course the MOFU campaign on LinkedIn.","index":127,"end_time":678.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"LinkedIn is driving is the primary performance channel and AdRoll is functioning as an awareness channel.","index":128,"end_time":689.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So contextual targeting is outperforming, retargeting and we also plan to modify and tighten audiences a bit for the efficiency of the addroll campaign.","index":129,"end_time":703.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.33,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay then the Tofu campaign is building awareness with mostly with financial services audiences with vice president showing the strongest engagement.","index":130,"end_time":713.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":704.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s good question.","index":131,"end_time":717.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.14,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"When you say contextual targeting is a performing retargeting, what do you mean by that?","index":132,"end_time":724.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":717.94,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I''m not really familiar with that.","index":133,"end_time":726.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":725.22,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, I can hop in there.","index":134,"end_time":729.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, so the retargeting is using that pixel that you installed on your website.","index":135,"end_time":737.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So if someone goes to certain pages it''ll retarget them and then contextual targeting is basically we inputted things about like their preferences and their jobs kind of stuff like that.","index":136,"end_time":751.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s not people who are coming to your website, it''s just people that we think would be interested.","index":137,"end_time":757.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There''s a bigger audience for that than the retargeting.","index":138,"end_time":762.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":759.41,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":139,"end_time":764.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":763.17,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":140,"end_time":766.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.09,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"This is so good so far.","index":141,"end_time":769.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.93,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"In my opinion this is my first ever campaign so I mean I, I''m biased so I think that''s good.","index":142,"end_time":774.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.17,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But we''ll see because we''re trying to push it until at least March because that''s when the law will take in effect.","index":143,"end_time":783.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":775.73,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So yeah, we''ll see.","index":144,"end_time":785.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":783.83,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Maybe they''ll.","index":145,"end_time":786.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":785.51,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Things will change more so and things will pick up, but we''ll see.","index":146,"end_time":789.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":786.55,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"How have the downloads been on your end with people actually like downloading the guide?","index":147,"end_time":796.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I think only I won''t have access to self force.","index":148,"end_time":801.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":797.19,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I will have to ask Sean, but I feel like we''ve gotten maybe two or couple of downloads.","index":149,"end_time":807.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.43,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I know the one from LinkedIn there was a download and form fill as well and I think there is a maybe one or two more but I will double check and verify I was shown on that.","index":150,"end_time":817.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.43,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be awesome.","index":151,"end_time":819.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.33,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, because the campaign seems to be doing really well at like keeping people aware of what''s going on.","index":152,"end_time":827.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like it seems to be getting to the right people.","index":153,"end_time":829.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.45,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I always like to see more downloads.","index":154,"end_time":834.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But we all, that''s what we all want to see.","index":155,"end_time":838.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean also part of it obviously that would be great to have all the downloads but also I think the other part of it that we wanted to drive is awareness of what''s happening and then maybe whoever is downloading can be like oh vms put this out.","index":156,"end_time":856.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":839.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I should reach out to VMS about this law that''s changing.","index":157,"end_time":860.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":856.52,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So we''ll see if that even happens in the future.","index":158,"end_time":864.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.92,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":159,"end_time":868.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And this is just a couple more things.","index":160,"end_time":871.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":869.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So as I said, so the MOFU campaign produced a lead and also based on your requirements from I think like 10, 10 days ago.","index":161,"end_time":885.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I think so, Christina.","index":162,"end_time":886.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We shifted this to conversions to improve lead quality and efficiency.","index":163,"end_time":890.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.38,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So now like we''re directing people, they should fill out the form on your website only.","index":164,"end_time":900.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So.","index":165,"end_time":900.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.34,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":166,"end_time":900.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then this is an interesting insight.","index":167,"end_time":905.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.82,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So creatives with lighter white backgrounds are clearly outperforming and they will guide upcoming optimizations.","index":168,"end_time":914.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So if you remember, we have two versions, so the white ones and the dark blue ones.","index":169,"end_time":923.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, the lighter ones are definitely performing better.","index":170,"end_time":927.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also.","index":171,"end_time":928.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry, no, I was just wondering like why that is.","index":172,"end_time":935.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":929.22,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That''s just so interesting that that''s happening.","index":173,"end_time":937.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.22,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But I don''t know, that''s.","index":174,"end_time":939.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.98,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, maybe people just like that design better.","index":175,"end_time":942.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And that is something also.","index":176,"end_time":944.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":944.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.26,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That we, we want to suggest that maybe the creatives are.","index":178,"end_time":950.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Should be.","index":179,"end_time":952.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":951.47,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So keeping this in mind and also the number, the number of impressions is, is good.","index":180,"end_time":958.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.51,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"But then the number of clicks is then so the, the reach and the awareness, as Bailey said.","index":181,"end_time":967.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So a lot of people actually see the, the, the ads, but then not so many of them actually click on the ads.","index":182,"end_time":977.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.19,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And this has to do with.","index":183,"end_time":978.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.61,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, with the creatives and copy.","index":184,"end_time":981.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So one of the, one of our suggestions is to do some optimization and refresh on the creatives to land better messaging and actually get more people to engage because that''s, that''s what we all want.","index":185,"end_time":995.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":982.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And another thing is to exclude some irrelevant audiences which will then just help.","index":186,"end_time":1002.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Help us have better context.","index":187,"end_time":1005.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.12,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":188,"end_time":1006.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.68,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I think that''ll be great actually update because this part of the plan, this is like phase one, we have a meeting next week for phase two campaign.","index":189,"end_time":1019.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.2,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Maybe when we optimize the messaging of it as well, we can work together to refine and fine tune that.","index":190,"end_time":1027.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.96,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But I''ll keep you updated after the meeting.","index":191,"end_time":1030.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1028.87,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I think it''s on Tuesday or Wednesday next week, so.","index":192,"end_time":1033.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1030.59,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":193,"end_time":1034.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1033.99,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":194,"end_time":1035.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.95,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":195,"end_time":1036.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.91,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also here''s a full report and if you want to look at it, I can send it over.","index":196,"end_time":1041.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1036.79,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be really great.","index":197,"end_time":1043.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1042.15,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":198,"end_time":1043.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.23,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Sure.","index":199,"end_time":1044.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.389,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And that''s it on the agenda.","index":200,"end_time":1051.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":201,"end_time":1051.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.43,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Any questions on your side?","index":202,"end_time":1053.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.83,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No questions.","index":203,"end_time":1056.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.28,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I think everything is looking good, specifically on HR2808.","index":204,"end_time":1061.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.04,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"And also obviously, always, as always, great job on the delivery of the episodes and stuff.","index":205,"end_time":1067.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1062.56,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But I think another thing we have another what is it?","index":206,"end_time":1075.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Campaign for one of our product total IP addresses.","index":207,"end_time":1078.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.24,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"We might need your help with that.","index":208,"end_time":1081.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.76,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"But that''s question mark because we want to see how HR 2808 is performing before we start working on any campaign tactics for that one.","index":209,"end_time":1093.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1081.44,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"So just something to keep in mind and you know, for the future.","index":210,"end_time":1097.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1093.46,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Sure, we''ll be happy to work on them.","index":211,"end_time":1100.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.779,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":212,"end_time":1102.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1101.74,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Nice.","index":213,"end_time":1102.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1102.46,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t have anything else.","index":214,"end_time":1105.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.9,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys have anything else.","index":215,"end_time":1106.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1105.14,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Bailey.","index":216,"end_time":1107.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1106.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No, that''s everything.","index":217,"end_time":1108.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1107.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Always great to see you, Christina.","index":218,"end_time":1110.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":219,"end_time":1112.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.73,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"You too.","index":220,"end_time":1112.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.09,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Sorry my camera is not working.","index":221,"end_time":1113.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.49,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"My Internet is horrible.","index":222,"end_time":1114.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.57,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"The cold here is bad, so.","index":223,"end_time":1118.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.81,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":224,"end_time":1120.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.13,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":225,"end_time":1121.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1120.69,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":226,"end_time":1121.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.25,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No problem.","index":227,"end_time":1122.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.81,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Okay then.","index":228,"end_time":1124.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.49,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":229,"end_time":1125.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1125.25,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Great talking to you and see you soon.","index":230,"end_time":1128.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.13,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yes.","index":231,"end_time":1129.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1128.61,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"See you guys.","index":232,"end_time":1129.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.01,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Bye.","index":233,"end_time":1129.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1129.57,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Bye.","index":234,"end_time":1130.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1129.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":235,"end_time":1130.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.21,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Bye.","index":236,"end_time":1136.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.49,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"}],"dateString":"2026-01-23T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84418344570?pwd=Q4jwjvSlBFex6HPeIBY3JaK1RFchWb.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com,gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com,tim.finnigan@verisk.com,christina.bila@verisk.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","gabrielle.verzella@verisk.com","tim.finnigan@verisk.com","christina.bila@verisk.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFH2VAS9XD7K4CGM7RSQHHQH","organizer_email":"igor.zagradjanin@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Delivered 15 story points this month, including distribution of Rustamirani and Bet Sullivan episodes.","Confirmed LinkedIn MOFU campaign yielded one lead; shifted to conversions to boost efficiency.","Identified white-background creatives strongly outperform blue versions, guiding future asset optimization.","Suggested excluding irrelevant audiences and updating copy to increase engagement from impressions.","Planned to align phase two messaging optimizations next week around HR2808 campaign performance."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Creatives with lighter white backgrounds are clearly outperforming and they will guide upcoming optimizations.","speaker":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"quote":"Everything is looking good, specifically on HR2808.","speaker":"Christina Bila"},{"quote":"The campaign seems to be doing really well at like keeping people aware of what''s going on.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["campaign","delivery","optimization","engagement"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-26T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Production and Distribution**\n\nThe team successfully delivered **15 content points this month**, including the **Rustamirani episode** and LinkedIn carousel posts approved by **Gab** (06:19).\n\n- The only active task beyond monthly maintenance is **campaign management**, with **23 points currently in progress** this month.\n- A compilation video using last year’s episodes is pending **Tim’s recording of intro and transition parts**, expected to resume in the next meeting.\n- Upcoming priorities include distributing the recently uploaded **Spotify audio episode** and scheduling the **full video episode for next Thursday** on Spotify.\n- The team plans to confirm with **Gab**, returning Tuesday, on missing CES episode videos and raw material for completion.\n- There is potential to create a **thought leadership blog** tied to podcast episodes, starting with the upcoming one, to enhance content reach and brand positioning.\n\n## **Marketing Campaign Performance**\n\nThe mid-December campaign reached **40,000 impressions**, generated **95 clicks**, and produced **1 lead** so far, focused on **LinkedIn (MOFU)** and **AdRoll (awareness)** platforms (10:49).\n\n- **Contextual targeting** on AdRoll outperforms retargeting by reaching broader, interest-based audiences rather than website visitors, as explained by **Baylee**.\n- The campaign targets financial services, with **Vice Presidents showing the strongest engagement**.\n- Campaign budget is planned to continue until **March**, aligned with the upcoming law effective date, to maximize awareness.\n- Downloads of the campaign guide are low, with only about **2-3 downloads reported**, but the main goal is to boost awareness and prompt outreach to the company.\n- The MOFU campaign was shifted to focus on **conversions via website form fills** to improve lead quality and efficiency, following **Christina’s request** about 10 days ago.\n- Creatives with **lighter white backgrounds clearly outperform dark blue ones**, guiding future design choices.\n- Despite good reach, click-through rates are low, attributed to creatives and copy, prompting plans for a **creative refresh and messaging optimization** to improve engagement.\n- The team will also **exclude irrelevant audiences** to improve targeting quality and efficiency.\n- A phase two campaign meeting is scheduled next week, where messaging and targeting refinements will be discussed collaboratively.\n\n## **Strategic Planning and Future Campaigns**\n\nThe team is monitoring the **HR2808 campaign’s performance** before launching new campaigns, including one for the **Total IP Addresses product** (17:35).\n\n- **Christina** emphasized the need to evaluate current campaign results before deploying new tactics, ensuring resource focus and data-driven decisions.\n- The team expressed readiness to support future campaigns once HR2808 insights are available.\n- This phased approach reflects a cautious, data-driven marketing strategy to optimize budget and maximize impact.\n\n## **Operational and Communication Challenges**\n\nTechnical and scheduling issues impacted meeting participation and content production (07:30).\n\n- **Tim’s connection issues** delayed recording tasks, creating dependencies in video compilation.\n- **Gab’s absence until Tuesday** affects access to necessary media assets for CES episode finalization.\n- The team agreed to follow up with Gab after her return to maintain workflow continuity.\n- **Christina’s laptop and connection issues** highlight ongoing challenges with tools and platforms, affecting remote collaboration quality.\n- Transition to **Google Meet for Active Prospect** is anticipated, potentially affecting future meeting stability.\n\n## **Creative and Audience Insights**\n\nData-driven creative decisions are shaping campaign optimizations to increase engagement and lead generation (14:27).\n\n- The clear preference for **lighter, white-background creatives** informs upcoming design standards.\n- Insights into audience engagement reveal that while many see the ads, fewer click, indicating a need for better messaging alignment.\n- Ongoing testing and refinement will focus on improving click rates and form fills by aligning creative style and copy more closely with audience preferences.\n- The team plans to maintain a balance between awareness and lead generation to support both brand recognition and conversion goals.","outline":null,"keywords":["Fireflies","Zoom integration","CES episode","LinkedIn campaign","contextual targeting","lead generation"],"overview":"- **Content Delivery Success:** Delivered 15 content points this month, focusing on recent episodes and social media posts.  \n- **Campaign Insights:** Mid-December campaign achieved 40,000 impressions, 95 clicks, and 1 lead; shifts needed for better engagement.  \n- **Strategic Planning Emphasis:** Evaluating HR2808 campaign results is crucial before launching new tactics, ensuring focused efforts.  \n- **Operational Hurdles:** Technical issues impacted meeting participation and production; follow-up on content tasks is essential post-absence.  \n- **Creative Optimization:** Lighter creatives perform better; future designs will align messaging to improve click rates and conversions.  \n- **Audience Engagement Focus:** Balancing awareness and lead generation is key; ongoing testing to enhance effectiveness in campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Christina Bila**\nInform Tim about recording requirements for compilation video and confirm his availability (07:30)\nVerify and report on the number of guide downloads via Salesforce and LinkedIn; follow up with Sean if needed (13:10)\nUpdate marketers after internal phase two campaign discussion early next week (16:45)\nCheck with Gab on Tuesday regarding CES episode videos and raw materials (09:57)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nFollow up with Gab on pending CES materials once she returns to office (09:57)\nSend full campaign performance report to Christina for review (17:14)\nPrepare and implement creative refresh and audience refinement based on campaign performance insights (15:40)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nSupport explanation of campaign targeting techniques and optimize campaign according to Christina’s feedback (11:55)\nContinue monitoring campaign awareness and engagement, supporting potential improvements in creative and messaging (13:38)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a0599004-1cd1-4e6e-a7bc-70b24d3578b7","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
