INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Content Production and Distribution**

The team successfully delivered **15 content points this month**, including the **Rustamirani episode** and LinkedIn carousel posts approved by **Gab** (06:19).

- The only active task beyond monthly maintenance is **campaign management**, with **23 points currently in progress** this month.
- A compilation video using last year’s episodes is pending **Tim’s recording of intro and transition parts**, expected to resume in the next meeting.
- Upcoming priorities include distributing the recently uploaded **Spotify audio episode** and scheduling the **full video episode for next Thursday** on Spotify.
- The team plans to confirm with **Gab**, returning Tuesday, on missing CES episode videos and raw material for completion.
- There is potential to create a **thought leadership blog** tied to podcast episodes, starting with the upcoming one, to enhance content reach and brand positioning.

## **Marketing Campaign Performance**

The mid-December campaign reached **40,000 impressions**, generated **95 clicks**, and produced **1 lead** so far, focused on **LinkedIn (MOFU)** and **AdRoll (awareness)** platforms (10:49).

- **Contextual targeting** on AdRoll outperforms retargeting by reaching broader, interest-based audiences rather than website visitors, as explained by **Baylee**.
- The campaign targets financial services, with **Vice Presidents showing the strongest engagement**.
- Campaign budget is planned to continue until **March**, aligned with the upcoming law effective date, to maximize awareness.
- Downloads of the campaign guide are low, with only about **2-3 downloads reported**, but the main goal is to boost awareness and prompt outreach to the company.
- The MOFU campaign was shifted to focus on **conversions via website form fills** to improve lead quality and efficiency, following **Christina’s request** about 10 days ago.
- Creatives with **lighter white backgrounds clearly outperform dark blue ones**, guiding future design choices.
- Despite good reach, click-through rates are low, attributed to creatives and copy, prompting plans for a **creative refresh and messaging optimization** to improve engagement.
- The team will also **exclude irrelevant audiences** to improve targeting quality and efficiency.
- A phase two campaign meeting is scheduled next week, where messaging and targeting refinements will be discussed collaboratively.

## **Strategic Planning and Future Campaigns**

The team is monitoring the **HR2808 campaign’s performance** before launching new campaigns, including one for the **Total IP Addresses product** (17:35).

- **Christina** emphasized the need to evaluate current campaign results before deploying new tactics, ensuring resource focus and data-driven decisions.
- The team expressed readiness to support future campaigns once HR2808 insights are available.
- This phased approach reflects a cautious, data-driven marketing strategy to optimize budget and maximize impact.

## **Operational and Communication Challenges**

Technical and scheduling issues impacted meeting participation and content production (07:30).

- **Tim’s connection issues** delayed recording tasks, creating dependencies in video compilation.
- **Gab’s absence until Tuesday** affects access to necessary media assets for CES episode finalization.
- The team agreed to follow up with Gab after her return to maintain workflow continuity.
- **Christina’s laptop and connection issues** highlight ongoing challenges with tools and platforms, affecting remote collaboration quality.
- Transition to **Google Meet for Active Prospect** is anticipated, potentially affecting future meeting stability.

## **Creative and Audience Insights**

Data-driven creative decisions are shaping campaign optimizations to increase engagement and lead generation (14:27).

- The clear preference for **lighter, white-background creatives** informs upcoming design standards.
- Insights into audience engagement reveal that while many see the ads, fewer click, indicating a need for better messaging alignment.
- Ongoing testing and refinement will focus on improving click rates and form fills by aligning creative style and copy more closely with audience preferences.
- The team plans to maintain a balance between awareness and lead generation to support both brand recognition and conversion goals.',
  '2026-01-23 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Inform Tim about recording requirements for compilation video and confirm his availability (07:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Verify and report on the number of guide downloads via Salesforce and LinkedIn; follow up with Sean if needed (13:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Update marketers after internal phase two campaign discussion early next week (16:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Check with Gab on Tuesday regarding CES episode videos and raw materials (09:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Follow up with Gab on pending CES materials once she returns to office (09:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Send full campaign performance report to Christina for review (17:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare and implement creative refresh and audience refinement based on campaign performance insights (15:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Support explanation of campaign targeting techniques and optimize campaign according to Christina’s feedback (11:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue monitoring campaign awareness and engagement, supporting potential improvements in creative and messaging (13:38)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
