WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '66a4318e-0698-422f-854d-3aeb4c4bd804',
    '2026-01-22 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFH3Y02SXXXY5TFYYVHMYW61',
    'WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW)',
    '{"Andrew Hill","Christine Saur","Don Hill","Nina Belina","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    2108,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85897587831?pwd=hDlQElXqYVOp2bzGDuaodhOZVUT4GB.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KFH3Y02SXXXY5TFYYVHMYW61","title":"WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW)","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nMarketing efforts have maintained strong lead engagement despite a challenging business environment.\n\n- **Google Ads delivered 42 conversions with a continued 13% lead volume growth**, driven by both the general brand campaign and the targeted Costco campaign, showing that brand awareness remains strong and top-of-mind for emergency freight services (09:32)  \n    - Geo-fencing targeting for the Costco campaign was reinstated after noticing leads from those locations, confirming effective regional focus  \n    - **Cost per conversion remained stable**, despite increased competition bidding on the brand name, which raised cost per click slightly  \n    - Nina emphasized the importance of quality leads over quantity to ensure marketing spend drives real business  \n    - Top converting keywords include **cross docking services, ballot restacking, temporary warehousing, and lumber services near me**, aligning closely with core service offerings  \n    - AdRoll campaigns showed stable performance with **26,000+ impressions, 23 clicks, and 1 conversion**, supporting brand awareness outside of search ads  \n\n- **The “Emergency Card” resource gained traction with 23 downloads**, including repeat interest signaling growing client engagement with helpful content (10:56)  \n    - Data analytics recommendations include targeting **3 to 5 major distribution hubs and large 3PL centers for geo-fencing** and optimizing existing landing pages for SEO to reduce paid lead costs  \n    - Nina proposed addressing common client questions and misconceptions during sales calls through targeted content to improve lead comfort and conversion  \n\n## **Sales and Lead Quality Challenges**\n\nCurrent lead volume contrasts with poor business conversion, highlighting gaps between marketing and sales outcomes.\n\n- **Christine reported a significant drop in business activity, calling January the slowest in over three years despite healthy lead flow**, indicating that leads are not translating into sales (14:10)  \n    - She attributed lower conversion partly to economic conditions and customer price sensitivity, especially among drivers reluctant to pay out of pocket  \n    - Chris stressed the need to target brokers more aggressively, as they represent higher-value customers than drivers  \n    - Calls to action conversion rates remain unclear due to lack of consistent follow-up and lead status tracking  \n\n- **Andrew proposed establishing a feedback loop between sales and marketing to track which leads convert and which don’t, including reasons for lost sales**, to refine keyword targeting and improve lead quality (18:30)  \n    - He offered to analyze existing sales spreadsheets and HubSpot CRM data to bridge gaps and identify lead outcomes over the past 60-90 days  \n    - Baylee agreed to align on CRM data organization and dashboard creation to streamline lead tracking without complicating sales workflows  \n    - The group recognized that a CRM-driven process is crucial to improve sales follow-up, lead nurturing, and marketing ROI, especially to support future sales hires  \n\n## **CRM Integration and Process Improvements**\n\nAdopting CRM tools and improving data tracking are critical steps to enhance sales efficiency and growth potential.\n\n- **Andrew emphasized the strategic value of a CRM system to manage leads, automate follow-ups, and provide actionable sales insights**, highlighting its role in scaling sales efforts and improving customer relationships (21:30)  \n    - He pointed out that CRM adoption would help future salespeople systematically follow up on unconverted leads, turning marketing spend into more closed deals  \n    - Baylee and Andrew agreed on starting with simple spreadsheet data sharing and moving toward more integrated HubSpot dashboards and workflows after further discussion  \n    - The team plans to share lead data including company names, contact info, and deal close dates for the last 90 days to enable initial analysis and CRM alignment  \n\n- **Chris confirmed she can provide monthly sales spreadsheets with job numbers and business names but noted challenges linking individual drivers to companies within current tracking** (32:00)  \n    - The group agreed not to require sensitive financial data, focusing instead on identifiers useful for matching marketing leads to sales outcomes  \n    - This data will enable reverse engineering of conversions and losses to better understand lead quality and ROI  \n\n## **Market and Economic Context**\n\nExternal economic factors and market conditions are influencing demand and website traffic trends.\n\n- **Baylee reported a 20% overall drop in website traffic in January compared to December, with a notable 37% decrease in direct traffic from brand searches** (30:50)  \n    - The reduction in direct traffic suggests fewer repeat or returning visitors aware of the brand, supporting Chris’s assessment of a slow market  \n    - Paid search traffic remained relatively stable despite increased cost per click due to competitive bidding  \n    - Andrew and Don discussed the importance of monitoring industry-wide transportation volumes and economic indicators to contextualize business performance  \n    - Understanding whether slowdowns are due to lower freight demand or increased competition will help guide marketing and sales strategies  \n\n- **Don highlighted the importance of maintaining top Google search rankings for “freight repair,” considering it a key competitive advantage for capturing urgent customer needs** (15:10)  \n    - This visibility supports brand positioning as the go-to emergency service provider despite market headwinds  \n\n## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to focus on improving lead quality tracking, enhancing CRM integration, and refining marketing content to boost conversion.\n\n- **Immediate priority is to provide and analyze the last 90 days of sales data to match marketing leads with actual jobs won or lost**, forming the basis for a feedback loop to optimize campaigns (24:00)  \n    - Baylee will work with Andrew and Chris to define CRM dashboard requirements and lead tracking processes without overcomplicating existing workflows  \n    - The team plans a follow-up discussion to review HubSpot capabilities and determine resource allocation for CRM adoption and lead management improvements  \n\n- **Content strategy will evolve to address common client questions and misconceptions, aiming to reduce friction in the sales process and improve customer trust** (09:45)  \n    - Optimizing existing landing pages for SEO will balance paid efforts with organic growth, lowering lead acquisition costs over time  \n\n- **Longer-term vision includes hiring dedicated sales personnel supported by CRM tools to follow up on leads and build stronger customer relationships, increasing conversion rates and revenue growth** (21:30)  \n    - This approach reflects a shift from relying solely on marketing to proactive sales outreach as a growth lever during slow economic periods  \n\n- **Business leaders will continue monitoring external economic and transportation activity metrics to better understand demand fluctuations and adjust strategies accordingly** (27:00)","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","Lead Conversion","CRM Integration","HubSpot","Economic Slowdown","Geofencing"],"overview":"- **Strong Google Ads Performance:** Achieved 42 conversions with 13% lead growth, driven by brand and Costco campaigns.\n\n- **Sales Activity Decline:** January was the slowest month in over three years, despite healthy lead flow, highlighting conversion issues.\n\n- **CRM System Importance:** Proposed CRM adoption for lead management and tracking will improve sales follow-ups and marketing ROI.\n\n- **Website Traffic Concerns:** January saw a 20% drop in traffic, with urgent need to maintain Google search rankings for key terms.\n\n- **Content Strategy Evolution:** Focus on common client questions to reduce sales friction and enhance trust, optimizing landing pages for SEO.\n\n- **Long-term Vision:** Consider hiring dedicated sales staff alongside CRM tools to boost lead conversion and overall revenue growth.","action_items":"\n**Andrew Hill**\nVolunteer to review internal spreadsheet of converted and non-converted leads and assist in matching data with HubSpot CRM records (20:10)\nProvide marketers with a spreadsheet of last 90 days’ closed jobs detailing company names and closing dates for CRM integration (26:15)\n\n**Christine Saur**\nSend spreadsheet data of last three months of closed jobs including company names and closure dates to marketing team (32:00)\nCoordinate internally to gather and deliver lead contact information for marketers to analyze (31:50)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAnalyze shared data and demonstrate potential HubSpot CRM dashboards and tracking functionalities to the team (26:50)\nProvide comparison report of website traffic between December and January to assess business volume trends (28:10)\n\n**Unassigned**\nPlan a follow-up meeting to discuss refining goals and strategies for the year based on marketing and sales data alignment (12:25)\n"},"duration":35.130001068115234,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Andrew Hill"},{"id":1,"name":"Christine Saur"},{"id":2,"name":"Don Hill"},{"id":3,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":4,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam, Am I on there?","index":0,"end_time":250.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":1,"end_time":250.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.09,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay.","index":2,"end_time":251.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.57,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"My video and on.","index":3,"end_time":254.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.93,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":254.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.17,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yep.","index":5,"end_time":254.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":254.45,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Hi.","index":6,"end_time":256.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.94,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Hello.","index":7,"end_time":259.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hello, Nina.","index":8,"end_time":260.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":259.7,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"How are you?","index":9,"end_time":262.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":261.86,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":10,"end_time":263.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.3,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"How are you?","index":11,"end_time":266.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.46,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":12,"end_time":267.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":266.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It''s been a busy day, but it''s great.","index":13,"end_time":269.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":267.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Happy New Year.","index":14,"end_time":270.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":269.7,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":15,"end_time":271.499,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":270.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Happy New Year too, as well.","index":16,"end_time":272.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":271.499,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hello, everyone.","index":17,"end_time":275.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I''m under the weather again, but I wanted to make sure I made the call.","index":18,"end_time":280.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.26,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"What''s wrong with you?","index":19,"end_time":282.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.11,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Double ear infection and sinus infection.","index":20,"end_time":286.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.63,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Been sick.","index":21,"end_time":287.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.75,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Oh, God.","index":22,"end_time":287.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":287.39,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Wow, Andy.","index":23,"end_time":290.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.39,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":291.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.67,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yep.","index":25,"end_time":291.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.23,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I''ve had a string of bad luck.","index":26,"end_time":293.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.67,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":293.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.47,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Sorry to hear that.","index":28,"end_time":294.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":293.87,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":296.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.63,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Well, I just went to the doctor for the second time this week this morning and got a new antibiotic.","index":30,"end_time":302.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.51,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I had.","index":31,"end_time":302.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"They thought I had strep earlier this week, and they treated that and it kind of either morphed into this or I had it in conjunction.","index":32,"end_time":312.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.71,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"One of the two, but hopefully on to.","index":33,"end_time":317.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"To healthier pastures with new meds, I hope.","index":34,"end_time":321.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Hi, Bailey.","index":35,"end_time":324.939,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, good to see you.","index":36,"end_time":326.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":325.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your studio looks awesome.","index":37,"end_time":328.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":326.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, thank you.","index":38,"end_time":329.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.7,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":39,"end_time":330.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I was worried.","index":40,"end_time":332.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.42,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I worked on it myself personally.","index":41,"end_time":335.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":332.26,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Kind of built the feature wall and the shelves and I think it turned out pretty good.","index":42,"end_time":341.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":335.24,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":43,"end_time":341.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.28,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, I love the wooden panels.","index":44,"end_time":344.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":342.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Your, like LED light.","index":45,"end_time":346.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":344.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s.","index":46,"end_time":346.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":346.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s a great setup.","index":47,"end_time":347.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":346.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":48,"end_time":348.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.96,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":49,"end_time":349.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.84,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, my dad got to see it over Christmas break when he was here.","index":50,"end_time":353.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.28,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Oh, fun.","index":51,"end_time":354.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":353.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I did.","index":52,"end_time":355.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.92,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It was awesome.","index":53,"end_time":357.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.2,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":54,"end_time":358.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":357.56,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"It''s old barnwood, actually, that I. I used in my basement for a feature wall.","index":55,"end_time":364.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.24,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Oh, cool.","index":56,"end_time":365.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":364.74,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I liked it so much that I ended up using a lot of what I had left over, so.","index":57,"end_time":372.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.02,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":58,"end_time":374.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":373.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Barely.","index":59,"end_time":375.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.58,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I let them know I''m kind of under the weather, but I wanted to make sure I made the.","index":60,"end_time":378.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The meeting today.","index":61,"end_time":379.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.5,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So if you hear it in my voice or what have you, I''m.","index":62,"end_time":383.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.62,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I''m here and this is important.","index":63,"end_time":384.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.46,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So.","index":64,"end_time":385.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, thank.","index":65,"end_time":387.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":386.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thanks for joining.","index":66,"end_time":388.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":387.3,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s never fun to be on camera when you''re not feeling well.","index":67,"end_time":391.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":388.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, no sweat, no sweat.","index":68,"end_time":393.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.58,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I hope everybody else is feeling well.","index":69,"end_time":394.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.1,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I know the flu is horrible.","index":70,"end_time":396.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.86,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":71,"end_time":399.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":398.46,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hi, Chris.","index":72,"end_time":401.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.7,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"All right, so I''m ready to dive in if you guys are.","index":73,"end_time":408.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.42,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Let''s do it.","index":74,"end_time":411.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.86,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Dad, you want to kick us off, Nina?","index":75,"end_time":415.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":414.22,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":76,"end_time":416.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":416.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":77,"end_time":418.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":417.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this week we are going through our project updates.","index":78,"end_time":432.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":428.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mentioned a couple of emails ago about the cross docking and Olympus services landing page which has been done and we only need you to approve if everything is all right from your end and we can add it to the resources page.","index":79,"end_time":448.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":433.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We also have a issue that is a little bit starting to be on schedule.","index":80,"end_time":455.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":449.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We''ve been waiting for the Women''s conference swag choice, like if you want to have any kind of gift during the conference.","index":81,"end_time":465.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":455.51,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And we made a list of items and the price tag for each one.","index":82,"end_time":469.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":465.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So if you, we can take that one off there.","index":83,"end_time":473.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":470.15,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''ve already taken care of that.","index":84,"end_time":474.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":473.07,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":85,"end_time":475.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":474.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the Google Ads, I wanted to mention that engagement is really going well.","index":86,"end_time":482.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":476.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Our impressions are up and clicks are also up, which is probably because we''ve passed that holiday period and things are, you know, moving even faster than they were at the end of December.","index":87,"end_time":495.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":483.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So let''s go through the Google Ads, the conversions this week we had 42 and the cost per conversion was $, which is a great surge.","index":88,"end_time":509.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":497.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"When it comes to previous weeks we see that people are growing more and more interested.","index":89,"end_time":516.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":509.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And what I mentioned last week about the geo fencing in Google Ads on our last meeting at the beginning of the month, I mentioned to Chris that we noticed that we had people reaching out from the geographical locations that we targeted during the Costco campaign.","index":90,"end_time":537.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":516.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we decided, decided to allocate the budget again between the general and campaign and the Costco campaign to see if we have an increase of people who would directly become leads from the Costco campaign.","index":91,"end_time":552.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":537.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And we can say now that both Costco and the brand campaigns are performing well.","index":92,"end_time":559.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it means that people have kept we fix right on top of their mind when it comes to who to call when they have an emergency, which is really great.","index":93,"end_time":571.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":559.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And we also maintain the healthy lead volume growth of 13% which is really great data.","index":94,"end_time":581.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":572.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Our top converting keywords are cross docking services, ballot restacking, temporary warehousing and lumber services near me.","index":95,"end_time":591.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":582.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"These are all options for our topics, but as I''ve also mentioned it in the emails, we can also go through some common questions that you get asked during sales calls or some maybe misconceptions that people have when it comes to fried services because it''s always good to kind of clear things up and just, you know, address some issues that you see are recurring with customers or potential clients where they might not be sure like what kind, what kind of a service they''re getting or if they have some common smaller issues that that might, might make them feel even more comfortable.","index":96,"end_time":632.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":591.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Working with XPRIZE when it comes to AdRoll, we had a good number of impressions.","index":97,"end_time":639.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":632.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So over 26,000 we have one conversions and 23 clicks.","index":98,"end_time":645.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":639.24,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The performance is stable and it''s in this, in our expectation when it comes to budget and audience size.","index":99,"end_time":654.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":645.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And our engagement is driven by save the mar hero narrative creatives.","index":100,"end_time":662.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":655.48,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"When it comes to the emergency card, we had 23 downloads.","index":101,"end_time":666.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":663.22,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And what''s interesting, we had one person who downloaded it multiple times.","index":102,"end_time":670.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So obviously it''s gaining a lot of interest.","index":103,"end_time":674.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for data analytics, we had a couple of suggestions which also mentioned to Chris on our previous meeting, which is to maybe identify additional three or five major distribution hubs, for example, competitors or large three PL centers to GeoFext, and also for SEO optimization of existing pages.","index":104,"end_time":698.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":676.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So, for example, we don''t always have to create new landing pages.","index":105,"end_time":702.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":698.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We can also optimize the one that we have on the website to match them to the keywords that we see showing up in Google.","index":106,"end_time":710.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":702.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because the more people click organically, the less we pay for the cost per lead.","index":107,"end_time":715.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":710.08,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it works well in our advantage and for the items for that need to review.","index":108,"end_time":724.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":715.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we already went through the women''s conference.","index":109,"end_time":728.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":724.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"One of the things is adding new landing pages to the resource page and deciding which topics to target next.","index":110,"end_time":735.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":729.13,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And also we wanted to discuss goals and strategies for this year from your side.","index":111,"end_time":741.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":735.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And that''s all from a lot of.","index":112,"end_time":749.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":746.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Information there, but like questions or thoughts says we''re going through stuff.","index":113,"end_time":754.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":749.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''ll jump in first.","index":114,"end_time":757.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":755.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It sounds like the idea to Geofence was really something that worked out well, which I think I had mentioned, I don''t know, 60 days ago, so.","index":115,"end_time":770.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But it also looks like it''s increased the cost per click because it''s more targeted or is that just happening because of more competition?","index":116,"end_time":782.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.82,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So it''s mostly happening because of competition, because a lot of the times the competitors also bid for our brand name and that increases the price.","index":117,"end_time":792.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":782.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, but you''re always going to see different, different numbers on very specific campaigns.","index":118,"end_time":800.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":793.21,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So, for example, something that''s very narrow, like a geofencing campaign and a general campaign, which is more wide in scope.","index":119,"end_time":808.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.09,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But if our conversion to our call to action, our conversion percentage is higher, it doesn''t matter as much that the expense goes up because ultimately that''s the goal is to get the most number of conversions within.","index":120,"end_time":825.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.17,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The goal is to get quality leads.","index":121,"end_time":828.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.57,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So people who are really interested in the service.","index":122,"end_time":831.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":828.65,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":123,"end_time":833.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.5,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And so that''s a perfect segue to Chris to ask her what the quality has been like, because she''s the one that can, you know, give us the insight on that.","index":124,"end_time":843.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.22,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Say, because, you know, what you''re presenting looks really good, but the business right now is terrible.","index":125,"end_time":856.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.38,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Like, we''re very, very slow.","index":126,"end_time":858.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":856.9,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We''re struggling to make it through this month.","index":127,"end_time":861.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":859.76,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So, you know, I''m not really seeing the results that.","index":128,"end_time":866.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.36,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I mean, what you''re presenting doesn''t isn''t really representative of what we''re seeing.","index":129,"end_time":870.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.04,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":130,"end_time":871.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":871.04,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Like, you say, oh, this is great.","index":131,"end_time":873.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.16,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Everything looks great.","index":132,"end_time":874.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.72,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"People are really looking at this, but we''re not getting the business from it.","index":133,"end_time":878.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.48,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So that''s where I think Nina at the end had kind of mentioned, like, goals for this year.","index":134,"end_time":886.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":880.48,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So as of right now, I know we''re like, not in HubSpot a lot.","index":135,"end_time":891.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":887.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So I feel like there is a bit of a disconnect between, like, what we''re doing, which is trying to get people to fill out forms.","index":136,"end_time":899.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":892.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And from what we can see, lots of people are filling out forms.","index":137,"end_time":902.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":899.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But then it''s kind of just like, okay, Chris, let''s see.","index":138,"end_time":905.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":902.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s see what happens.","index":139,"end_time":906.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":905.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Let''s see if we can get the business.","index":140,"end_time":908.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":906.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And we''re not really intertwined in that.","index":141,"end_time":911.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":908.29,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, like, if you want, we can have another conversation to talk about, like, what your goals are for this next year and to see where we can maybe plug in more.","index":142,"end_time":919.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":912.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''d like to weigh in.","index":143,"end_time":922.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.6,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"I. Andy, you, you were, you missed the Christmas thing that we do with Bill and, and Chris.","index":144,"end_time":930.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":923.52,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"But I met with Bill separately before and he showed me that when you look for freight repair, we fix freight is at the top.","index":145,"end_time":939.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.76,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"As far as the Google search, to me, that''s crucially important, and I was very, very happy to see that and whatever it takes for us to be at the top.","index":146,"end_time":950.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.08,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Because I got to tell you, if you''re a driver who''s got a repair job that needs to be done and you''re quickly Google searching and we come up to the top of the list, to me, that''s half the battle right there.","index":147,"end_time":965.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.2,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Now, Chris, I don''t know how January compares to this same time period last year, do you?","index":148,"end_time":973.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.59,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"It could be because it''s January and.","index":149,"end_time":976.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":974.27,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"You know.","index":150,"end_time":977.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":976.67,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Something to do with it as well, but no, last January was, was fairly good compared to this January.","index":151,"end_time":986.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.869,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We have not been this slow since I joined three and a half years ago.","index":152,"end_time":991.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.07,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So it is very, very slow.","index":153,"end_time":994.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":991.63,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Right now.","index":154,"end_time":995.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.51,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We are, we''re just struggling to get through the month.","index":155,"end_time":998.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.36,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But, you know, the leads that do come in, we''re not, we''re not landing them all.","index":156,"end_time":1002.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.4,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So they, they come in, but they, they don''t follow through.","index":157,"end_time":1005.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.6,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"What is some of the biggest reasons for that?","index":158,"end_time":1009.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1007.24,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I really couldn''t tell you.","index":159,"end_time":1011.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1010.2,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, I might be pricing.","index":160,"end_time":1014.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1012.6,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"They take a look.","index":161,"end_time":1015.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1014.56,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Especially if you''re dealing with drivers, you know how they are, they don''t want to pay for anything.","index":162,"end_time":1019.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.56,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"They think that it''s coming out of their money.","index":163,"end_time":1021.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.4,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So, I mean, that could be a lot of where we''re losing them.","index":164,"end_time":1024.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.48,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":1027.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026.43,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I think that to go with what Bailey said is having that follow up, because I think this is the first time since I''ve been on these calls that I''ve heard you say, at least in the last year, that it''s like fallen off a cliff slow.","index":166,"end_time":1042.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.31,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, it really has.","index":167,"end_time":1043.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.75,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And.","index":168,"end_time":1043.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.55,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And the economy, I think, is.","index":169,"end_time":1045.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.87,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Has got to do with that.","index":170,"end_time":1046.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1045.35,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And what''s going on with the stock market probably is affecting that a great deal as well.","index":171,"end_time":1050.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.67,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But, yeah, you know, it''s just we''re not.","index":172,"end_time":1053.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1050.59,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"The business is not coming through form fills, you know, they''re there, but we''re not getting business.","index":173,"end_time":1059.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.31,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And what we need to do, I think more than drivers is we definitely need to target those brokers.","index":174,"end_time":1067.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.41,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s who we want to get.","index":175,"end_time":1068.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1067.29,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":176,"end_time":1070.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1068.97,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And when someone does, you know, most of our marketing spend is on pay per click for Google, and it''s an open marketplace for anyone to search, unfortunately.","index":177,"end_time":1081.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.73,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But I think that the one thing that we can maybe do to try and isolate for.","index":178,"end_time":1088.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.01,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"For marketers in demand to get even better and take it to the next level would be a feedback loop on which leads that came through that were good versus bad.","index":179,"end_time":1098.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1088.57,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And I think that''s what Bailey''s saying, because they have no clue on what leads are good or bad to help us kind of hone in on those keywords that are landing us jobs versus the keywords that aren''t landing us jobs.","index":180,"end_time":1112.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.61,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And so maybe finding a way for us all to work together, especially because it sounds critical now to isolate.","index":181,"end_time":1119.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.73,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Like, even if you had three really good ones so far this month and 30 that were bad or non converters, and a reason why, if we could start tracking that.","index":182,"end_time":1130.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1119.29,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I know that''s what we do in my business is we track leads, the ones we get versus the ones we don''t as far as putting our spend into the ones that converted the keywords that got us the most jobs.","index":183,"end_time":1143.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1130.89,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So some sort of feedback loop would be.","index":184,"end_time":1151.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.11,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, there should be something for that and.","index":185,"end_time":1153.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.63,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But there''s some that, like, we don''t know why they''re not converting.","index":186,"end_time":1157.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1153.71,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We.","index":187,"end_time":1158.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1157.87,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"We don''t know.","index":188,"end_time":1158.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.15,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, they don''t tell you.","index":189,"end_time":1160.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.27,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"They just don''t.","index":190,"end_time":1161.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1160.35,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, they just don''t respond.","index":191,"end_time":1162.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.03,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Respond after we send them pricing.","index":192,"end_time":1165.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.71,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Bailey, you guys still put everything in HubSpot, right?","index":193,"end_time":1172.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.35,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":194,"end_time":1174.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1173.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Any of the.","index":195,"end_time":1174.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1174.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"The contacts that fill out a form are in HubSpot.","index":196,"end_time":1178.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1175.55,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":197,"end_time":1179.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.07,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"All right.","index":198,"end_time":1181.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1180.59,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Do you think it would be beneficial to kind of have all the leads that we saw didn''t convert if we have, for example, maybe their email address or some kind of contact information to follow up and ask them, like, oh, we see, we had a conversation a while back, but could you give us a little bit more information of on why you didn''t go to the next step?","index":199,"end_time":1201.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1181.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":200,"end_time":1202.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1201.77,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Chris, the spreadsheet that you guys work off of for everything, you keep the ones on there that didn''t convert.","index":201,"end_time":1209.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1202.73,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Right.","index":202,"end_time":1209.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.17,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Like, they start out.","index":203,"end_time":1211.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1210.25,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":204,"end_time":1213.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.17,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"We would not keep that on the spreadsheet unless it was assigned a job number, and it wouldn''t be assigned a job number if we didn''t come back from them after the initial contact where we send the rate sheet.","index":205,"end_time":1223.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.69,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":206,"end_time":1224.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.15,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Because I was gonna offer to go through that sheet and then, you know, look at HubSpot and see if I could kind of bridge the gap to start.","index":207,"end_time":1233.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.95,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Because.","index":208,"end_time":1234.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1234.23,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Because I understand HubSpot and CRMs pretty well.","index":209,"end_time":1239.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.31,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"You have a spreadsheet of the people who do work with you, though, right?","index":210,"end_time":1243.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1240.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, yes.","index":211,"end_time":1245.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.15,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean, then there you go backwards there.","index":212,"end_time":1248.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1246.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"There you go.","index":213,"end_time":1250.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1249.37,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"All right.","index":214,"end_time":1251.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1250.81,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Well, I mean, I''d be willing to take on the task to get the ball rolling, to just show them, like, here''s some of the jobs that over the last 60 days that converted.","index":215,"end_time":1264.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1251.85,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean, would that be a.","index":216,"end_time":1266.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.49,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Would that be helpful if I pulled it and tagged it in HubSpot?","index":217,"end_time":1270.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1266.41,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Or just give you the list of the email addresses and names?","index":218,"end_time":1274.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.13,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Because Chris could probably do that.","index":219,"end_time":1275.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1274.21,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I would say let''s maybe just start with a spreadsheet there, because we probably just need to align on, like, how we want to have it all organized in HubSpot.","index":220,"end_time":1286.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1276.83,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Unless, like, you already have it all set up.","index":221,"end_time":1288.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1286.27,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"If you don''t have something set up yet, then I think it''s a bigger conversation of how do we want to have it set up?","index":222,"end_time":1295.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1289.63,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, what dashboards can we create to help track this kind of stuff?","index":223,"end_time":1299.95,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1295.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":224,"end_time":1300.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1300.27,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And, like, how can we maybe integrate it into your sales process?","index":225,"end_time":1305.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1301.31,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like.","index":226,"end_time":1306.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1305.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yes, in a.","index":227,"end_time":1307.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1306.19,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"In a really simple, streamlined way.","index":228,"end_time":1308.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1307.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, I don''t want to make Chris''s job harder.","index":229,"end_time":1311.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1308.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"No, I, I, I, I really felt like for us to take a leap and this is a separate conversation for Don, Chris, and I to have.","index":230,"end_time":1321.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.69,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But at some point, I''d really like to get into more of a CRM customer management system where we''re.","index":231,"end_time":1330.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1321.57,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"If we''re hiring salespeople, they can use the CRM to follow up with all the leads we didn''t get over time.","index":232,"end_time":1340.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.77,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":1340.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1340.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, like, that''s how, as we grow and evolve, we''re gonna need some sort of Customer relationship management tool.","index":234,"end_time":1348.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1340.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, so that''s what companies use at, you know, over a million bucks usually.","index":235,"end_time":1353.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, I''d love to get us there at some point and I, I''ll be the first one to raise my hand and say I''m not active at all in the day to day.","index":236,"end_time":1361.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.02,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So, you know, I want to, you know, see what our options are and, But I think that feedback loop is how we take what''s been a really good marketing relationship and growing our business.","index":237,"end_time":1373.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.54,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I think we can attribute at least 40% of our growth last year to what you guys did.","index":238,"end_time":1379.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.95,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So I want to really take, you know, and, and continue to work that.","index":239,"end_time":1384.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.23,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"How we can get you information without, you know, crushing us but also making us more streamlined and efficient would be fantastic if we can figure out a way to get there.","index":240,"end_time":1396.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.71,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1396.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1396.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I''d like to ask, does anyone.","index":242,"end_time":1399.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.51,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Is there any way of knowing if our Google hits are individuals or companies?","index":243,"end_time":1402.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1399.31,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Could you say that one more time?","index":244,"end_time":1407.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1405.59,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Sure.","index":245,"end_time":1407.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.35,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Is there any way of discerning whether our Google hits.","index":246,"end_time":1412.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1408.23,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"The Google search is individuals or companies.","index":247,"end_time":1417.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1413.99,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Like the people who are clicking on, is it C.H.","index":248,"end_time":1421.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1419.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Robinson or is it Joe Smith?","index":249,"end_time":1423.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1421.52,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Chris would be able to best answer that, but it''s both.","index":250,"end_time":1427.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.4,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I think it''s mainly companies though, right, Chris?","index":251,"end_time":1429.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.28,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean the, the list I look at, it seems like mainly companies, but I''ll let her answer.","index":252,"end_time":1433.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.56,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Oh, your microphone.","index":253,"end_time":1437.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1435.92,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I''m sorry.","index":254,"end_time":1440.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1439.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s mainly companies that convert, you know, that we were able to capture and, and get that to completion.","index":255,"end_time":1447.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.8,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"As far as who clicks, I would not have that information.","index":256,"end_time":1452.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.84,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But who fills out the forms?","index":257,"end_time":1454.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.38,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I do have that information and generally it''s.","index":258,"end_time":1458.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1454.22,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"It''s the email.","index":259,"end_time":1459.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1458.38,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Is it Gmail?","index":260,"end_time":1460.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1459.06,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s not a company.","index":261,"end_time":1461.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1460.14,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"You know, Outlook, whatever.","index":262,"end_time":1463.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.66,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So we, we know that way.","index":263,"end_time":1464.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1463.26,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":264,"end_time":1465.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Okay.","index":265,"end_time":1465.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.54,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s good.","index":266,"end_time":1467.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.7,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So can we start with providing them maybe, Chris, with a list of.","index":267,"end_time":1474.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.78,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Would just the company name be good enough or what''s.","index":268,"end_time":1477.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1475.26,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean, because we don''t want to give access to your sheet, obviously, but if we could copy and paste into a new spreadsheet the ones.","index":269,"end_time":1485.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean.","index":270,"end_time":1485.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1485.46,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, you can, you can definitely copy it.","index":271,"end_time":1487.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.82,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"That''s not a problem.","index":272,"end_time":1488.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.9,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"I want you to have access, you know, editorial access or anything.","index":273,"end_time":1492.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.58,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But a copy of it is fine.","index":274,"end_time":1494.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1492.18,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, whatever information you can give us because we''ll want to try and match what''s in the CRM, so whatever people are filling out.","index":275,"end_time":1503.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1494.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So like if you have their name or their email, the company name, like anything you can give us would be really helpful.","index":276,"end_time":1512.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1503.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"When I used to try to data match and come and show you guys, like, here''s all our hits from last month.","index":277,"end_time":1518.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.09,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I did that a while back.","index":278,"end_time":1520.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.97,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s been a long time, and it was a big task just trying to match everything.","index":279,"end_time":1524.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.17,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But I remember searching in HubSpot on the company name and would usually get a hit.","index":280,"end_time":1533.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.61,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"If not, you know, they''re the person''s name that filled out the form, and I would find them in there.","index":281,"end_time":1540.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And that''s how I could determine whether it came from the website or it came from another lead source or someone that just called Chris, you know, that did business with us before.","index":282,"end_time":1551.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1540.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So.","index":283,"end_time":1553.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.22,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s awesome.","index":284,"end_time":1556.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1555.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you could send us whatever you have, and then I think it would be really helpful if we could have, like, a longer conversation.","index":285,"end_time":1565.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1558.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, if you feel like you''re ready to.","index":286,"end_time":1568.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1566.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"To start tracking this stuff, we''d love to help out and just figure out what your current process is and then how we can maybe plug in there.","index":287,"end_time":1577.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1568.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, Bailey, once we.","index":288,"end_time":1584,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1577.6,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Once we send you the information for, like, the last 90 days of what converted, maybe then we can talk about.","index":289,"end_time":1590.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1584.38,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Maybe we can have a call that shows, like, the benefits of working in a HubSpot because the information''s already coming in.","index":290,"end_time":1599.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.9,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s just a matter of us saying in there, did we get the job or not?","index":291,"end_time":1602.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.26,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And.","index":292,"end_time":1602.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, and then we''ll have all the tools to analyze what''s working, what''s not, and there''ll be a feedback loop that you guys can see live.","index":293,"end_time":1609.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.7,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So maybe once we get you that information, you can show us what it would look like in HubSpot.","index":294,"end_time":1614.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1609.5,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And then maybe that might be a way to see if we have the resources or if it makes sense for us to do.","index":295,"end_time":1622.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.92,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, we can work from there and show you if budget''s a concern, we can maybe try a way to fit it in.","index":296,"end_time":1631.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1623,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You do have a couple extra points every month to do stuff.","index":297,"end_time":1635.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1631.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we can.","index":298,"end_time":1636.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1635.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":299,"end_time":1637.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1637.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"We''ll see what we can do.","index":300,"end_time":1638.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1637.42,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":301,"end_time":1639.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1638.54,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And the other thing I''d like to see researched is, is business determined by it?","index":302,"end_time":1644.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1639.02,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"When we say business is bad right now, is that more the economy, Is truck traffic down, or is that more of competition?","index":303,"end_time":1652.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1644.94,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"I mean, if things are slow right now because there''s just not for economic reasons.","index":304,"end_time":1660.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1653.02,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"There''s just not as much transit.","index":305,"end_time":1661.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.42,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"There has to be some metric that we could measure as far as how much transportation is going on around the country.","index":306,"end_time":1669.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1661.94,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":307,"end_time":1670.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.07,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Bailey, quickly, to Don''s point, if you could tell us how many website visitors we had in maybe in January versus December.","index":308,"end_time":1682.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1670.79,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I know we''re only 22 days in.","index":309,"end_time":1684.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1682.15,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But I''m sure you could probably find that pretty quickly.","index":310,"end_time":1687.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.19,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, let me look at that.","index":311,"end_time":1689.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1688.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Would be, like, maybe the quickest way to see, like, if we''re getting.","index":312,"end_time":1693.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.78,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"If the traffic and the.","index":313,"end_time":1695.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1693.62,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Is there, but it''s not good traffic is then kind of what we were diving into.","index":314,"end_time":1700.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1696.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Right?","index":315,"end_time":1701.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1701.02,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean, Andy, is our.","index":316,"end_time":1702.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1701.34,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Our prices too high or is it just the economy right now?","index":317,"end_time":1705.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1702.7,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"Is business just too slow because of that?","index":318,"end_time":1707.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.66,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"That''s why it would be great to know for the jobs that we don''t get, if it''s price related or if it''s timing related.","index":319,"end_time":1716.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1709.1,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Like, and we could mark all that if we were in a CRM, we could have stats and data to back all this up.","index":320,"end_time":1722.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.46,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But it''s not something that we''ve done yet to this point in our company.","index":321,"end_time":1726.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.64,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Like, we don''t have any analytics or any data behind what we do.","index":322,"end_time":1732.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1727.12,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Is that hard to do?","index":323,"end_time":1734.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1732.56,"speaker_name":"Don Hill"},{"text":"I mean, it''s a relative word.","index":324,"end_time":1737.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.2,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Once you use a CRM, I think it makes everybody''s life way easier because the data you get from it, the communication you get with your customers improves because no matter what.","index":325,"end_time":1748.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.72,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So, like, one of the best things about using a CRM for me isn''t for someone in Chris''s seat.","index":326,"end_time":1753.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.27,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s for people that we would hire to do sales functions to follow up on this.","index":327,"end_time":1759.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1753.59,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"All this money we''re spending to capture new customers is Chris is in operation.","index":328,"end_time":1765.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.03,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"She''s gonna respond to them as the opportunities come in.","index":329,"end_time":1769.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1765.67,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But we don''t have anybody that has the time or resources to like, go back and say, hey, thanks for the job.","index":330,"end_time":1774.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1769.35,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"What else do you have this month?","index":331,"end_time":1776.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1775.54,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Or what can we do for you in other markets?","index":332,"end_time":1779.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1776.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And so having all that stuff in a CRM gives you the ability to have maybe hire a salesperson at some point that could drive more business because we are spending a lot of money on leads and the ones that don''t hit to figure out why they didn''t hit.","index":333,"end_time":1796.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1779.78,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Like, if they just go quiet, you have a salesperson that''s calling on that lead to try and build a relationship.","index":334,"end_time":1802.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1796.82,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I mean, part of the reason that we fixed freight, took off is because I flew around the country and met with C.H.","index":335,"end_time":1809.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1803.83,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"robinson and Alan Lund and all these people and got face to face and built a relationship.","index":336,"end_time":1815.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.59,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So they didn''t just give us one job a month anymore.","index":337,"end_time":1817.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.51,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"They gave us, you know, five or ten jobs a month in all different markets.","index":338,"end_time":1821.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.91,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And so we''re not doing anything wrong.","index":339,"end_time":1824.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1822.55,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s just this is part of how do we grow and you think about growth.","index":340,"end_time":1828.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1824.79,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The Most in a time like this when the business dies, you know.","index":341,"end_time":1833.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1828.79,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So I think this is, you know, it just, it breeds good conversation for us to look inside at what else we can be doing, especially when we''re slow.","index":342,"end_time":1842,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1833.28,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So I''ll show just really quick.","index":343,"end_time":1846.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1844,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So this is comparing so the last 28 days and I, and I can change those.","index":344,"end_time":1852.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1846.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So yeah, that''s good.","index":345,"end_time":1853.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1852.4,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":346,"end_time":1854.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1853.68,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"But yeah, traffic''s down.","index":347,"end_time":1855.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1854.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":348,"end_time":1857.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1856.4,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The biggest decrease that is coming from like direct traffic.","index":349,"end_time":1861.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1857.28,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s people who could just go right to your website.","index":350,"end_time":1863.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1861.64,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like a small decrease in, in the pay per click.","index":351,"end_time":1868.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1863.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But that''s honestly like not bad at all.","index":352,"end_time":1870.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1868.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":353,"end_time":1872.56,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1870.76,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then organic searches up a tiny bit.","index":354,"end_time":1875.159,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1872.56,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So people that commonly.","index":355,"end_time":1877,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1875.64,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"That top one.","index":356,"end_time":1877.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1877,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"That is people that commonly just type in.","index":357,"end_time":1881.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1878.44,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"We fix freight.","index":358,"end_time":1881.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1881.12,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"They know us from before, they''ve heard of us.","index":359,"end_time":1884.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1881.92,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So that number is down quite a bit.","index":360,"end_time":1887.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1885.43,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"37%.","index":361,"end_time":1889.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1888.71,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":362,"end_time":1890.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1890.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Which kind of would.","index":363,"end_time":1891.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.87,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Would go to what Chris was saying about.","index":364,"end_time":1894.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.07,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s just slow.","index":365,"end_time":1894.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.03,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The economy is slow right now.","index":366,"end_time":1896.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.87,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So there is certainly some of that we''re seeing here.","index":367,"end_time":1902.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.59,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":368,"end_time":1903.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1902.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"About a 20 overall decrease in site traffic, which normally most months we see steady increases.","index":369,"end_time":1911.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.15,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":370,"end_time":1912.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1911.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All of our stuff.","index":371,"end_time":1913.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1912.21,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And that''s probably too why our cost per click is up because it''s more competitive right now because everybody''s trying to squeeze the juice to get business and, and that''s how it works, you know, so it all makes sense.","index":372,"end_time":1927.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1913.41,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It all makes sense.","index":373,"end_time":1930.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1929.33,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Chris, do you.","index":374,"end_time":1931.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1930.69,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Will you be able to send her that information or do you need me to help with that?","index":375,"end_time":1935.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1931.89,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I can probably send it to her.","index":376,"end_time":1938.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1937.02,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Not exactly sure how, but I''ll figure it out.","index":377,"end_time":1941.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1938.94,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay.","index":378,"end_time":1941.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1941.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah, just the spreadsheet, as far as how many months of it do you.","index":379,"end_time":1948.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1941.7,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Would you want to see like three?","index":380,"end_time":1951.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1948.54,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"All right, we can do that.","index":381,"end_time":1953.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1952.54,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And no financials are needed.","index":382,"end_time":1955.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1953.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Right.","index":383,"end_time":1956.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"We just need the name.","index":384,"end_time":1957.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1956.06,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Business email.","index":385,"end_time":1958.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1957.34,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yes.","index":386,"end_time":1959.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1958.7,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t need job amounts or anything.","index":387,"end_time":1960.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1959.14,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Just name business email.","index":388,"end_time":1962.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.86,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I think the emails, that''s going to be a task to go back.","index":389,"end_time":1966.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1963.66,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Okay.","index":390,"end_time":1969.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.94,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"All right.","index":391,"end_time":1970.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":392,"end_time":1970.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1970.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just whatever is easy.","index":393,"end_time":1972.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1970.94,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, yeah, don''t.","index":394,"end_time":1973.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1972.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Don''t spend too much time on this.","index":395,"end_time":1975.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1973.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":396,"end_time":1977.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1976.62,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":397,"end_time":1978.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1977.74,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"I think HubSpot, she can research it based on the company name, the person''s name.","index":398,"end_time":1981.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1978.1,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So the email is not really necessary.","index":399,"end_time":1983.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981.98,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"It''s just having at least one thing we can search by will be great.","index":400,"end_time":1988.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.14,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"The company name that we''d have.","index":401,"end_time":1990.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1988.86,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And then I think it''s difficult as well because you''ve got the driver will call in.","index":402,"end_time":1997.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1991.26,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"But then we switch over to dealing with the company.","index":403,"end_time":1999.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1997.2,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"So you don''t know like you''re not making the connection there.","index":404,"end_time":2003.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2000.12,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":405,"end_time":2004.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2003.64,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Got it.","index":406,"end_time":2007,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2006.36,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":407,"end_time":2009.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2008.84,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Well, at least this is a good start to see, you know, because they can reverse engineer it and say, okay, up till like, maybe a week ago, because there is a lag.","index":408,"end_time":2020.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2010.04,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So, like, up to a week ago, here''s the ones we got.","index":409,"end_time":2024.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2021.58,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"So they''ll say, we got these 80 jobs.","index":410,"end_time":2028.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2024.78,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Here''s the other 150 we didn''t get.","index":411,"end_time":2031.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2028.18,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"And then so we''ll have something to go off of.","index":412,"end_time":2034.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2031.26,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"If you also have, like, the date that you close the deal or like the month that it happened, that would be helpful, just so we can make sure we look at the right time period.","index":413,"end_time":2045.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2034.86,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Thing is, on the spreadsheet, everything is month.","index":414,"end_time":2050.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2046.46,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Like, you have a new spreadsheet every month.","index":415,"end_time":2052.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2050.79,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"And then our job numbers, our tracking numbers that we use are the day.","index":416,"end_time":2056.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2052.59,"speaker_name":"Christine Saur"},{"text":"Oh, perfect.","index":417,"end_time":2058.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2057.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Amazing.","index":418,"end_time":2060.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2059.67,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''ll be great.","index":419,"end_time":2061.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2060.39,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":420,"end_time":2065.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2065.35,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, great.","index":421,"end_time":2066.63,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2065.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"On time.","index":422,"end_time":2067.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2066.87,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":423,"end_time":2067.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2067.51,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Super, super excited to dive in.","index":424,"end_time":2069.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2067.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":2071.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2070.55,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Thank you very much, guys.","index":426,"end_time":2072.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2071.07,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Chris, thanks for seeing all you guys.","index":427,"end_time":2074.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2072.95,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":428,"end_time":2076.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2076.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":429,"end_time":2077.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2076.71,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":430,"end_time":2077.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2077.57,"speaker_name":"Andrew Hill"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85897587831?pwd=hDlQElXqYVOp2bzGDuaodhOZVUT4GB.1&jst=2","participants":["nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,donhill@dedicatedtg.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,chris@wefixfreight.com,andrew@cashtoclose.net","donhill@dedicatedtg.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","chris@wefixfreight.com","andrew@cashtoclose.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFH3Y02SXXXY5TFYYVHMYW61","organizer_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"negative","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Christine reported business is the slowest in 3.5 years, causing struggle to meet monthly goals.","Andrew proposed creating a CRM feedback loop to isolate high-converting vs non-converting leads.","Team agreed to provide 90-day data on closed deals to help optimize keyword spending.","Baylee confirmed website traffic dropped 20%, especially in returning direct visits, indicating economic slowdown.","Christine confirmed most converting leads are companies, but many form fills come from individual emails."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We have not been this slow since I joined three and a half years ago.","speaker":"Christine Saur"},{"quote":"Sounds critical now to isolate... the ones that converted vs the ones that were non converters.","speaker":"Andrew Hill"},{"quote":"Traffic''s down... biggest decrease that is coming from like direct traffic.","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"topics":["delivery","lead_quality","CRM","traffic","economy"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-24T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Performance and Lead Generation**\n\nMarketing efforts have maintained strong lead engagement despite a challenging business environment.\n\n- **Google Ads delivered 42 conversions with a continued 13% lead volume growth**, driven by both the general brand campaign and the targeted Costco campaign, showing that brand awareness remains strong and top-of-mind for emergency freight services (09:32)  \n    - Geo-fencing targeting for the Costco campaign was reinstated after noticing leads from those locations, confirming effective regional focus  \n    - **Cost per conversion remained stable**, despite increased competition bidding on the brand name, which raised cost per click slightly  \n    - Nina emphasized the importance of quality leads over quantity to ensure marketing spend drives real business  \n    - Top converting keywords include **cross docking services, ballot restacking, temporary warehousing, and lumber services near me**, aligning closely with core service offerings  \n    - AdRoll campaigns showed stable performance with **26,000+ impressions, 23 clicks, and 1 conversion**, supporting brand awareness outside of search ads  \n\n- **The “Emergency Card” resource gained traction with 23 downloads**, including repeat interest signaling growing client engagement with helpful content (10:56)  \n    - Data analytics recommendations include targeting **3 to 5 major distribution hubs and large 3PL centers for geo-fencing** and optimizing existing landing pages for SEO to reduce paid lead costs  \n    - Nina proposed addressing common client questions and misconceptions during sales calls through targeted content to improve lead comfort and conversion  \n\n## **Sales and Lead Quality Challenges**\n\nCurrent lead volume contrasts with poor business conversion, highlighting gaps between marketing and sales outcomes.\n\n- **Christine reported a significant drop in business activity, calling January the slowest in over three years despite healthy lead flow**, indicating that leads are not translating into sales (14:10)  \n    - She attributed lower conversion partly to economic conditions and customer price sensitivity, especially among drivers reluctant to pay out of pocket  \n    - Chris stressed the need to target brokers more aggressively, as they represent higher-value customers than drivers  \n    - Calls to action conversion rates remain unclear due to lack of consistent follow-up and lead status tracking  \n\n- **Andrew proposed establishing a feedback loop between sales and marketing to track which leads convert and which don’t, including reasons for lost sales**, to refine keyword targeting and improve lead quality (18:30)  \n    - He offered to analyze existing sales spreadsheets and HubSpot CRM data to bridge gaps and identify lead outcomes over the past 60-90 days  \n    - Baylee agreed to align on CRM data organization and dashboard creation to streamline lead tracking without complicating sales workflows  \n    - The group recognized that a CRM-driven process is crucial to improve sales follow-up, lead nurturing, and marketing ROI, especially to support future sales hires  \n\n## **CRM Integration and Process Improvements**\n\nAdopting CRM tools and improving data tracking are critical steps to enhance sales efficiency and growth potential.\n\n- **Andrew emphasized the strategic value of a CRM system to manage leads, automate follow-ups, and provide actionable sales insights**, highlighting its role in scaling sales efforts and improving customer relationships (21:30)  \n    - He pointed out that CRM adoption would help future salespeople systematically follow up on unconverted leads, turning marketing spend into more closed deals  \n    - Baylee and Andrew agreed on starting with simple spreadsheet data sharing and moving toward more integrated HubSpot dashboards and workflows after further discussion  \n    - The team plans to share lead data including company names, contact info, and deal close dates for the last 90 days to enable initial analysis and CRM alignment  \n\n- **Chris confirmed she can provide monthly sales spreadsheets with job numbers and business names but noted challenges linking individual drivers to companies within current tracking** (32:00)  \n    - The group agreed not to require sensitive financial data, focusing instead on identifiers useful for matching marketing leads to sales outcomes  \n    - This data will enable reverse engineering of conversions and losses to better understand lead quality and ROI  \n\n## **Market and Economic Context**\n\nExternal economic factors and market conditions are influencing demand and website traffic trends.\n\n- **Baylee reported a 20% overall drop in website traffic in January compared to December, with a notable 37% decrease in direct traffic from brand searches** (30:50)  \n    - The reduction in direct traffic suggests fewer repeat or returning visitors aware of the brand, supporting Chris’s assessment of a slow market  \n    - Paid search traffic remained relatively stable despite increased cost per click due to competitive bidding  \n    - Andrew and Don discussed the importance of monitoring industry-wide transportation volumes and economic indicators to contextualize business performance  \n    - Understanding whether slowdowns are due to lower freight demand or increased competition will help guide marketing and sales strategies  \n\n- **Don highlighted the importance of maintaining top Google search rankings for “freight repair,” considering it a key competitive advantage for capturing urgent customer needs** (15:10)  \n    - This visibility supports brand positioning as the go-to emergency service provider despite market headwinds  \n\n## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**\n\nThe team agreed to focus on improving lead quality tracking, enhancing CRM integration, and refining marketing content to boost conversion.\n\n- **Immediate priority is to provide and analyze the last 90 days of sales data to match marketing leads with actual jobs won or lost**, forming the basis for a feedback loop to optimize campaigns (24:00)  \n    - Baylee will work with Andrew and Chris to define CRM dashboard requirements and lead tracking processes without overcomplicating existing workflows  \n    - The team plans a follow-up discussion to review HubSpot capabilities and determine resource allocation for CRM adoption and lead management improvements  \n\n- **Content strategy will evolve to address common client questions and misconceptions, aiming to reduce friction in the sales process and improve customer trust** (09:45)  \n    - Optimizing existing landing pages for SEO will balance paid efforts with organic growth, lowering lead acquisition costs over time  \n\n- **Longer-term vision includes hiring dedicated sales personnel supported by CRM tools to follow up on leads and build stronger customer relationships, increasing conversion rates and revenue growth** (21:30)  \n    - This approach reflects a shift from relying solely on marketing to proactive sales outreach as a growth lever during slow economic periods  \n\n- **Business leaders will continue monitoring external economic and transportation activity metrics to better understand demand fluctuations and adjust strategies accordingly** (27:00)","outline":null,"keywords":["Google Ads","Lead Conversion","CRM Integration","HubSpot","Economic Slowdown","Geofencing"],"overview":"- **Strong Google Ads Performance:** Achieved 42 conversions with 13% lead growth, driven by brand and Costco campaigns.\n\n- **Sales Activity Decline:** January was the slowest month in over three years, despite healthy lead flow, highlighting conversion issues.\n\n- **CRM System Importance:** Proposed CRM adoption for lead management and tracking will improve sales follow-ups and marketing ROI.\n\n- **Website Traffic Concerns:** January saw a 20% drop in traffic, with urgent need to maintain Google search rankings for key terms.\n\n- **Content Strategy Evolution:** Focus on common client questions to reduce sales friction and enhance trust, optimizing landing pages for SEO.\n\n- **Long-term Vision:** Consider hiring dedicated sales staff alongside CRM tools to boost lead conversion and overall revenue growth.","action_items":"\n**Andrew Hill**\nVolunteer to review internal spreadsheet of converted and non-converted leads and assist in matching data with HubSpot CRM records (20:10)\nProvide marketers with a spreadsheet of last 90 days’ closed jobs detailing company names and closing dates for CRM integration (26:15)\n\n**Christine Saur**\nSend spreadsheet data of last three months of closed jobs including company names and closure dates to marketing team (32:00)\nCoordinate internally to gather and deliver lead contact information for marketers to analyze (31:50)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAnalyze shared data and demonstrate potential HubSpot CRM dashboards and tracking functionalities to the team (26:50)\nProvide comparison report of website traffic between December and January to assess business volume trends (28:10)\n\n**Unassigned**\nPlan a follow-up meeting to discuss refining goals and strategies for the year based on marketing and sales data alignment (12:25)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"00e2d661-f74d-454c-8310-2033631b4af0","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
