INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: WFF // New North - Biweekly meeting (NEW)',
  '## **Marketing Performance and Lead Generation**

Marketing efforts have maintained strong lead engagement despite a challenging business environment.

- **Google Ads delivered 42 conversions with a continued 13% lead volume growth**, driven by both the general brand campaign and the targeted Costco campaign, showing that brand awareness remains strong and top-of-mind for emergency freight services (09:32)  
    - Geo-fencing targeting for the Costco campaign was reinstated after noticing leads from those locations, confirming effective regional focus  
    - **Cost per conversion remained stable**, despite increased competition bidding on the brand name, which raised cost per click slightly  
    - Nina emphasized the importance of quality leads over quantity to ensure marketing spend drives real business  
    - Top converting keywords include **cross docking services, ballot restacking, temporary warehousing, and lumber services near me**, aligning closely with core service offerings  
    - AdRoll campaigns showed stable performance with **26,000+ impressions, 23 clicks, and 1 conversion**, supporting brand awareness outside of search ads  

- **The “Emergency Card” resource gained traction with 23 downloads**, including repeat interest signaling growing client engagement with helpful content (10:56)  
    - Data analytics recommendations include targeting **3 to 5 major distribution hubs and large 3PL centers for geo-fencing** and optimizing existing landing pages for SEO to reduce paid lead costs  
    - Nina proposed addressing common client questions and misconceptions during sales calls through targeted content to improve lead comfort and conversion  

## **Sales and Lead Quality Challenges**

Current lead volume contrasts with poor business conversion, highlighting gaps between marketing and sales outcomes.

- **Christine reported a significant drop in business activity, calling January the slowest in over three years despite healthy lead flow**, indicating that leads are not translating into sales (14:10)  
    - She attributed lower conversion partly to economic conditions and customer price sensitivity, especially among drivers reluctant to pay out of pocket  
    - Chris stressed the need to target brokers more aggressively, as they represent higher-value customers than drivers  
    - Calls to action conversion rates remain unclear due to lack of consistent follow-up and lead status tracking  

- **Andrew proposed establishing a feedback loop between sales and marketing to track which leads convert and which don’t, including reasons for lost sales**, to refine keyword targeting and improve lead quality (18:30)  
    - He offered to analyze existing sales spreadsheets and HubSpot CRM data to bridge gaps and identify lead outcomes over the past 60-90 days  
    - Baylee agreed to align on CRM data organization and dashboard creation to streamline lead tracking without complicating sales workflows  
    - The group recognized that a CRM-driven process is crucial to improve sales follow-up, lead nurturing, and marketing ROI, especially to support future sales hires  

## **CRM Integration and Process Improvements**

Adopting CRM tools and improving data tracking are critical steps to enhance sales efficiency and growth potential.

- **Andrew emphasized the strategic value of a CRM system to manage leads, automate follow-ups, and provide actionable sales insights**, highlighting its role in scaling sales efforts and improving customer relationships (21:30)  
    - He pointed out that CRM adoption would help future salespeople systematically follow up on unconverted leads, turning marketing spend into more closed deals  
    - Baylee and Andrew agreed on starting with simple spreadsheet data sharing and moving toward more integrated HubSpot dashboards and workflows after further discussion  
    - The team plans to share lead data including company names, contact info, and deal close dates for the last 90 days to enable initial analysis and CRM alignment  

- **Chris confirmed she can provide monthly sales spreadsheets with job numbers and business names but noted challenges linking individual drivers to companies within current tracking** (32:00)  
    - The group agreed not to require sensitive financial data, focusing instead on identifiers useful for matching marketing leads to sales outcomes  
    - This data will enable reverse engineering of conversions and losses to better understand lead quality and ROI  

## **Market and Economic Context**

External economic factors and market conditions are influencing demand and website traffic trends.

- **Baylee reported a 20% overall drop in website traffic in January compared to December, with a notable 37% decrease in direct traffic from brand searches** (30:50)  
    - The reduction in direct traffic suggests fewer repeat or returning visitors aware of the brand, supporting Chris’s assessment of a slow market  
    - Paid search traffic remained relatively stable despite increased cost per click due to competitive bidding  
    - Andrew and Don discussed the importance of monitoring industry-wide transportation volumes and economic indicators to contextualize business performance  
    - Understanding whether slowdowns are due to lower freight demand or increased competition will help guide marketing and sales strategies  

- **Don highlighted the importance of maintaining top Google search rankings for “freight repair,” considering it a key competitive advantage for capturing urgent customer needs** (15:10)  
    - This visibility supports brand positioning as the go-to emergency service provider despite market headwinds  

## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**

The team agreed to focus on improving lead quality tracking, enhancing CRM integration, and refining marketing content to boost conversion.

- **Immediate priority is to provide and analyze the last 90 days of sales data to match marketing leads with actual jobs won or lost**, forming the basis for a feedback loop to optimize campaigns (24:00)  
    - Baylee will work with Andrew and Chris to define CRM dashboard requirements and lead tracking processes without overcomplicating existing workflows  
    - The team plans a follow-up discussion to review HubSpot capabilities and determine resource allocation for CRM adoption and lead management improvements  

- **Content strategy will evolve to address common client questions and misconceptions, aiming to reduce friction in the sales process and improve customer trust** (09:45)  
    - Optimizing existing landing pages for SEO will balance paid efforts with organic growth, lowering lead acquisition costs over time  

- **Longer-term vision includes hiring dedicated sales personnel supported by CRM tools to follow up on leads and build stronger customer relationships, increasing conversion rates and revenue growth** (21:30)  
    - This approach reflects a shift from relying solely on marketing to proactive sales outreach as a growth lever during slow economic periods  

- **Business leaders will continue monitoring external economic and transportation activity metrics to better understand demand fluctuations and adjust strategies accordingly** (27:00)',
  '2026-01-22 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Volunteer to review internal spreadsheet of converted and non-converted leads and assist in matching data with HubSpot CRM records (20:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide marketers with a spreadsheet of last 90 days’ closed jobs detailing company names and closing dates for CRM integration (26:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Send spreadsheet data of last three months of closed jobs including company names and closure dates to marketing team (32:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internally to gather and deliver lead contact information for marketers to analyze (31:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Analyze shared data and demonstrate potential HubSpot CRM dashboards and tracking functionalities to the team (26:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide comparison report of website traffic between December and January to assess business volume trends (28:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Plan a follow-up meeting to discuss refining goals and strategies for the year based on marketing and sales data alignment (12:25)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: GSS Weekly Meeting (2026-01-21 16:58:36+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6061d0c2-de11-40b9-8824-1ccd80a970d6',
    '2026-01-21 16:58:36+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFGQWTK9WJ3WTY0RHE5F98VJ',
    'GSS Weekly Meeting',
    NULL,
    1817,
    NULL,
    '{"id":"01KFGQWTK9WJ3WTY0RHE5F98VJ","title":"GSS Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Distribution**\n\nThe team finalized an **ebook with a new clickable email CTA linking to the global shared services URL** to improve post-download engagement (01:52).  \n- The ebook’s promotion will roll out in phases across social media, newsletters, and possibly paid ads to maximize reach.  \n- Sending the ebook via the **January newsletter** aims to leverage the existing HubSpot list for early traction and lead tracking.  \n- The team plans to monitor who downloads the ebook to identify engaged prospects for targeted follow-up.  \n- Additional distribution methods like website pop-ups are being considered to expand visibility beyond the current channels.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaign was **paused due to excessive outreach to the same companies**, prompting a list enrichment focused on CFO and CEO titles to restart efforts (06:52).  \n- The enriched contact list will be reviewed and adjusted to resume LinkedIn and email outreach, aiming to regain momentum quickly.  \n- The team recognizes the current campaign’s low engagement, with **no meaningful conversations generated so far**, signaling a need to revise messaging and targeting strategies.  \n- New campaign ideas are in development to improve appeal, including potentially bundling CFO and accounting outreach for a stronger value proposition.  \n- Will offered to review the new list and provide feedback today to expedite reactivation and testing of fresh approaches.\n\n## **2026 Sales and Revenue Goals**\n\nThe **2026 sales forecast targets $2.41 million in new revenue**, split primarily between marketing-driven sales and CFO services (08:25).  \n- Marketing efforts aim for **$446,250 in new sales**, while CFO services target **$624,000**, totaling just over $1 million from these two streams.  \n- Last year’s marketing-related sales were **$247,500 (17% of goal)**, reflecting significant growth expectations for the coming year.  \n- The CFO services bucket is new for 2026, with a goal to close **4 to 6 new CFO service clients**, requiring about **14 qualified CFO leads annually** or roughly **4 leads per month** to sustain this pipeline.  \n- The sales close ratio averages **37%**, implying the need for approximately **$1.2 million in marketing leads** to meet the marketing sales target.  \n- Lead sizing and pricing vary by restaurant type, with accounting services ranging from **$350 per unit for simple chains** up to **$1,100 per unit for full-service restaurants**, guiding lead volume and revenue expectations.  \n- Large accounts, like a **100-unit Taco Bell deal worth about $450 per unit**, could nearly cover half the marketing goal with one win, showing the strategic value of targeting bigger groups alongside smaller ones.\n\n## **Sales Pipeline and Lead Management**\n\nSales tracking uses a **HubSpot system with tagged buckets for marketing, referrals, direct business, upsell, and CFO services**, enabling detailed pipeline visibility (13:46).  \n- Historical data shows a shift from smaller deals closed more often to fewer but larger deals, complicating close ratios and forecasting.  \n- Close rate variability exists by lead source: marketing leads close at about **18%**, direct business at **5%**, referrals and upsell near **100%**, averaging to an overall **37% close rate**.  \n- The team plans to refine lead volume targets based on average deal size and close ratios to hit revenue goals more precisely.  \n- Larger deals present longer sales cycles but greater revenue impact, whereas smaller deals may close faster, influencing marketing messaging and resource allocation.  \n- Will and Nick will collaborate to further analyze lead-to-win metrics and optimize pipeline management for better forecasting accuracy.\n\n## **Challenges and Strategic Adjustments in CFO Services Marketing**\n\nDespite efforts, the **ABM campaign has failed to spark interest in CFO services**, even with offers like 30-day free trials during holidays (26:00).  \n- The team suspects CFO service complexity and perceived risk reduce the attractiveness of current offers; the service might require a different value approach.  \n- Feedback from ongoing client discussions shows customers opting for fractional CFOs despite trial offers, highlighting market hesitation.  \n- Tristan and others suggest testing more compelling incentives or revising messaging to create an irresistible offer that overcomes buyer inertia.  \n- Early-year timing provides a window to test new campaign ideas and pivot quickly to meet the CFO services lead goal.  \n- The team agreed to schedule follow-up meetings this week to review and refine campaign tactics and accelerate progress.","outline":null,"keywords":["ebook distribution","ABM campaign","sales forecast 2026","CFO services leads","marketing leads targets","HubSpot tracking"],"overview":"- **Ebook Launch:** A new ebook with clickable email CTA launches via January newsletter for early traction and tracking.  \n- **ABM Campaign Pause:** Campaign paused due to outreach issues; enriching CFO and CEO contact list to resume efforts.  \n- **2026 Revenue Goals:** Targeting $2.41 million in new revenue, mostly from marketing sales and new CFO services clients.  \n- **Sales Pipeline Insights:** HubSpot tracks multiple lead sources; average close rate is 37% with variances by lead type.  \n- **CFO Services Challenge:** Current ABM strategy hasn''t engaged CFO services; need revised messaging or stronger incentives for appeal.  \n- **Testing New Strategies:** Upcoming meetings scheduled to refine campaign tactics and boost progress toward CFO leads.","action_items":"\n**Unknown (likely marketing/management team)**\nUpdate the ebook''s last page CTA to include a clickable email and correct global shared services URL (01:52)\nProvide social media posts for ebook promotion on LinkedIn personal pages and coordinate newsletter inclusion before the end of January (05:06)\nSend enriched CFO and CEO contact list for ABM campaign review and reactivation (06:52)\nReview and comment on the new contact list for ABM outreach including LinkedIn and email (07:31)\nPrepare and share new ABM campaign ideas for discussion in follow-up meeting this week (28:42)\n\n**Will (likely sales lead)**\nShare sales forecast spreadsheet and explain sales bucket tracking and close ratio methodology for 2026 goals (08:25)\nPerform calculations on required lead volume based on close ratios and quota targets (16:46)\nAssist in determining average client revenue sizes to estimate volume of leads needed to meet marketing sales targets (23:45)\nCollaborate on refining CFO services lead definitions and target setting (23:45)\n\n**Nick (likely marketing/operations)**\nOrganize HubSpot and sales pipeline data for easy tracking of deals classified by marketing and CFO services buckets, and analyze historic sales data (13:46)\nTrack win/loss ratio and calculate close percentages differentiated by lead source (15:19)\n"},"duration":30.280000686645508,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Looks like Will''s trying to join.","index":0,"end_time":114.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":1,"end_time":115.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It.","index":2,"end_time":128.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There he is.","index":3,"end_time":165.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I. Hello?","index":4,"end_time":179.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, Will.","index":5,"end_time":180.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":179.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi.","index":6,"end_time":181.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":7,"end_time":184.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":181.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Great.","index":8,"end_time":184.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":184.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know.","index":9,"end_time":188.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How was your break?","index":10,"end_time":188.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Feel like I''ve been gone for so long.","index":11,"end_time":191.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It was really good.","index":12,"end_time":193.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We got to drive up the Pacific coast highway, got to see some really beautiful beaches, and it''s just a slow time of year right now, so it was nice.","index":13,"end_time":203.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not.","index":14,"end_time":204.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not too much traffic.","index":15,"end_time":205.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It was beautiful.","index":16,"end_time":206.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Good.","index":17,"end_time":208.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":208.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No fires, I guess.","index":18,"end_time":210.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, no fires.","index":19,"end_time":212.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":211.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Luckily, those are always dangerous.","index":20,"end_time":214.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, Nick, can you hear me okay?","index":21,"end_time":219.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":22,"end_time":220.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":23,"end_time":220.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":24,"end_time":221.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":220.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, it was saying zoom is not loading, responding.","index":25,"end_time":224.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":221.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it was taking me forever to get in, but looks like I''m good now.","index":26,"end_time":227.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":224.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Cool.","index":27,"end_time":228.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":227.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, maybe there was an update or something, but nice sound great.","index":28,"end_time":233.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Love your background too.","index":29,"end_time":234.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s fun.","index":30,"end_time":235.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":31,"end_time":237.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All righty.","index":32,"end_time":240.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.71,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But let''s go over our updates.","index":33,"end_time":246.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But this is the agenda for today.","index":34,"end_time":250.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''re going to go over some content updates, the ABM campaign, and as we talked about, we''re going to talk about goals for 2026 today.","index":35,"end_time":263.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":250.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s after everything else.","index":36,"end_time":268.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for content updates, I sent you guys the ebook that we worked on.","index":37,"end_time":275.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We are working on changing the last page, which was the CTA that I added just to have some sort of communication after it.","index":38,"end_time":286.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So as you said, we''re adding like an email, a clickable email that people can just like link to you and the correct global shared services URL at the end of it.","index":39,"end_time":305.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The idea with this ebook is that when we distribute it, we give you guys social media posts so that you can put on your personal LinkedIn.","index":40,"end_time":316.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":306.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know we still don''t have a podcast _Recording, but we can put it in the newsletter because January is about to end.","index":41,"end_time":324.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we can send it out to the list that we have in HubSpot and it will be good to know like, who''s interested in our content, who''s downloading it, and maybe a good idea to follow up with everyone that downloads it.","index":42,"end_time":341.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":324.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we can also see like other ways to distribute it, like maybe doing some ads around it, maybe adding a pop up on our website, stuff like that.","index":43,"end_time":355.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":343.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So.","index":44,"end_time":356.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But it will be like different phases of promoting this ebook throughout the quarter.","index":45,"end_time":362.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we also published the last published blog post.","index":46,"end_time":366.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You already reviewed those.","index":47,"end_time":368.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They are on the website.","index":48,"end_time":369.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":368.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How restaurant operations can regain control of cash flow and the true cost of CFO turnover.","index":49,"end_time":376.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I. I wanted to ask you, can we do the newsletter on this ebook?","index":50,"end_time":384.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sure.","index":51,"end_time":385.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":52,"end_time":387.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":386.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":53,"end_time":388.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":54,"end_time":389.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Meanwhile, we''re just waiting on the next podcast _Recording, Right?","index":55,"end_time":394.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for abm, I mentioned that the campaigns were paused because there was some.","index":56,"end_time":400.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":396.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The tools that we''re using were saying that we were doing too much outreach to the same company.","index":57,"end_time":411.979,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what we did is enrich the list that we already have with the same title, CFO, CEOs.","index":58,"end_time":418.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I will send this over for your review so that we can keep the campaigns going because right now, at least the one on LinkedIn is deactivated.","index":59,"end_time":428.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I will send this over and.","index":60,"end_time":433.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s a big thing we definitely want to talk about today.","index":61,"end_time":436.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We got a lot of ideas for some new things we can run as well as this new list is a quick way we can get some traction again.","index":62,"end_time":444.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But yeah, definitely just want to talk through some of your goals for this year and see where we can rework things.","index":63,"end_time":451.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now, just to be clear, on the ABM campaign, it goes beyond LinkedIn, right?","index":64,"end_time":456.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Will we be doing an email campaign as well on top of that?","index":65,"end_time":460.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":456.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":462.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":461.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so then what I''ll do is I''ll take a look at that list today and I''ll make some comments and adjust it around and.","index":67,"end_time":471.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":462.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And yeah, I''ll just review it and make some comments to that.","index":68,"end_time":475.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":472.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep, pretty much.","index":69,"end_time":477.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is just extra contacts that we generated to get it going.","index":70,"end_time":482.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And next, you guys said that you want to talk about goals for 2026.","index":71,"end_time":492.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, we have a couple questions on the screen, but we''re hoping you can just.","index":72,"end_time":498.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You guys can do most of the talking and let us know kind of what you''re thinking for this next year.","index":73,"end_time":503.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":499.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What does success look like?","index":74,"end_time":505.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is there like a number you have in mind or a certain number of leads?","index":75,"end_time":509.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":505.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, yeah, I, I''ll take it from here, Will, if you don''t mind.","index":76,"end_time":517.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":513.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, so I''m going to share here.","index":77,"end_time":524.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":518.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let me.","index":78,"end_time":524.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":524.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And just give you access.","index":79,"end_time":528.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":527.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":80,"end_time":529.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you.","index":81,"end_time":533.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":82,"end_time":534.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You see that spreadsheet there?","index":83,"end_time":535.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":534.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not yet.","index":84,"end_time":538.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":537.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Oh, there it is.","index":85,"end_time":539.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":538.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":539.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":539.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So our Sales forecast for 2026 is $2.41 million in new sales.","index":87,"end_time":547.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we don''t need to get into the weeds about how we.","index":88,"end_time":551.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":548.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How we track the number, what that number looks like.","index":89,"end_time":553.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But we want $2.4 million in new revenue opportunities coming our way.","index":90,"end_time":559,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We track a different way of retention and overall growth as a company, but new sales through the sales development process, marketing efforts, prospecting, referral, etc.","index":91,"end_time":570.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":560.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then over on the far left over here, you''ll see this is how I have it broken up on how these sales come to fruition.","index":92,"end_time":579.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":572.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And not only do I keep track of them in here in a spreadsheet, because then I do all my projections for, you know, quarters and month end and all that good stuff.","index":93,"end_time":590.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":580.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I also have this tagged in HubSpot.","index":94,"end_time":593.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":590.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when a deal comes in or a lead comes in or a prospect or, or anything, or a new customer is buying five stores or adding a store or, you know, of that nature, I take that opportunity, proposal, prospect or whatever in HubSpot according to these buckets right here.","index":95,"end_time":615.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":594.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So CFO services is new, but that does relate into our marketing efforts.","index":96,"end_time":622.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":616.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":97,"end_time":623.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":622.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then.","index":98,"end_time":624.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":624.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I''ll talk about the marketing number.","index":99,"end_time":627.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So what I''ve done and how I''ve always done sales projections in my career is I do a rolling three, and you''ll see that number there.","index":100,"end_time":635.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":627.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t need to share that with you.","index":101,"end_time":636.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":635.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But What a rolling 3 does is it takes three years of sales, and then you take an average of that and then you say, hey, for the past three years, you''ve been averaging X amount of sales per these efforts.","index":102,"end_time":651.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":637.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then what we do is we determine how much we want to grow in new sales.","index":103,"end_time":656.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":653.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then I, we take a look at that number and we say, okay, hey, we want to grow by 20%.","index":104,"end_time":661.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":656.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That equates to $2.4 million.","index":105,"end_time":664.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":662.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s kind of how it worked out.","index":106,"end_time":666.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":665.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the number that I''ve always applied is a certain percentage of that number of the $2.4 million is, you know, the referral, marketing, direct business and upsell increase.","index":107,"end_time":683.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":667.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we''re keeping CFO services.","index":108,"end_time":685.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":683.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So just to jump to the chase, so for marketing, and that would be, you know, any attempts of the campaigns, your content, they find us on Google.","index":109,"end_time":697.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":686.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We go to shows any kind of marketing expense per se, and I tag that as marketing.","index":110,"end_time":704.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":697.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we''re looking at 446,250 new marketing sales for this year.","index":111,"end_time":711.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":704.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then in addition, we''re looking for 624,000 in CFO services.","index":112,"end_time":716.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":712.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So roughly a little over a million dollars in those two.","index":113,"end_time":722.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In those two buckets.","index":114,"end_time":724.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":723.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Any questions on that?","index":115,"end_time":727.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":726.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":729.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do you know what the numbers were last year for those buckets?","index":117,"end_time":732.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":729.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or I guess CFO services.","index":118,"end_time":733.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like this is a newer bucket, right?","index":119,"end_time":736.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":120,"end_time":737.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Here, I''ll tell you.","index":121,"end_time":738.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":737.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So last year was 292,500.","index":122,"end_time":746.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":743.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":123,"end_time":748.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s like, see?","index":124,"end_time":750.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":749.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, you can see.","index":125,"end_time":751.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":752.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":751.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We only did 4.","index":127,"end_time":754.708,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"$750 in sales that related to marketing efforts.","index":128,"end_time":758.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":755.092,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it came out to a 17% to goal.","index":129,"end_time":761.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":758.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":130,"end_time":763.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":763.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then CFO, you see there''s nothing in the CFO.","index":131,"end_time":767.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":764.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":132,"end_time":767.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"One thing that might be helpful, Nick, is to.","index":133,"end_time":772.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is to give them a, like, like if we''re a 30 unit opportunity, like a 30 unit restaurant group where we''re doing the accounting, we typically charge 450 a unit.","index":134,"end_time":787.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":772.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So a 30 unit would be 175.","index":135,"end_time":789.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":787.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was going to go into that next.","index":136,"end_time":792.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was, I was assuming they''re going to be like, well, how feasible is it get to, you know, 446,000.","index":137,"end_time":797.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":792.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What are we charging for CFO services?","index":138,"end_time":800.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that will relate to kind of the leads I was looking at.","index":139,"end_time":803.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, sorry.","index":140,"end_time":804.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just wanted to know how to evaluate those numbers.","index":141,"end_time":809,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":805,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sure.","index":142,"end_time":809.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll jump into that, Bailey.","index":143,"end_time":811.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, any other questions on those numbers right now?","index":144,"end_time":813.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":811.56,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, I think that that''ll make sense.","index":145,"end_time":818.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":815.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I do.","index":146,"end_time":819.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.76,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"In HubSpot you mentioned you have like these buckets.","index":147,"end_time":822.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":819.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If I were to look at last year, are they organized in those buckets?","index":148,"end_time":826.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if I wanted to see like the marketing wins from last year, I could find those?","index":149,"end_time":830.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":826.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":150,"end_time":831.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":830.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yep.","index":151,"end_time":831.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":831.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":152,"end_time":832.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Awesome.","index":153,"end_time":832.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll definitely move around.","index":154,"end_time":834,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That was one of my first tasks when I came in and joined with Will and GSS is kind of reorganize a front end sales processing and pipeline management.","index":155,"end_time":845.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":834.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that was one of the first things I did.","index":156,"end_time":848.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there should be about four, a good four and a half, five years of tracking, referral, marketing, you know, DBD and upsell increase.","index":157,"end_time":858.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then CFO services is new this year.","index":158,"end_time":861.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So there''s a couple of opportunities in there already for CFO services.","index":159,"end_time":865.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":861.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But yeah, you could do a search on that and you could see what we won, you know, what all marketing deals came in and then what we won versus lost and we can talk about that with leads.","index":160,"end_time":879.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":866.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I also on another spreadsheet, and I don''t want to bore you sheets, but I also have another spreadsheet where I keep track of all the opportunities and then it''s just a total for me that I plug into here.","index":161,"end_time":893.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":879.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But in that spreadsheet, I keep track of win loss and the percentage of opportunities coming in.","index":162,"end_time":901.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":895.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it, it tracks my close ratio.","index":163,"end_time":904.219,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":901.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":164,"end_time":906.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And yeah, so I mean, historically on a rolling average, it used to be a little bit higher.","index":165,"end_time":912.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":906.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s been dipping.","index":166,"end_time":912.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I only attribute that to if we''ve increased our sales opportunity size.","index":167,"end_time":918.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":912.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when I first came on, we were, you know, we were quoting smaller deals, closing more deals.","index":168,"end_time":925.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":919.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now we''re quoting larger deals and it''s, it''s kind of, it''s starting to get convoluted.","index":169,"end_time":930.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":925.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s the last year and a half, it''s kind of thrown a wrench into the plan.","index":170,"end_time":934.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":930.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So hopefully, I mean, we''ve been quoting deals at 6, $700,000 on an annual basis, and I think we''ve won one of those.","index":171,"end_time":942.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And there''s been multiple ones that we''ve been quoting, which is great news.","index":172,"end_time":946.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":943.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":173,"end_time":946.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":946.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But the close ratio on that is quite a bit lower than, hey, I got a, you know, a seven unit Taco Bell.","index":174,"end_time":953.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":946.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":955.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then obviously data, though.","index":176,"end_time":957.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":958.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":957.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I don''t have it hyper broken down.","index":178,"end_time":959.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":958.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, I could, but I didn''t do it.","index":179,"end_time":962.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":959.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I could calculate close ratios based on the lead too.","index":180,"end_time":965.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":962.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like, hey, marketing leads, I close at 18%.","index":181,"end_time":968.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, direct business development, 5% referrals, a hundred percent upsell increase a hundred percent.","index":182,"end_time":976.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":969.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t have it broken down into close ratios in that I just got, hey, overall average and we''re tracking at like 37%.","index":183,"end_time":985.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":976.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so if we do the math, how many opportunities do we need in the pipeline?","index":184,"end_time":993.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":985.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How many leads do we need in the pipeline to get to that number?","index":185,"end_time":997.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":994.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We just have to do the quick math of 37%.","index":186,"end_time":1000.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":998.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I haven''t done that yet.","index":187,"end_time":1002.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1001.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, that''s not that difficult to do.","index":188,"end_time":1004.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it''s, I mean, we''re going to need for marketing leads over a million dollars in marketing leads in, in proposals sent out in order to get that number.","index":189,"end_time":1014.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1006.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":190,"end_time":1015.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then CFO services.","index":191,"end_time":1017.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1016.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":192,"end_time":1018.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1017.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Now I''m not hyper focused on analytics on that or anything.","index":193,"end_time":1021.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1018.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This is the first year of it that we''re tracking it.","index":194,"end_time":1023.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1021.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s.","index":195,"end_time":1025.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1024.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s, you know, a completely different sales process and it''s, it''s just different.","index":196,"end_time":1031.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1025.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So let''s just, you know, hang out on that.","index":197,"end_time":1034.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1031.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But.","index":198,"end_time":1035.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":199,"end_time":1037.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So any questions?","index":200,"end_time":1038.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1037.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, this is great.","index":201,"end_time":1040.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1039.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so what, what I would like to do is focus on a number of, I guess a dollar size of leads.","index":202,"end_time":1055.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How many leads do we need to get in?","index":203,"end_time":1059.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1057.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t.","index":204,"end_time":1060.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Did anybody do the math real quick?","index":205,"end_time":1062.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1060.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I guess I haven''t done it yet.","index":206,"end_time":1063.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1062.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if we do.","index":207,"end_time":1065.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"See.","index":208,"end_time":1069.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Minus 63%.","index":209,"end_time":1071.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1069.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":210,"end_time":1074.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we need $1.2 million, let''s just say that for now, $1.2 million in marketing leads.","index":211,"end_time":1082.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1074.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then if I close 37% of that, that''s roughly $444,000.","index":212,"end_time":1089.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1085.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":213,"end_time":1090.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1090.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think I did the math right there.","index":214,"end_time":1092.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1090.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So then how do we get to the $1.2 million?","index":215,"end_time":1095.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1093.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What does that look like?","index":216,"end_time":1097.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1095.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I, I think you''re privy to how we go to market and how we do proposals, Bailey, where we, you know, standard accounting services.","index":217,"end_time":1110.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s a majority of our leads and a majority of our proposals.","index":218,"end_time":1112.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1110.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That go out.","index":219,"end_time":1113.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Our standard accounting services is priced into three different service sets.","index":220,"end_time":1117.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1113.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We have simplistic, high efficiency sandwich chains and pizza chains.","index":221,"end_time":1124.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1118.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we have, and that''s, that''s a low number.","index":222,"end_time":1128.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1126.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s around, let''s just say $350 per location per unit.","index":223,"end_time":1133.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1128.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we have your, your mainline QSRs, you know, big brands, everything but McDonald''s.","index":224,"end_time":1142.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1134.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, just think drive thru focus, you know, Hardee''s, whatever it is, Arby''s, Taco Bell, all that jazz that comes in at 4, $450 per location.","index":225,"end_time":1154.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1142.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then we have fast casual.","index":226,"end_time":1159.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1156.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''S.","index":227,"end_time":1161.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Anything a little bit more complex and not mainline like streamed and regional brands.","index":228,"end_time":1168.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1162.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Fast casual things with it always.","index":229,"end_time":1171.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s a little gray area there when we propose these numbers, but anything that has a little bit more complex invoicing, process payables, a lot of more moving parts.","index":230,"end_time":1182.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1171.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, like when you do a mainline Taco Bell, it''s look, they got like six vendors.","index":231,"end_time":1188.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1183.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, it''s like, it''s pretty bam, bam, bam, you know, and it''s, it''s, it''s a lot easier to do their accounting for the most part.","index":232,"end_time":1194.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1188.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not always, but for the most part.","index":233,"end_time":1195.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1194.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But then when you get into like a fast casual that has a ton more line items, a ton more invoices, a ton more vendors, a little bit more complexity there.","index":234,"end_time":1204.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1196.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are 750 a location.","index":235,"end_time":1207.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1204.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then, then we go into the full service world where there''s a lot of complexities.","index":236,"end_time":1213.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1208.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s liquor, there''s wine, there''s beer, there''s tips, there''s you know, local vendors, national vendors, regional vendors, and there''s just a lot more going on.","index":237,"end_time":1223.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1213.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s your sit down locations, that''s you know, like your fine dining restaurants, those kind of situations.","index":238,"end_time":1229.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1223.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And those are 1100 a location.","index":239,"end_time":1231.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1229.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, so to get to $1.2 million in marketing leads, I''m telling you right now, it''s not that difficult.","index":240,"end_time":1241.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1232.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''ll give you a perfect example.","index":241,"end_time":1244.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1242.66,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We did get a marketing lead.","index":242,"end_time":1247.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1245.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think it was last year, maybe it was the year before that.","index":243,"end_time":1250.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1247.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hey, we found you on, you know, on the Internet.","index":244,"end_time":1252.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1250.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I went into HubSpot and oh, the, the CFOs been tagged getting newsletters for a while.","index":245,"end_time":1258.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1253.38,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''ve been, he''s been getting marketed, he found us, he''s been getting hit.","index":246,"end_time":1263.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1258.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You know, it might be a subconscious thing.","index":247,"end_time":1265.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1263.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And he comes in and you know, the guy owns 100 Taco Bells, 100 Taco Bells at 300 or $450 a location.","index":248,"end_time":1274.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1265.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s half of our goal almost right there.","index":249,"end_time":1277.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1275.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s one lead half of our goal.","index":250,"end_time":1279.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1277.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":251,"end_time":1282.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1281.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":1283.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No.","index":253,"end_time":1283.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s awesome.","index":254,"end_time":1284.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So when we''re talking about marketing leads, these are all going to be focused more on your accounting services keeping separate from the cfo.","index":255,"end_time":1292.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1284.579,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve yet to give that a lot of thought.","index":256,"end_time":1295.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1294.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":257,"end_time":1296.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1295.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because right now we''re focused on CFO services and marketing.","index":258,"end_time":1300.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1296.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, I mean, I. I really don''t have an answer for that.","index":259,"end_time":1308.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1302.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if we''re looking at, you know, 1.1 million, then this number goes up, you know, to 2.4, 2.5 million.","index":260,"end_time":1316.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1309.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But now when CFO Services land.","index":261,"end_time":1320.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1318.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You.","index":262,"end_time":1322.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1322.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Know, just one client is, you know, $10,000 a month.","index":263,"end_time":1327.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1322.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s just on average, you know, we charge between like 8 and 12, maybe even higher sometimes.","index":264,"end_time":1332.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1328,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if we''re doing, you know, to say, $10,000 a month at $120,000 a year, we''re looking at, we''re trying to close four to six CFO services.","index":265,"end_time":1344.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1334.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So let''s, let''s do that on a simple way.","index":266,"end_time":1348.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if we''re looking to try to close four to six new CFO services, we would need what, six minus 10, 12?","index":267,"end_time":1358.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''d say 14 leads.","index":268,"end_time":1361.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1358.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"14 CFO leads.","index":269,"end_time":1363.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1361.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So one to two leads a month if I were to close them.","index":270,"end_time":1367.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1363.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I have no idea if I''m closing these things at 37%.","index":271,"end_time":1370.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1367.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s the problem.","index":272,"end_time":1370.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1370.17,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, yeah, let''s shoot for the moon on that.","index":273,"end_time":1373.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1371.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let''s.","index":274,"end_time":1373.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1373.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let''s get four leads a month and then see what happens.","index":275,"end_time":1377.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1374.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Love it.","index":276,"end_time":1384.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1383.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":277,"end_time":1385.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we got to aim for four CFO services leads a month.","index":278,"end_time":1392.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for accounting.","index":279,"end_time":1396.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If we were to do leads and kind of put it into perspective, I mean, I guess I could find an average, like how many deals we closed, and then just divided by the top line revenue and say, hey, we''ve, you know, last year we did, you know, $1.2 million, $1.5 million, whatever it was, divided by the amount of deals or amount of, you know, pipe, you know, amount of proposals that were sent out that were closed.","index":280,"end_time":1424.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1398.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I could get an average size cost, but it''s very convoluted because a lot of those are like, hey, we added one location, and that''s $3,000 annually.","index":281,"end_time":1435.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1425.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And you''re like, okay.","index":282,"end_time":1436.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1435.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I would say, I mean, will, you might be able to help me out here?","index":283,"end_time":1441.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1437.9,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Average size client, average revenue spend, and then we could divide that by 1.2 million.","index":284,"end_time":1448.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1442.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That can kind of give us an idea of the amount of leads needed.","index":285,"end_time":1451.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1448.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, 200, 200 units is basically, is that number if it''s all QSR.","index":286,"end_time":1459.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1452.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if, I mean if I don''t, I think it''s hard, it can be hard to get like I do think that the, let''s say the guy that is, is getting the newsletters and he''s kind of being nurtured and then one day he decides that now''s the time to reach out.","index":287,"end_time":1479.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think he is, he''s a longer term sale.","index":288,"end_time":1485.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1480.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like if you have 100 units, that''s, that''s 600, 700,000.","index":289,"end_time":1491.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s a big decision.","index":290,"end_time":1492.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But it can be, you can get 20, I''m sorry, five 20 unit opportunities much easier.","index":291,"end_time":1502.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1493.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that guy is not going to have the time.","index":292,"end_time":1505.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"He''s just going to make his decision quickly.","index":293,"end_time":1508.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So you know, five 20 unit deals, I mean it might be harder for us in some respects to service that but I think from a marketing and sort of return on investment that''s going to be easier to get to.","index":294,"end_time":1523,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1508.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think that the message inside of our hash book and some of the recent marketing is targeted to that, that segment rather than the Big Guy.","index":295,"end_time":1531.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":296,"end_time":1532.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that that guy also offers CFO services as well.","index":297,"end_time":1538.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just see like, like we''re doing really well in the, in the, you know, the history, just for sake of this discussion, I may have said this before is that we kind of did CFO services but not seriously just we kind of did it for a few customers that asked and we went, we, we got organized in 25, we got Munson who we spoke about.","index":298,"end_time":1561.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1538.62,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s been a good, a good customer for us.","index":299,"end_time":1564.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1561.98,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s 400.","index":300,"end_time":1565.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1564.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They, we do about 400,000 with them.","index":301,"end_time":1567.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1565.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I think there''s a lot of, I, I, and I don''t, I think there''s a lot of groups like that.","index":302,"end_time":1573.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1568.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But if you were to say, okay, if we were to take all the casual dining brands, you know, in each of those brands there''s at least two groups that fit that profile that we could probably win and be applicable to.","index":303,"end_time":1588.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1574.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like once you do the, once you sort of narrow it down because there''s I don''t know how many restaurants, but there''s just, there''s 7,000 Taco Bells in the United States.","index":304,"end_time":1598.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1588.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So like the numbers are huge and we''re not asking for a big number to hit our, hit our metrics.","index":305,"end_time":1605.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1598.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think what''s, what''s causing us a little bit of concern is that in the ABM campaign we haven''t gotten even one since we started one conversation that, that''s concerning it seems like if, if we were to superimpose three months into the next year, that, that seems like we''re not doing something right.","index":306,"end_time":1629.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1606.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean even if you take out the, the, the holiday period, I mean something''s not triggering people and I don''t know if we should be trying to target CFO plus the accounting or how, what the right approach is, but for whatever reason it doesn''t seem that appealing for people to get 30 days free.","index":307,"end_time":1650.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1629.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, because I, I did agree with Tristan''s sort of opinion that makes, make it irresistible like give them something.","index":308,"end_time":1662.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1651.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I thought that was, but I mean even the, we were, we have a customer that we were going to try to get their CFO services, they''d expressed an interest and I felt like we could offer them the 30 days during the holidays.","index":309,"end_time":1678.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1662.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Somehow they, they got a fractional CFO or somebody that they''re going to be paying and they, we weren''t even able to, to pull the trigger on the 30 day free I had, I''ve been offering them now the 30 day free until they get up to speed with the guy they''re paying.","index":310,"end_time":1694.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1678.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I don''t, I mean it''s just not, it''s not something that''s being perceived to be irresistible.","index":311,"end_time":1702.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe for that service there''s nothing that could be irresistible.","index":312,"end_time":1705.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1702.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":313,"end_time":1705.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The people look at it as real complex but I mean something''s not working right in that feel that feels to me.","index":314,"end_time":1714.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1705.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, there''s definitely something not clicking and I mean that''s part of ABM though.","index":315,"end_time":1722.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1715.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s just like testing a lot of things until you, you see what lands.","index":316,"end_time":1727.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.79,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like we''re making some hypothesis hypotheses, however you say that to, to test them out.","index":317,"end_time":1735.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1728.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I agree we should definitely switch out some things.","index":318,"end_time":1737.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1735.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ve got a couple ideas on just like new ways we can run, run the campaigns and Yeah, I, I think that, yeah, just like reworking some things, trying some new things out.","index":319,"end_time":1753.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1737.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Especially like early in the year we''ve got some time to, to hit the goals so that we can make sure we, we hit your goals for the year.","index":320,"end_time":1763.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1754.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You have some stuff right now.","index":321,"end_time":1767.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1766.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can we see?","index":322,"end_time":1767.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can we see?","index":323,"end_time":1768.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can we see?","index":324,"end_time":1768.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Can you see?","index":325,"end_time":1769.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1768.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know, I know we''re really close to time, but I can go like quickly over a couple ideas and we can spend more time next week or we can like schedule another meeting this week to tick over a few more things in detail.","index":326,"end_time":1783.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1771.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s up to you.","index":327,"end_time":1786.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1786.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I, I, I''m free for a few more minutes.","index":328,"end_time":1789.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1786.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think so.","index":329,"end_time":1790.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1789.84,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1790.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1790.6,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t got anything.","index":331,"end_time":1791.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1790.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think this is really important.","index":332,"end_time":1794.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If.","index":333,"end_time":1795.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1794.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"If we want to set up more time later this week, I would be up.","index":334,"end_time":1798.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve got another meeting, but let''s schedule time again later this week, if that''s okay, and we can go over some more ideas and get.","index":335,"end_time":1806.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1799.28,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Get some stuff rolling quickly.","index":336,"end_time":1807.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1806.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":337,"end_time":1808.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.4,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''d be great.","index":338,"end_time":1809.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1808.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":339,"end_time":1810.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1809.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We''ll talk again later then.","index":340,"end_time":1812.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1810.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, thanks, all.","index":341,"end_time":1813.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1812.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, we''ll see you.","index":342,"end_time":1814.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1813.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":343,"end_time":1814.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1814.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":344,"end_time":1815.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1814.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":345,"end_time":1815.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1815.45,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2026-01-21T16:58:36.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFGQWTK9WJ3WTY0RHE5F98VJ","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Launched finalized ebook with clickable CTA and shared distribution plan including LinkedIn and newsletter.","Paused ABM campaign due to outreach limits; list replenished with new CFO/CEO contacts for review.","Set 2026 sales target at $2.41M new revenue; $446K from marketing and $624K from CFO services.","Confirmed goal of four new CFO service leads per month to meet $624K target.","Agreed to revise ABM campaign messaging after lack of December response; follow-up session scheduled."],"highlights":[{"quote":"So our Sales forecast for 2026 is $2.41 million in new sales.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"Paused ABM campaign due to too much outreach to same company.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"Let''s get four leads a month and then see what happens.","speaker":"Unknown"}],"topics":["abm","goals","delivery","marketing","cfo"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-24T22:47:12Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Strategy and Distribution**\n\nThe team finalized an **ebook with a new clickable email CTA linking to the global shared services URL** to improve post-download engagement (01:52).  \n- The ebook’s promotion will roll out in phases across social media, newsletters, and possibly paid ads to maximize reach.  \n- Sending the ebook via the **January newsletter** aims to leverage the existing HubSpot list for early traction and lead tracking.  \n- The team plans to monitor who downloads the ebook to identify engaged prospects for targeted follow-up.  \n- Additional distribution methods like website pop-ups are being considered to expand visibility beyond the current channels.\n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Optimization**\n\nThe ABM campaign was **paused due to excessive outreach to the same companies**, prompting a list enrichment focused on CFO and CEO titles to restart efforts (06:52).  \n- The enriched contact list will be reviewed and adjusted to resume LinkedIn and email outreach, aiming to regain momentum quickly.  \n- The team recognizes the current campaign’s low engagement, with **no meaningful conversations generated so far**, signaling a need to revise messaging and targeting strategies.  \n- New campaign ideas are in development to improve appeal, including potentially bundling CFO and accounting outreach for a stronger value proposition.  \n- Will offered to review the new list and provide feedback today to expedite reactivation and testing of fresh approaches.\n\n## **2026 Sales and Revenue Goals**\n\nThe **2026 sales forecast targets $2.41 million in new revenue**, split primarily between marketing-driven sales and CFO services (08:25).  \n- Marketing efforts aim for **$446,250 in new sales**, while CFO services target **$624,000**, totaling just over $1 million from these two streams.  \n- Last year’s marketing-related sales were **$247,500 (17% of goal)**, reflecting significant growth expectations for the coming year.  \n- The CFO services bucket is new for 2026, with a goal to close **4 to 6 new CFO service clients**, requiring about **14 qualified CFO leads annually** or roughly **4 leads per month** to sustain this pipeline.  \n- The sales close ratio averages **37%**, implying the need for approximately **$1.2 million in marketing leads** to meet the marketing sales target.  \n- Lead sizing and pricing vary by restaurant type, with accounting services ranging from **$350 per unit for simple chains** up to **$1,100 per unit for full-service restaurants**, guiding lead volume and revenue expectations.  \n- Large accounts, like a **100-unit Taco Bell deal worth about $450 per unit**, could nearly cover half the marketing goal with one win, showing the strategic value of targeting bigger groups alongside smaller ones.\n\n## **Sales Pipeline and Lead Management**\n\nSales tracking uses a **HubSpot system with tagged buckets for marketing, referrals, direct business, upsell, and CFO services**, enabling detailed pipeline visibility (13:46).  \n- Historical data shows a shift from smaller deals closed more often to fewer but larger deals, complicating close ratios and forecasting.  \n- Close rate variability exists by lead source: marketing leads close at about **18%**, direct business at **5%**, referrals and upsell near **100%**, averaging to an overall **37% close rate**.  \n- The team plans to refine lead volume targets based on average deal size and close ratios to hit revenue goals more precisely.  \n- Larger deals present longer sales cycles but greater revenue impact, whereas smaller deals may close faster, influencing marketing messaging and resource allocation.  \n- Will and Nick will collaborate to further analyze lead-to-win metrics and optimize pipeline management for better forecasting accuracy.\n\n## **Challenges and Strategic Adjustments in CFO Services Marketing**\n\nDespite efforts, the **ABM campaign has failed to spark interest in CFO services**, even with offers like 30-day free trials during holidays (26:00).  \n- The team suspects CFO service complexity and perceived risk reduce the attractiveness of current offers; the service might require a different value approach.  \n- Feedback from ongoing client discussions shows customers opting for fractional CFOs despite trial offers, highlighting market hesitation.  \n- Tristan and others suggest testing more compelling incentives or revising messaging to create an irresistible offer that overcomes buyer inertia.  \n- Early-year timing provides a window to test new campaign ideas and pivot quickly to meet the CFO services lead goal.  \n- The team agreed to schedule follow-up meetings this week to review and refine campaign tactics and accelerate progress.","outline":null,"keywords":["ebook distribution","ABM campaign","sales forecast 2026","CFO services leads","marketing leads targets","HubSpot tracking"],"overview":"- **Ebook Launch:** A new ebook with clickable email CTA launches via January newsletter for early traction and tracking.  \n- **ABM Campaign Pause:** Campaign paused due to outreach issues; enriching CFO and CEO contact list to resume efforts.  \n- **2026 Revenue Goals:** Targeting $2.41 million in new revenue, mostly from marketing sales and new CFO services clients.  \n- **Sales Pipeline Insights:** HubSpot tracks multiple lead sources; average close rate is 37% with variances by lead type.  \n- **CFO Services Challenge:** Current ABM strategy hasn''t engaged CFO services; need revised messaging or stronger incentives for appeal.  \n- **Testing New Strategies:** Upcoming meetings scheduled to refine campaign tactics and boost progress toward CFO leads.","action_items":"\n**Unknown (likely marketing/management team)**\nUpdate the ebook''s last page CTA to include a clickable email and correct global shared services URL (01:52)\nProvide social media posts for ebook promotion on LinkedIn personal pages and coordinate newsletter inclusion before the end of January (05:06)\nSend enriched CFO and CEO contact list for ABM campaign review and reactivation (06:52)\nReview and comment on the new contact list for ABM outreach including LinkedIn and email (07:31)\nPrepare and share new ABM campaign ideas for discussion in follow-up meeting this week (28:42)\n\n**Will (likely sales lead)**\nShare sales forecast spreadsheet and explain sales bucket tracking and close ratio methodology for 2026 goals (08:25)\nPerform calculations on required lead volume based on close ratios and quota targets (16:46)\nAssist in determining average client revenue sizes to estimate volume of leads needed to meet marketing sales targets (23:45)\nCollaborate on refining CFO services lead definitions and target setting (23:45)\n\n**Nick (likely marketing/operations)**\nOrganize HubSpot and sales pipeline data for easy tracking of deals classified by marketing and CFO services buckets, and analyze historic sales data (13:46)\nTrack win/loss ratio and calculate close percentages differentiated by lead source (15:19)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"5f2ade04-7ad7-43ea-9a3d-7ae557efc914","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
