  'Meeting Notes: Hydrian x New North Weekly Meeting 01.21.26',
  '## **Survey Response and Engagement Strategy**

The team plans to boost survey participation by changing distribution methods and considering incentives to improve response rates.

- **Two new survey responses** arrived after the latest reminder, showing ongoing engagement but at about **50% of the previous response volume** (03:45)
    - Switching the survey email domain aims to reduce messages landing in spam folders for the next distribution.
    - Bailey noted mixed answer consistency, with the current survey showing more varied responses than the initial one.
    - The survey will be linked through HubSpot in the upcoming newsletter and also sent via Mailchimp to broaden audience reach.
    - Offering a **$50 gift card** prize in a draw was proposed as a low-cost incentive to increase participation, pending further discussion with Josh.

- The team now has access to detailed **open and unopened email stats**, improving transparency compared to previous blind spots (06:28)
    - SurveyMonkey’s new analytics help identify who responds and who might miss the survey due to spam filters.
    - These insights support refining future survey outreach to improve engagement rates.

## **Booth and Brochure Messaging Alignment**

Efforts are underway to refresh booth materials to better reflect current messaging and improve readability for trade shows.

- The **brochure text was condensed and rewritten** to align with the website’s messaging and make it punchier for quick scanning at events (09:04)
    - The goal is to communicate clearly what the company does in simple terms visible to passersby.
    - Shorter, bigger text replaces dense paragraphs to encourage scanning and engagement.
    - Graphics and icons are being reviewed for consistency with the website’s current style, aiming for brand cohesion.
    - Bailey emphasized the need to reflect the company’s advisory role rather than just software features, highlighting evolving customer expectations.

- The booth design and brochure final files are being prepared for print after incorporating these edits (07:46)
    - Design fixes include reducing white space and enlarging fonts for better legibility.
    - The survey links in the newsletter now feature a colored bar for visibility, a format planned for reuse in future editions.

## **Strategic Positioning and Client Communication**

The team is adjusting the company’s positioning from a software vendor to a hybrid advisory and technology partner, based on client feedback and market needs.

- Bailey explained that clients want **clear guidance and actionable advice**, not just software tools, reflecting a shift toward a consultative approach (13:07)
    - The company is increasingly asked to advise on process changes and task execution, blending technology with advisory services.
    - This hybrid model differentiates the company from pure software providers and pure consulting firms.
    - Messaging updates aim to reflect this dual role clearly, reducing client confusion and aligning sales and marketing communications.

- Consistency across website, brochures, and sales conversations is a priority to avoid mixed messages during client interactions (15:44)
    - This alignment is critical to maintain trust and clarity throughout the buyer journey.
    - QR codes on brochures lead to additional assets that reinforce this messaging strategy.

## **Client Testimonials and Content Development**

Building a stronger pipeline of client testimonials and case studies is recognized as vital to supporting sales and marketing efforts.

- The team identified a need for **more testimonials and case studies**, including anonymous formats to respect client confidentiality (17:02)
    - Bailey plans to discuss testimonial opportunities with Josh, especially with clients like Imperial, despite some approval challenges.
    - Third-party interviews were suggested as a low-pressure way to gather authentic client stories.
    - Taylor and Bailey see these as key content assets to showcase results and build credibility.

- These testimonials will be repurposed across website content and social media, including carousel posts to highlight client success (18:25)
    - Drafts for carousel post copy are being finalized and will be shared for review soon.
    - This content will help communicate the company’s value proposition more vividly on social channels.

## **Process and Collaboration Improvements**

The team is improving feedback handling and collaborative document management to streamline design and messaging workflows.

- Moving to a **markup-based feedback system** will simplify managing multiple rounds of design comments and revisions (22:10)
    - This change will reduce confusion from scattered feedback and improve document clarity.
    - Michael will consolidate all design notes into a single markup file for easier review and version control.
    - The team agreed this approach is more user-friendly, especially given the volume of feedback involved.

- Upcoming meetings will focus on strategic brainstorming and reviewing the goals document to refine direction further (19:39)
    - Josh’s participation is mandatory to ensure alignment and full team input.
    - The meetings aim to integrate new ideas with existing plans, allowing for iterative improvements in strategy and execution.',
  '2026-01-23 21:55:45+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Monitor incoming SurveyMonkey responses and provide updated PDF by Friday with current data (03:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Switch survey domain in next distribution to avoid spam folder issues (03:45)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize newsletter edits with design team, adjusting layout, font size, and white space issues (07:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Send revised brochure text and comments separately for review, ensuring improved alignment with website messaging (09:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Review website icon library and propose updated graphics for brochure consistency (11:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Send markup links for all design files to facilitate easy commenting and review (22:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare final booth design files for print and share with team (19:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Share copy outline for social media carousel posts for client edits later in the day (19:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss client testimonial opportunities and permissions with Josh; report back with updates (17:02)","completed":false},{"text":"Participate in next week’s brainstorming and strategy session, prepare to review referral partnership and goals document (20:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate inclusion of survey link in new newsletter via HubSpot and Mailchimp distribution lists to increase response rates (05:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate testimonial collection from clients, including offering anonymous Zoom interviews (17:02)","completed":false},{"text":"Review attached final design templates and provide feedback (19:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Review social media carousel post copy and provide edits or suggestions as needed (19:39)","completed":false},{"text":"Attend next brainstorming and strategy session, ensure Josh’s attendance (20:50)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
