-- Meeting: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting (2026-01-22 15:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ff2ef389-756d-4ece-b525-93fab32170d6',
    '2026-01-22 15:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KFE636G2X6ZGXWQEQPM6V7BP',
    'New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Taylor Doerbaum","Lauren Poirier","Baylee Gunnell"}'::text[],
    1254,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1',
    '{"id":"01KFE636G2X6ZGXWQEQPM6V7BP","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Audience Targeting Refinement**\n\nThe team finalized a more precise targeting strategy focused on specific university roles to improve survey relevance and engagement (02:11).\n\n- **Lauren Poirier** clarified that the survey should target roles in **real estate, space, and facilities leadership** at approximately **400 priority U.S. and Canadian universities** as the primary audience, excluding CIO, IT, and finance leadership roles (03:17).\n    - This change aligns with the tailored survey questions, ensuring respondents have relevant expertise.\n    - Lauren emphasized combining the U.S. and Canadian universities into a single list for simplicity.\n    - Taylor Doerbaum confirmed the team updated the audience spreadsheet to reflect these role and university prioritizations, including around **200-300 contacts** per key title group (06:06).\n    - This focused approach aims to increase survey response quality and decision-maker engagement.\n\n- The secondary audience was defined as the same roles but across all remaining universities outside the priority list (08:19).\n    - Taylor ensured the updated lists cover both countries and multiple industry-specific titles.\n    - Lauren approved this segmentation and requested the combined lists to streamline internal tracking.\n\n## **Survey Development and Outreach Approach**\n\nThe survey will be built using SurveyMonkey and integrated into multi-channel outreach to maximize participation (09:03).\n\n- Taylor outlined a plan to create the survey on **SurveyMonkey’s free platform** with the client’s logo, using a **simple questionnaire** to avoid respondent fatigue (09:47).\n    - The survey link will be embedded within a messaging sequence consisting of two emails (initial and reminder) and LinkedIn messages.\n    - Multiple sending domains will be used to increase deliverability and speed response rates.\n    - Survey responses will be compiled in SurveyMonkey, with results shared as PDFs for client review.\n\n- Lauren shared that final approval on the survey approach is pending review by a newly onboarded **North American marketing team lead, Jessica**, expected to speed decision-making (09:17).\n    - This leadership change centralizes approval and should reduce delays.\n    - Taylor will hold off on full survey build-out until formal approval is received.\n\n- The team agreed that **paid advertising will accompany the survey outreach** to enhance brand awareness and response rates, filling a prior gap where ads were not run simultaneously (11:27).\n    - Taylor explained options for targeted ads, including retargeting website visitors and segment-specific messaging.\n    - Lauren approved adding this advertising plan into the campaign document for clarity.\n\n## **ABM Campaign Messaging and Ad Segmentation**\n\nThe ABM ads will be segmented into two key groups to balance granularity and budget constraints while maximizing audience reach (15:17).\n\n- Taylor and Baylee recommended grouping audiences into **space titles and facilities titles** rather than more granular splits, to ensure sufficient volume for ad delivery (15:39).\n    - Lauren confirmed these two groups align with internal priorities and have adequate contact size (over **600 names in facilities** alone).\n    - This segmentation supports tailored messaging while maintaining campaign efficiency.\n\n- Taylor noted the ability to create different ad messaging for each group, pulling from survey question themes to maintain relevance (14:56).\n    - Lauren will consider messaging options to ensure synergy between survey content and ads.\n\n## **Call Scheduling and Lead Management**\n\nThe team identified a need for a streamlined scheduling process for follow-up calls to reduce manual workload and improve lead handling (16:40).\n\n- Lauren confirmed that scheduling will likely be handled by herself and a solutions team member, but currently, no calendar link or scheduling platform like Calendly is in use (17:33).\n    - Taylor recommended implementing an online scheduling tool to reduce back-and-forth and missed opportunities.\n    - Lauren acknowledged this as a gap but noted coordinating multiple calendars could be challenging.\n\n- For now, incoming interest will be managed via the existing **contact us form**, though Taylor noted this may add friction for respondents (18:30).\n    - They agreed to keep this under review and potentially introduce a scheduling link in the future for efficiency.\n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nThe team plans to launch the updated campaign in early **February**, pending quick approval from the new marketing lead (19:41).\n\n- Lauren expects Jessica to review and likely approve the survey and campaign materials promptly, though final sign-off is still uncertain (19:57).\n    - Taylor will send the updated audience spreadsheets and revise the ABM plan to reflect discussed targeting and outreach strategies immediately after the call.\n    - Once approved, the team will build the messaging sequences and finalize campaign components.\n\n- Video edits will be addressed in parallel, with the design team’s feedback incorporated before resubmitting for review (02:11).\n    - Taylor will coordinate these updates alongside the campaign deliverables.\n\n- Both Lauren and Taylor confirmed clear communication channels and readiness to proceed once approvals are secured (20:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Audience targeting","survey outreach","ABM campaign","paid ads","scheduling tool","video storyboard"],"overview":"- **Target Audience Defined:** Survey targets real estate and facilities roles at 400 U.S. and Canadian universities, excluding CIO and finance.\n\n- **Survey Development Plan:** Survey will use SurveyMonkey, with simple questions and multi-channel outreach via emails and LinkedIn.\n\n- **Advertising Strategy:** Paid ads will run alongside the survey to enhance awareness and response rates, targeting specific audience segments.\n\n- **ABM Messaging Efficiency:** Ads will be grouped into space and facilities titles for effective outreach, ensuring sufficient audience size.\n\n- **Streamlined Scheduling Needed:** Current lead management relies on contact form; a scheduling tool is suggested to reduce manual work.\n\n- **Campaign Launch Timeline:** Updated campaign expected to launch in early February, pending quick approvals from the new marketing lead.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend updated audience spreadsheet with revised segmentation to Lauren for review (19:01)\nIncorporate Lauren’s edits into the ABM plan and share revised document (19:01)\nBegin survey build in SurveyMonkey once approval is granted (09:47)\nDraft messaging sequences for survey outreach and call-first campaigns with placeholder scheduling link (18:58)\nReview and start video edits based on storyboard feedback (20:00)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview updated audience spreadsheet and confirm segmentation for primary and secondary audiences (19:01)\nShare storyboard markups and clarifications with internal design team as needed (02:50)\nObtain final approval from new North American marketing team lead, Jessica, on survey and campaign approach (19:41)\nConsider and confirm if Planon will establish a scheduling tool (e.g., Calendly) for call-first outreach (17:33)\nDetermine if paid ads messaging will align with survey topics or remain separate and provide direction accordingly (14:56)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAdvise on ad group structure feasibility and budget considerations for persona-based messaging split (15:39)\n"},"duration":20.899999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"id":1,"name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sam.","index":0,"end_time":25.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hey there.","index":1,"end_time":40.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":42.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good.","index":3,"end_time":43.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":42.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":4,"end_time":43.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How was your weekend?","index":5,"end_time":44.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":43.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It was good.","index":6,"end_time":46.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":45.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I always forget, like when people ask me during the week on the weekend, I feel like I forget.","index":7,"end_time":50.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I forget everything when people ask, like, what''s new?","index":8,"end_time":55.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, couldn''t tell you.","index":9,"end_time":57.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have no idea.","index":10,"end_time":58.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Oh, I remember now.","index":11,"end_time":60.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I went to one of those head spas with my friends.","index":12,"end_time":63.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":61.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, nice.","index":13,"end_time":64.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was so nice.","index":14,"end_time":65.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I loved it.","index":15,"end_time":67.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So recommend.","index":16,"end_time":68.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you guys haven''t done it yet.","index":17,"end_time":69.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s.","index":18,"end_time":70.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was so relaxing.","index":19,"end_time":71.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, that sounds amazing.","index":20,"end_time":73.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Maybe like a scalp treatment or is it like a massage?","index":21,"end_time":76.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":73.09,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"They did like a bunch of stuff.","index":22,"end_time":78.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They did like the red light in your hair with like this massage.","index":23,"end_time":81.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then they did like a.","index":24,"end_time":82.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":81.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like those fancy combs.","index":25,"end_time":84.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then they give me like a facial during it.","index":26,"end_time":86.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":84.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was crazy.","index":27,"end_time":87.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it wasn''t like a bad price and it was in Austin, so I was kind of surprised.","index":28,"end_time":91.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, it was really.","index":29,"end_time":93.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":91.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It was really fun.","index":30,"end_time":94.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":93.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a good girls day thing to do.","index":31,"end_time":96.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":94.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s my favorite part of getting my hair done.","index":32,"end_time":99.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Or a haircut, like when they are shampooing your hair for you.","index":33,"end_time":103.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Then you''d love it.","index":34,"end_time":104.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You would love it.","index":35,"end_time":105.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":104.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll have to try it.","index":36,"end_time":107.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":105.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it was a lot of fun.","index":37,"end_time":109.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":107.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nice.","index":38,"end_time":110.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":39,"end_time":112.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"All right, let me.","index":40,"end_time":114,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":112.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m going to pull up a couple of things to, like, go through, but did you have anything you wanted to start with?","index":41,"end_time":120.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was going to go through our updated audience targeting and things like that and then get into kind of next steps.","index":42,"end_time":125.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if you have any updates, I''ll let you start too, because I know I sent you a few things over the week.","index":43,"end_time":129.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sure.","index":44,"end_time":130.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I think we''re good on the contract amendment.","index":45,"end_time":133.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you for sending the fully executed version back, the video edits.","index":46,"end_time":138.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.32,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I heard back from our design team.","index":47,"end_time":140.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They went through the storyboard and he said he left comments in markup.","index":48,"end_time":144.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":140.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"He did say that his comments that he left were all sort of comments that he''s made before on edits that should be made.","index":49,"end_time":153.679,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":145.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So from here, just so I''m confident that I know how this is going to work.","index":50,"end_time":160,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So you guys will go back and make those changes to the storyboard and then send it to us again for review, right?","index":51,"end_time":165.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":165.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":166.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":165.88,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s how we''ll do the next step.","index":54,"end_time":168.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":55,"end_time":168.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, so that was.","index":56,"end_time":171.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":170.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That was what he said.","index":57,"end_time":172.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":58,"end_time":172.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You guys should have those comments and markup.","index":59,"end_time":176.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then if you have any clarifying questions, I can.","index":60,"end_time":181.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can share that with him too.","index":61,"end_time":183.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I did have a chance to go through The ABM plan.","index":62,"end_time":188.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.64,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you for putting together that document.","index":63,"end_time":190.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"This reads really well.","index":64,"end_time":192.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":190.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I like this a lot.","index":65,"end_time":193.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I have a few edits that I''d like to make.","index":66,"end_time":196.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":67,"end_time":197.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Mainly to the target audience section.","index":68,"end_time":200.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I see you broke it down by priority audience, which is the call first, and the secondary, which is survey first, which I think is a great strategy.","index":69,"end_time":207.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":200.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The only thing here.","index":70,"end_time":210.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So the CIO and IT leadership and finance leadership, these two, we haven''t really tailored the survey to those roles.","index":71,"end_time":220.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I don''t think that we should include those in our targeting.","index":72,"end_time":222.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":73,"end_time":223.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then facilities leadership is also important.","index":74,"end_time":226.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So facilities, space and real estate are the three that we tailored the questions towards.","index":75,"end_time":231.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So what I''m thinking is instead of breaking down primary and secondary by those role types, if the primary can be those 400 something universities that I sent you, I think last week, if those, if people from those three types of roles at those 400 universities can be our primary audience and then everyone else who fits those three type of roles at the rest of the universities can be the secondary.","index":76,"end_time":257.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":77,"end_time":258.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that''s for U.S. and Canada, both of them.","index":78,"end_time":260.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":79,"end_time":261.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":261.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":262.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can change that.","index":81,"end_time":263.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I wanted to make sure.","index":82,"end_time":266.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I, I know we had talked about a couple of specific things that you had said which will go where.","index":83,"end_time":271.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just wanted to have you review it so that makes sense.","index":84,"end_time":273.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can change that around.","index":85,"end_time":275.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":273.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because I know we were kind of going back and forth on exactly what, what we''ll do as far as who''s the first and second.","index":86,"end_time":280.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I think that that would be good.","index":87,"end_time":283.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Sorry, I don''t see your comments in here.","index":88,"end_time":286.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":284.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s the only one, but the version I''m looking at doesn''t have comments in it.","index":89,"end_time":291.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, I just said left you.","index":90,"end_time":292.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think that was the only comment I left.","index":91,"end_time":295.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, because I, I knew this was kind of up in the air, exactly what we were going to do.","index":92,"end_time":298.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":93,"end_time":299.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes, perfect.","index":94,"end_time":301.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s just the one thing that I had a comment on.","index":95,"end_time":305.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":302.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":96,"end_time":307.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So going off of that, we built out the audiences based on what you and I had talked about last week.","index":97,"end_time":314.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I went ahead and created an updated spreadsheet here.","index":98,"end_time":319.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t want to keep like messing with the current ones.","index":99,"end_time":321.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll just keep a new version each time.","index":100,"end_time":322.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So this is the latest spreadsheet.","index":101,"end_time":324.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, and what you''ll see at the bottom here is I have the old real estate one here.","index":102,"end_time":330.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We went ahead and added some, but then we were seeing it pulling the same universities.","index":103,"end_time":336.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we went ahead and re.","index":104,"end_time":338.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Pulled a list and so that.","index":105,"end_time":341.459,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s what you''ll see here.","index":106,"end_time":342.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.459,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''ll see the new.","index":107,"end_time":343.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And this is what you can just review after the call, whenever you have time.","index":108,"end_time":346.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We try to get more titles and names like you were talking about, make the list closer to 200, 300.","index":109,"end_time":352.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we were able to do that here for real estate.","index":110,"end_time":354.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the same thing with Director of Space.","index":111,"end_time":356.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You can ignore this one.","index":112,"end_time":358.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This was kind of like our test.","index":113,"end_time":359.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then you''ll see new here for, again, the Director of Space titles.","index":114,"end_time":364.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So then we.","index":115,"end_time":364.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think we got this to exactly 200.","index":116,"end_time":366.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":367.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":366.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you, after the call, just want to kind of peruse.","index":118,"end_time":370.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We tried getting all those upper executives and director titles like you were talking about people that can actually make decisions or talk to people that can make decisions.","index":119,"end_time":378.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":120,"end_time":378.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we were mindful of that here.","index":121,"end_time":380.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I figured it would just be easiest to separate them.","index":122,"end_time":384.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We built out each of the.","index":123,"end_time":388.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you were just talking about the universities for the US that were most important and Canada.","index":124,"end_time":392.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":388.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we built them out again by these titles.","index":125,"end_time":394.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you can click across all of these tabs at the bottom here, and they are all the universities that you had said that you wanted to target.","index":126,"end_time":403.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we just created out lists for each of the same industry specifics.","index":127,"end_time":410.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":403.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then same with Canada over here.","index":128,"end_time":412.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you''ll see that across the board over here, some of them, there are more titles to pull than others.","index":129,"end_time":417.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But again, if we''re just using this as like a whole, as a spreadsheet for our audience, then we should have plenty, because there are some.","index":130,"end_time":424.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Some of them have a lot of contacts versus the others.","index":131,"end_time":427.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But this is what you were thinking, right, Building them out this way?","index":132,"end_time":430.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly, exactly.","index":133,"end_time":431.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":430.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And if it''s easier for you to keep track of.","index":134,"end_time":434.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"For me, there''s no significance in separating out.","index":135,"end_time":437.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":434.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Separating out the U.S. and Canadian universities.","index":136,"end_time":440.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Those can all be in the same one sheet of the accounts.","index":137,"end_time":444.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":440.5,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":138,"end_time":445.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you''re fine with that, then we can combine them into.","index":139,"end_time":447.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":445.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll just put them into each of their own tabs here.","index":140,"end_time":451.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I can combine them.","index":141,"end_time":452.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, if you just want to take a look at that.","index":142,"end_time":454.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said, we tried getting the upper levels as far as the audience specifics, but I''ll send that to you after this meeting.","index":143,"end_time":462.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we should have that all set now.","index":144,"end_time":464.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So awesome.","index":145,"end_time":466.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yes.","index":146,"end_time":467.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the priority audiences then would be those two top.","index":147,"end_time":471.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"These two new spreadsheets with the US Universities and Canadian university titles.","index":148,"end_time":476.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":472.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":149,"end_time":477.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So just real estate titles, space titles, and facilities titles at those priority U.S. and Canadian universities.","index":150,"end_time":485.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.149,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":487.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":487.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You said real Estate space.","index":152,"end_time":492,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":490.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And what was the other one?","index":153,"end_time":493,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Facilities.","index":154,"end_time":493.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.16,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":155,"end_time":494.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":156,"end_time":499.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then secondary audience.","index":157,"end_time":501.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":499.88,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It should still just be real estate space and facilities titles, but at all the remaining universities.","index":158,"end_time":506.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, Okay, perfect.","index":159,"end_time":514.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":160,"end_time":516.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How about everything else on here?","index":161,"end_time":518.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did this look good as far as everything else, the way it was built?","index":162,"end_time":520.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is this kind of what you were looking for to take back to your internal side?","index":163,"end_time":523.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, no, this is great.","index":164,"end_time":525.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The only other thing that I have a question about, so I noticed there wasn''t a lot about the methods that we''re going to use for outreach.","index":165,"end_time":534.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So whether it''s, you know, emails, whether we''re going to do like, add graphics and what that.","index":166,"end_time":541.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":534.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What that will look like.","index":167,"end_time":542.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":541.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, so that was one of my questions here.","index":168,"end_time":545.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll pull this up now.","index":169,"end_time":546.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, because we were kind of up in the air about exactly the approach we''re going to take, I don''t know if you have confirmation now.","index":170,"end_time":551.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are we good to go ahead with the survey approach?","index":171,"end_time":553.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you get all your approvals that we can start building it out?","index":172,"end_time":557.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":173,"end_time":558.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So a little bit of an update there.","index":174,"end_time":560.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just this week we have brought on another member of the North American marketing team and she has done a lot of ABM in the past.","index":175,"end_time":567.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":560.02,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think I''ll run this document and our approach by her and get her thoughts.","index":176,"end_time":573.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t know that we''ll need to run it by anybody else at that point because she is sort of our new team lead.","index":177,"end_time":580.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So hopefully that means that she is like the one person that needs to approve this.","index":178,"end_time":585.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m hoping that will speed things up.","index":179,"end_time":586.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":585.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":180,"end_time":588.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, so that will kind of go into the next step.","index":181,"end_time":591.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So as soon as we get your approval on that, specifically what we can do, this is how I''m thinking we''re going to do it, is we''ll build out the survey with the questions that you had sent us, which I did put into a document document here with Survey Monkey.","index":182,"end_time":605.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":591.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''re able to just get a free version of Survey Monkey.","index":183,"end_time":608.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll create an account and I''ll create the survey within there.","index":184,"end_time":611.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":608.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll just put one of your logos on the top and I''ll send you an example of what it looks like.","index":185,"end_time":615.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And basically it will just have the questions.","index":186,"end_time":618.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":615.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to make it as easy as possible so people don''t think it''s like a long survey.","index":187,"end_time":622.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then what we''ll do is from there we''ll get a link from Survey Monkey and we''ll create a messaging sequence around this.","index":188,"end_time":629.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So probably like two emails, like a.","index":189,"end_time":632.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Here''s a survey and then a reminder email and then same with LinkedIn messaging.","index":190,"end_time":636.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And because we have three different domains to use, we can utilize that and go across and kind of get these through faster.","index":191,"end_time":643.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would just input that link that we get from SurveyMonkey into our messaging sequence.","index":192,"end_time":647.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that way people can click directly from that link and then go take the survey and then everything will be compiled into the SurveyMonkey platform.","index":193,"end_time":654.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can send you a PDF of all the responses that we get and it''ll show you all the data through there.","index":194,"end_time":661.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s the way I''m thinking about it.","index":195,"end_time":662.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would continue to utilize LEM List and heyreach, then we''d keep our same platform.","index":196,"end_time":666.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if it''s helpful, I can put that in the document to just reiterate the fact that we''ll use those same platforms and just introduce a link from SurveyMonkey to kind of create that.","index":197,"end_time":674.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would be a very basic form.","index":198,"end_time":676.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We don''t want to spend extra money.","index":199,"end_time":677.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it would just have like your logo and.","index":200,"end_time":679.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that would be pretty much it with the, with the questions.","index":201,"end_time":681.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds great.","index":202,"end_time":683.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then so that would mean no paid advertising for the survey promotion.","index":203,"end_time":687.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":204,"end_time":688.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, so I think we still need to do simultaneous ABM ads since we didn''t get to do that last time around.","index":205,"end_time":693.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So whether that is, you know, boosting the brand awareness kind of like we had last time, or if we create new ads that are kind of specific to the messaging that you''re wanting to get across.","index":206,"end_time":702.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as these specific questions, I think it would just be beneficial.","index":207,"end_time":707.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":702.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"ABM campaigns, it''s helpful to have simultaneous ads running with them.","index":208,"end_time":711.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we didn''t get to do that for the last time.","index":209,"end_time":713.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":210,"end_time":713.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I agree, I agree with that.","index":211,"end_time":716.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":717.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you could add just that, that to the document, that would be helpful to have that all in one place.","index":213,"end_time":721.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":214,"end_time":724.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":723.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that kind of ties into one of these other campaign ideas that we talked about, like either in the intent based outreach or targeted ads or the sandbox test approach.","index":215,"end_time":736.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":216,"end_time":737.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Doing some additional paid advertising within one of those sort of ideas.","index":217,"end_time":741.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, so we can.","index":218,"end_time":743.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me pull that up.","index":219,"end_time":744.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have that here.","index":220,"end_time":745.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":744.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So these were just the ideas that I know we had presented with Dan.","index":221,"end_time":749.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, you know, we could use specific targeted ads across like what we''re doing with these audiences or we could use a specific group like he was talking about.","index":222,"end_time":758.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think Dan was mentioning like website visitor data where we''re retargeting the same people, people that have had engagement with ads.","index":223,"end_time":765.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":758.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we could have like a specific ad Group running for those.","index":224,"end_time":768.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":765.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that is one of the options.","index":225,"end_time":770.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":769.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then targeted ads too.","index":226,"end_time":772.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This was specific to launching the ABM target accounts and then, you know, paying attention to visits or clicks about who specifically is doing that.","index":227,"end_time":779.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then once we see somebody triggered one of those engagements, then we would send a follow up email because we''ve seen that they''ve engaged with the content.","index":228,"end_time":786.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So those are the two ones I think depending on.","index":229,"end_time":789.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, once you look over that audience and make sure everything is good to go as far as our audience spreadsheet, we can go from there as far as what specific audience you want to do for the ABM ads.","index":230,"end_time":801.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.93,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we want to have two running or things like that.","index":231,"end_time":803.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":801.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, those are two different approaches that we could take.","index":232,"end_time":807.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":805.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":233,"end_time":808.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that leads me to my next question.","index":234,"end_time":810.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":808.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Is there any harm in targeting the same audience that we''re trying to target for the survey?","index":235,"end_time":816.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.14,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like are we going to overdo it by.","index":236,"end_time":818.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":816.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No.","index":237,"end_time":819.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No harm in there?","index":238,"end_time":820.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"No, not at all.","index":239,"end_time":821.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If anything it''s better.","index":240,"end_time":822.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then they''ll be like these people and then they''ll just finally take the survey.","index":241,"end_time":825.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":822.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, no, it can''t hurt to.","index":242,"end_time":827.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Can''t hu to.","index":243,"end_time":828.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":827.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s usually how we do it.","index":244,"end_time":830,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like the previous one that we had set up those ads and we were going to launch them that was going to target the same audience we were already sending the emails and messages to.","index":245,"end_time":837.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":830,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It just kind of is like a second layer of advertising your, your name out there and, and try to get that brand awareness and also hopefully responses.","index":246,"end_time":845.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So in this case it would be good because then, you know, we want the survey responses.","index":247,"end_time":848.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you guys have that data.","index":248,"end_time":849.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, the paid ads will be for a different asset though, right?","index":249,"end_time":852.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":850.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It won''t be for the survey.","index":250,"end_time":853.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Well, we can, yeah, I mean, I think we could just do something different.","index":251,"end_time":859.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":855.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if you wanted to create like a messaging for the ads around kind of the topics that we''re doing for the survey, if it''s like beneficial to your audience, then we would want to talk through that messaging.","index":252,"end_time":870.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if it was, you''re like, let''s just do some different kind of ads and ad copy, we could do that as well.","index":253,"end_time":875.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It can, it can be, you know, however you want to best, I guess advertise out for those ads.","index":254,"end_time":882.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":875.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Specifically we can pull in some survey aspects to it because I know those questions you guys had made specific across different industries, which would be helpful.","index":255,"end_time":890.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can just kind of pull from there if that makes sense.","index":256,"end_time":892.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":890.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":257,"end_time":894.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":894.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll think about that.","index":258,"end_time":898.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":896.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, like I said, once we have the approvals on Everything else, we can come with a better plan on how.","index":259,"end_time":906.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As soon as we know exactly what kind of ABM campaign we''re doing, we get approval on the survey.","index":260,"end_time":910.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Then next time we could talk about how we can do simultaneously ads with that campaign to best kind of like push it.","index":261,"end_time":917.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":262,"end_time":917.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":917.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Can we.","index":263,"end_time":919.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I know what your answer is going to be based on the different, like Personas that we have, the different tabs in our audience spreadsheet.","index":264,"end_time":927.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":919.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Can we do different ad messaging for each of those Personas?","index":265,"end_time":931.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.25,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think we could do ad groups for that.","index":266,"end_time":934.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is that correct, Bailey?","index":267,"end_time":935.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":934.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Where we could separate.","index":268,"end_time":935.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would just be different campaigns.","index":269,"end_time":937.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can separate things out.","index":270,"end_time":942.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We don''t want to get like too granular with that just because it''s gonna.","index":271,"end_time":948.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Budget wise, it will not really make sense to do that.","index":272,"end_time":951.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":948.62,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But like, if you wanted to split it maybe in like two groups, like, that would be fine.","index":273,"end_time":955.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.78,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":274,"end_time":956.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":955.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sometimes if you don''t have enough names for like the ads that we run, they don''t get pushed out as far.","index":275,"end_time":961.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we took like one of the like 100 audience ones list, it''s not going to get pushed out as far.","index":276,"end_time":966.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":961.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And LinkedIn will even flag it and say there''s not enough like, contacts for this, like campaign.","index":277,"end_time":971.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":966.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We need to add more.","index":278,"end_time":972.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we make them two big groups, that would probably be easier, like Bailey was saying.","index":279,"end_time":976.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":973.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think if we did maybe space and facilities as the two, our two groups, that would probably be the best bet for us.","index":280,"end_time":984.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we just want to make sure that there''s enough of an audience.","index":281,"end_time":987.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have facilities.","index":282,"end_time":989.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":987.77,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There were like 6, 600 plus names on the original, so hopefully that would be enough.","index":283,"end_time":993.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":284,"end_time":994.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if we''re combining it with another tab too, then we should, we should get there.","index":285,"end_time":998.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":994.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":286,"end_time":999.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":998.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right.","index":287,"end_time":1000.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1000.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":288,"end_time":1001.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.49,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I like it.","index":289,"end_time":1003.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1002.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":290,"end_time":1003.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1003.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me see.","index":291,"end_time":1005.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1004.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, so like I said, we would just create that messaging sequence around that and then so the other part of this would be the call to action for the call specifically.","index":292,"end_time":1015.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s what I wanted to do.","index":293,"end_time":1017.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1015.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just double check here.","index":294,"end_time":1018.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the call first outreach that we had talked about, so that would be a different messaging sequence as far as that goes.","index":295,"end_time":1026,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you guys have a particular link that you use for people to schedule this?","index":296,"end_time":1029.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1026,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because if we have like a reply to this email kind of thing to schedule, that could get just hairy with making sure we have all the responses and getting back to them.","index":297,"end_time":1037,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you guys just have a link that people can click, like a calendar link, like set up a call with someone from our team?","index":298,"end_time":1043,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"One of my other Clients has like a, a calendar link that we just attach through the sequence.","index":299,"end_time":1048.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way we don''t have to do the back and forth and it''s just easier for people to schedule that way.","index":300,"end_time":1053.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we don''t use any platform like that.","index":301,"end_time":1057.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.81,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"At least no one that I''m aware.","index":302,"end_time":1060.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Maybe I can try to set that up.","index":303,"end_time":1062.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It will probably be me and one of our solutions team.","index":304,"end_time":1067.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it would be me who they who would have to have the calendly account since I''m not sure which person on their team is going to be for each meeting or if you.","index":305,"end_time":1078.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1068.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Guys normally I know you have a couple links on your website where it''s like click here to.","index":306,"end_time":1083.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know there''s like scheduled demo but if there was something like that where somebody could click a link to, you know, set up a time.","index":307,"end_time":1090.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If not we could, could do it open ended.","index":308,"end_time":1092.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1090.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s just easier if sometimes we have a link people can utilize that way it''s just less back and forth.","index":309,"end_time":1097.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":310,"end_time":1099.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1097.43,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But you''re not going to be on the calls, right?","index":311,"end_time":1103.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1101.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would be somebody else on the calls.","index":312,"end_time":1104.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It would probably be me and on the solutions team.","index":313,"end_time":1108.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Oh, gotcha.","index":314,"end_time":1109.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Nice.","index":315,"end_time":1110.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1109.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I would say we could use the contact us form that, that almost everybody.","index":316,"end_time":1117.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"More work, that almost feels like more work for the respondent than just responding to the email.","index":317,"end_time":1122.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, probably not.","index":318,"end_time":1123.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That one would be the best route.","index":319,"end_time":1125.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean you could think about it.","index":320,"end_time":1126.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said we have some time to work that out.","index":321,"end_time":1128.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1126.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I, I can create a sequence and just kind of have a placeholder for that.","index":322,"end_time":1131.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1128.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can work that out after.","index":323,"end_time":1133.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I was just curious if off the top of your head you had, you had something like that.","index":324,"end_time":1137.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1133.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No.","index":325,"end_time":1138.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We should though.","index":326,"end_time":1138.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We really should.","index":327,"end_time":1139.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1138.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Be tricky to, to coordinate everybody''s schedules though, so.","index":328,"end_time":1144.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1141.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Understandable.","index":329,"end_time":1144.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1144.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":330,"end_time":1145.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":331,"end_time":1147.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1146.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So from here then I''m going to go ahead and send you those updated audience spreadsheet so you can just do a quick look and then I will make those adjustments that we talked about to this executive plan and then we''ll just wait to hear back from you.","index":332,"end_time":1164.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as the specifics of if we''re good to go for the survey and then we can start building out, you know, the messaging sequences and everything like that.","index":333,"end_time":1172.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you thinking you''ll get approval like sooner than later?","index":334,"end_time":1176.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like we would be able to launch hopefully in February for this new campaign?","index":335,"end_time":1180.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope so.","index":336,"end_time":1182.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1181.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m sure that this new person, her name''s Jessica.","index":337,"end_time":1186.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.39,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m sure she''ll get back to me very quickly.","index":338,"end_time":1188.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1186.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What I don''t know is how she feels about being the one to give final approval on this.","index":339,"end_time":1195.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.75,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So stay tuned on that.","index":340,"end_time":1197.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":341,"end_time":1198.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1197.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, that sounds good.","index":342,"end_time":1200.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, I will keep updated with you, then I''ll just look for updates in teams and I''ll.","index":343,"end_time":1205.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1200.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll send you these things over, and then we''ll also take a look at those video edits and get those started, too.","index":344,"end_time":1209.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1205.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":345,"end_time":1210.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1209.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":346,"end_time":1210.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":347,"end_time":1212.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1211.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was there anything else that you had questions about?","index":348,"end_time":1214.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1212.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, I think that was everything from me.","index":349,"end_time":1217.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":350,"end_time":1218.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1218.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know how to reach you.","index":351,"end_time":1219.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1218.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yep.","index":352,"end_time":1221.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1220.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right.","index":353,"end_time":1224.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1223.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Bye.","index":354,"end_time":1224.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I hope you have a good rest of the day.","index":355,"end_time":1225.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1224.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You, too.","index":356,"end_time":1226.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":357,"end_time":1226.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1226.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"See you.","index":358,"end_time":1227.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"}],"dateString":"2026-01-22T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KFE636G2X6ZGXWQEQPM6V7BP","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Agreed to revise audience targeting to focus on facilities, space, and real estate roles only.","Taylor confirmed updated spreadsheets segment U.S. and Canadian universities by relevant decision-maker roles.","Lauren expects swift internal approval from new ABM team lead, targeting February campaign launch.","Team plans to use SurveyMonkey with LEM List and Heyreach for survey outreach, avoiding additional costs.","Discussed layering paid ads with survey outreach using two persona groups for budget efficiency."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We should have that all set now.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"Yeah, no, this is great.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"},{"quote":"Once we have the approvals... we can come with a better plan.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["audience","survey","ads","ABM","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-23T20:41:57Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Audience Targeting Refinement**\n\nThe team finalized a more precise targeting strategy focused on specific university roles to improve survey relevance and engagement (02:11).\n\n- **Lauren Poirier** clarified that the survey should target roles in **real estate, space, and facilities leadership** at approximately **400 priority U.S. and Canadian universities** as the primary audience, excluding CIO, IT, and finance leadership roles (03:17).\n    - This change aligns with the tailored survey questions, ensuring respondents have relevant expertise.\n    - Lauren emphasized combining the U.S. and Canadian universities into a single list for simplicity.\n    - Taylor Doerbaum confirmed the team updated the audience spreadsheet to reflect these role and university prioritizations, including around **200-300 contacts** per key title group (06:06).\n    - This focused approach aims to increase survey response quality and decision-maker engagement.\n\n- The secondary audience was defined as the same roles but across all remaining universities outside the priority list (08:19).\n    - Taylor ensured the updated lists cover both countries and multiple industry-specific titles.\n    - Lauren approved this segmentation and requested the combined lists to streamline internal tracking.\n\n## **Survey Development and Outreach Approach**\n\nThe survey will be built using SurveyMonkey and integrated into multi-channel outreach to maximize participation (09:03).\n\n- Taylor outlined a plan to create the survey on **SurveyMonkey’s free platform** with the client’s logo, using a **simple questionnaire** to avoid respondent fatigue (09:47).\n    - The survey link will be embedded within a messaging sequence consisting of two emails (initial and reminder) and LinkedIn messages.\n    - Multiple sending domains will be used to increase deliverability and speed response rates.\n    - Survey responses will be compiled in SurveyMonkey, with results shared as PDFs for client review.\n\n- Lauren shared that final approval on the survey approach is pending review by a newly onboarded **North American marketing team lead, Jessica**, expected to speed decision-making (09:17).\n    - This leadership change centralizes approval and should reduce delays.\n    - Taylor will hold off on full survey build-out until formal approval is received.\n\n- The team agreed that **paid advertising will accompany the survey outreach** to enhance brand awareness and response rates, filling a prior gap where ads were not run simultaneously (11:27).\n    - Taylor explained options for targeted ads, including retargeting website visitors and segment-specific messaging.\n    - Lauren approved adding this advertising plan into the campaign document for clarity.\n\n## **ABM Campaign Messaging and Ad Segmentation**\n\nThe ABM ads will be segmented into two key groups to balance granularity and budget constraints while maximizing audience reach (15:17).\n\n- Taylor and Baylee recommended grouping audiences into **space titles and facilities titles** rather than more granular splits, to ensure sufficient volume for ad delivery (15:39).\n    - Lauren confirmed these two groups align with internal priorities and have adequate contact size (over **600 names in facilities** alone).\n    - This segmentation supports tailored messaging while maintaining campaign efficiency.\n\n- Taylor noted the ability to create different ad messaging for each group, pulling from survey question themes to maintain relevance (14:56).\n    - Lauren will consider messaging options to ensure synergy between survey content and ads.\n\n## **Call Scheduling and Lead Management**\n\nThe team identified a need for a streamlined scheduling process for follow-up calls to reduce manual workload and improve lead handling (16:40).\n\n- Lauren confirmed that scheduling will likely be handled by herself and a solutions team member, but currently, no calendar link or scheduling platform like Calendly is in use (17:33).\n    - Taylor recommended implementing an online scheduling tool to reduce back-and-forth and missed opportunities.\n    - Lauren acknowledged this as a gap but noted coordinating multiple calendars could be challenging.\n\n- For now, incoming interest will be managed via the existing **contact us form**, though Taylor noted this may add friction for respondents (18:30).\n    - They agreed to keep this under review and potentially introduce a scheduling link in the future for efficiency.\n\n## **Timelines and Next Steps**\n\nThe team plans to launch the updated campaign in early **February**, pending quick approval from the new marketing lead (19:41).\n\n- Lauren expects Jessica to review and likely approve the survey and campaign materials promptly, though final sign-off is still uncertain (19:57).\n    - Taylor will send the updated audience spreadsheets and revise the ABM plan to reflect discussed targeting and outreach strategies immediately after the call.\n    - Once approved, the team will build the messaging sequences and finalize campaign components.\n\n- Video edits will be addressed in parallel, with the design team’s feedback incorporated before resubmitting for review (02:11).\n    - Taylor will coordinate these updates alongside the campaign deliverables.\n\n- Both Lauren and Taylor confirmed clear communication channels and readiness to proceed once approvals are secured (20:18).","outline":null,"keywords":["Audience targeting","survey outreach","ABM campaign","paid ads","scheduling tool","video storyboard"],"overview":"- **Target Audience Defined:** Survey targets real estate and facilities roles at 400 U.S. and Canadian universities, excluding CIO and finance.\n\n- **Survey Development Plan:** Survey will use SurveyMonkey, with simple questions and multi-channel outreach via emails and LinkedIn.\n\n- **Advertising Strategy:** Paid ads will run alongside the survey to enhance awareness and response rates, targeting specific audience segments.\n\n- **ABM Messaging Efficiency:** Ads will be grouped into space and facilities titles for effective outreach, ensuring sufficient audience size.\n\n- **Streamlined Scheduling Needed:** Current lead management relies on contact form; a scheduling tool is suggested to reduce manual work.\n\n- **Campaign Launch Timeline:** Updated campaign expected to launch in early February, pending quick approvals from the new marketing lead.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend updated audience spreadsheet with revised segmentation to Lauren for review (19:01)\nIncorporate Lauren’s edits into the ABM plan and share revised document (19:01)\nBegin survey build in SurveyMonkey once approval is granted (09:47)\nDraft messaging sequences for survey outreach and call-first campaigns with placeholder scheduling link (18:58)\nReview and start video edits based on storyboard feedback (20:00)\n\n**Lauren Poirier**\nReview updated audience spreadsheet and confirm segmentation for primary and secondary audiences (19:01)\nShare storyboard markups and clarifications with internal design team as needed (02:50)\nObtain final approval from new North American marketing team lead, Jessica, on survey and campaign approach (19:41)\nConsider and confirm if Planon will establish a scheduling tool (e.g., Calendly) for call-first outreach (17:33)\nDetermine if paid ads messaging will align with survey topics or remain separate and provide direction accordingly (14:56)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nAdvise on ad group structure feasibility and budget considerations for persona-based messaging split (15:39)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"0c072f3e-7b52-4d0b-8e9f-ad1a890f00e6","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
