    '{"id":"01KF9C9D5CQ542N8KKD5EPF0H3","title":"BioSAFE Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Launch Confirmation**\n\nThe team confirmed the website is ready for launch, resolving link version issues and finalizing content (05:31).\n\n- **Dan Nelsen confirmed readiness to launch the website immediately**, resolving confusion caused by Brandon seeing an outdated version on Friday (01:06).\n    - Taylor Doerbaum clarified that all links are refreshed and redirected correctly, suggesting prior cached browser links caused the issue.\n    - Dan emphasized confidence that no links redirect to old pages, ensuring a smooth user experience.\n    - Taylor committed to notifying the developer to proceed, aiming for launch early the next morning for monitoring.\n    - Launch timing is flexible between today or tomorrow based on final checks and developer availability.\n\n- **Final content confirmation included updating homepage terminology from “biopharma companies” to “hospitals and Life Sciences”** to better target tissue digestor and effluent decon segments (02:24).\n    - Dan explained that “Life Sciences” covers biopharma adequately while aligning better with product focus.\n    - Taylor agreed to update the homepage text accordingly before launch.\n\n## **Inventory Page Development**\n\nPlans were made to create a flexible inventory page template that supports quick updates and file attachments (05:12).\n\n- **Dan outlined requirements for a modular inventory page allowing easy additions and removals of product listings**, with consistent formatting including title, subline, images, and paragraph text (04:11).\n    - He stressed the need for a common template due to product variants and occasional unique items.\n    - Dan requested the ability to attach files like cut sheets and O&M manuals to each listing for comprehensive user information.\n    - Taylor agreed to wait for detailed content from Dan before designing and building the page.\n    - Dan committed to providing existing inventory items to populate the initial listings.\n\n- **The inventory page design will not delay the website launch**, allowing the main site to go live while the inventory page is developed (05:18).\n    - Taylor will coordinate with the developer to start design work based on Dan’s forthcoming content.\n    - This approach ensures launch momentum while continuing product page enhancements.\n\n## **Content and Media Updates**\n\nThe team addressed last-minute content synchronization and media decisions ahead of launch (02:48).\n\n- **The developer will ensure all latest blogs and articles are integrated before launch** to maintain up-to-date content on the site (02:48).\n    - Taylor noted this may require some developer work post-approval but will be completed before going live.\n    - Dan confirmed no further changes to carousel images or GIFs are needed, focusing efforts on launch readiness.\n    - Taylor will communicate launch timing and status updates to Dan immediately after developer coordination.\n\n## **Stakeholder Communication and Coordination**\n\nClear communication lines and responsibilities were established to ensure smooth launch execution and post-launch monitoring (05:58).\n\n- **Taylor will send Dan a launch confirmation email and ongoing updates**, maintaining transparency and alignment throughout the process (05:38).\n    - Developer standby status was confirmed to enable quick response to any last-minute fixes or content updates.\n    - Dan expressed appreciation for the team''s responsiveness and readiness to proceed.\n    - This coordination supports immediate issue resolution and supports a stable rollout.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","Inventory page","Life Sciences","Hospitals","Template design","Developer coordination"],"overview":"- **Website Launch Confirmed:** Website is ready for launch, addressing previous link issues and final content checks.  \n- **Content Update:** Home page terminology changed to target hospitals and Life Sciences for better alignment with product focus.  \n- **Inventory Page Development:** Modular inventory page will support easy product updates and file attachments for user info.  \n- **Launch Timing:** Website launch can occur today or tomorrow, depending on final checks and developer availability.  \n- **Media Updates:** Developer will integrate latest blogs and articles before launch; no further changes to images required.  \n- **Communication Established:** Taylor will update Dan on launch status and maintain clear coordination for smooth execution.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nProvide text and content for the new ''available inventory'' page, including current floor stock details (05:12)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nUpdate homepage text to reflect ''Hospitals and Life Sciences'' instead of ''Biopharma Companies'' (02:27)\nInform developer to prepare for website launch after confirming blog/article updates (02:48)\nBuild flexible common template for the ''available inventory'' page with capacity for text, images, and file attachments once content is received (03:54)\nCommunicate launch timing and provide Dan with an email notification when the site goes live, coordinating developer’s schedule (05:31)\n"},"duration":6.510000228881836,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"id":1,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Joe.","index":0,"end_time":5.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Hey, Dan.","index":1,"end_time":6.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How are you doing this week?","index":2,"end_time":7.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Fine.","index":3,"end_time":9.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I had a little.","index":4,"end_time":10.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I. I guess.","index":5,"end_time":12.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"First bit for.","index":6,"end_time":14.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":7,"end_time":15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"First bit first.","index":8,"end_time":15.919,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We''re good to go on the website.","index":9,"end_time":17.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.919,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":10,"end_time":18.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My.","index":11,"end_time":20.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I sent the same link I''m using to look at it and look at it now.","index":12,"end_time":25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":21.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I know it''s the right link, but when Brandon clicked through it Friday, he saw, I think, one of the old sites or an old version of the site now when he went back to it this morning, and when I''m on it just now, it looks totally fine, I guess.","index":13,"end_time":44.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":25,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What happens if you click Affluent Decom there.","index":14,"end_time":46.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Scroll down.","index":15,"end_time":52.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, keep going, Keep going.","index":16,"end_time":57.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":56.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I just want.","index":17,"end_time":58.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.72,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I want to make sure.","index":18,"end_time":58.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":19,"end_time":59.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":58.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I was wondering if maybe one of the links was directing to an old page or something.","index":20,"end_time":63.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It shouldn''t be.","index":21,"end_time":67.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I haven''t seen that one.","index":22,"end_time":68.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s not.","index":23,"end_time":68.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m.","index":24,"end_time":69.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m.","index":25,"end_time":69.559,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Because he.","index":26,"end_time":70.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"He sent me a bunch of notes that I looked at.","index":27,"end_time":72.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I was like, none of these make sense.","index":28,"end_time":74.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So he was looking and he had screenshots.","index":29,"end_time":78.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So he was looking at an old version H. So I''m not sure why that would have happened, but he had a chance to go back through it and everything looks good.","index":30,"end_time":91.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":31,"end_time":92.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good.","index":32,"end_time":92.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":92.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m not sure why that.","index":34,"end_time":93.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_ti