    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/84801960534?pwd=tq9BFJBUCprJPJ0W7NRoAlJYH7bZXD.1&jst=2',
    '{"id":"01KFBFVS2VPDS1VEDPH92R5G0M","title":"Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Development and Design**\n\nThe team made key progress on the staging environment and case study page updates to support upcoming marketing efforts.\n\n- **Design updates for the case study page were delivered today**, with text alignment adjusted to be left-aligned for better readability (02:00)  \n    - Natalie confirmed the updated design was sent and ready to share with Rob quickly  \n    - Demir is handling major design and development changes on the staging environment to improve template structure  \n    - This work supports the overall goal of improving user experience and content presentation to boost engagement  \n    - The timeline aligns with the scheduled delivery of suggested case study edits tomorrow to finalize content  \n\n- **Structural questions on the staging environment will be addressed in a separate session** between Rob, Demir, and Natalie to refine the backend templates (01:10)  \n    - This ensures technical feasibility and smooth integration before the next deployment phase  \n    - Coordination between design and development teams aims to reduce rework and speed rollout  \n    - The staging environment improvements will enable more flexible content management and faster iterations  \n\n## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Email Campaigns**\n\nThe ABM email outreach volume increased significantly, but open rates are high with no replies yet, prompting refinement plans.\n\n- **Over 500 emails were sent last week, averaging about 100 per business day, with good open rates but zero replies so far** (02:35)  \n    - Rob noted the copy is low on calls to action, which may explain the lack of replies  \n    - He proposed tracking multiple opens to identify engaged contacts for targeted manual follow-up  \n    - Tristan agreed to generate reports from Smartly showing contacts with multiple opens to support this effort  \n    - Avoiding excessive API calls to HubSpot by limiting event pushes keeps the system stable while retaining analytics in source systems  \n\n- **Rob emphasized the importance of layering manual outreach on top of automated emails for better conversion** (04:03)  \n    - He shared that direct outreach often yields better quality leads than paid or automated channels  \n    - The current email copy is more exploratory than pushy, matching their cautious market approach  \n    - The team will reassess after completing a full email sequence cycle to decide on expanding or refining targets  \n    - The ABM strategy targets a small, specific market slice where personal relationships and handholding matter  \n\n## **Paid Media and Lead Quality Assessment**\n\nPaid channels provide awareness but generate mostly low-quality leads, impacting follow-up prioritization and analytics.\n\n- **Google search and LinkedIn ads generate leads that rarely qualify as sales-ready opportunities** (06:40)  \n    - Rob explained leads often come from individuals with limited buying power or outside core targets  \n    - Paid leads are tracked in HubSpot but often categorized as outbound due to data gaps on mid-funnel activity  \n    - The sales team prioritizes direct and enterprise contacts, reducing focus on paid channel leads  \n    - Rob stressed the need to map lead sources back to deal records for more accurate attribution and strategy refinement  \n\n- **Tristan proposed analyzing deal records to backtrack lead origins and optimize channel spend** (08:40)  \n    - Rob agreed deal records are the best proxy for qualified opportunities despite some gaps  \n    - They will test pulling data from Factors and Smartly to validate lead engagement against actual pipeline  \n    - This will help identify which paid and automated channels contribute to revenue, informing future investments  \n    - The approach aims to balance awareness generation with efficient resource allocation  \n\n## **Target Account List Expansion and Segmentation**\n\nThe team plans to test a wider target list after completing initial email sequences to reach more potential clients.\n\n- **Rob shared a list of over 200 companies labeled as Automated Facilities (AF) for potential expansion beyond core accounts** (17:52)  \n    - This list includes data center general contractors, manufacturing systems integrators, and warehouse players  \n    - The current direct outreach targets trades, which convert faster but cover a narrower segment  \n    - Expanding to AF accounts allows passive education campaigns to reach less-touched prospects  \n    - The idea is to clean and refine the list before launching campaigns, using tools like Clay for segmentation  \n\n- **Rob emphasized the difference in sales approach between trades and enterprise accounts** (15:27)  \n    - Trades yield faster, transactional deals while enterprise sales require longer handholding and partnership building  \n    - The team will run a full sequence on existing targets before deciding on wider campaigns  \n    - The AF list provides a scalable way to increase market coverage without overloading sales reps  \n    - This strategy supports long-term growth by nurturing a broader funnel at lower cost  \n\n## **Do Not Contact List and Contact-Level Opt-Outs**\n\nA system to exclude priority contacts from automated outreach will be implemented to respect relationships and reduce friction.\n\n- **Rob requested a way to exclude individual contacts from ABM email flows to avoid redundant or sensitive outreach** (19:55)  \n    - Tristan proposed building a blacklist in Clay that blocks these contacts before sending to Smart Lead  \n    - Rob agreed to coordinate with sales to provide the list via HubSpot exports or CSVs for easy updates  \n    - Natalie suggested uploading do-not-contact lists retroactively to prevent sending to these contacts in current campaigns  \n    - This measure balances automation efficiency with personalized relationship management to reduce risk  \n\n- **The team recognized the list size will likely remain small, making manual updates feasible** (22:28)  \n    - Regular syncing between sales and marketing will keep the blacklist current and accurate  \n    - This process prevents alienating important contacts while maintaining campaign scale  \n    - It reflects a careful approach to automation that respects existing trust and communication channels  \n\n## **LinkedIn Ad Campaign Planning and Retargeting**\n\nLinkedIn audience size is currently small, so the team will delay campaign launch to allow list growth and retargeting potential.\n\n- **Current LinkedIn contact audience is around 300, below the preferred minimum of 500 for efficient targeting** (24:30)  \n    - Tristan suggested expanding the list with additional roles to reach the threshold  \n    - Rob preferred waiting two weeks to let the email flows engage contacts before activating ads  \n    - The ads would then serve as retargeting to re-engage less responsive prospects  \n    - This phased approach aims to maximize ad spend ROI and avoid premature campaigns  \n\n- **Rob will review existing creative assets to determine if new ad formats are needed** (25:28)  \n    - The team agreed to postpone execution until the audience size and engagement justify the spend  \n    - This cautious approach aligns with their strategy to prioritize quality over quantity in lead generation  \n    - It also allows better integration of paid and organic outreach for sustained impact","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM","email campaigns","Factors analytics","lead qualification","blacklist management","LinkedIn ads"],"overview":"- **Website Updates Progress:** Case study page design delivered; key changes improve user experience and engagement for marketing efforts.  \n- **ABM Campaign Insights:** Over 500 emails sent, strong open rates but no replies; copy needs better calls to action for improved engagement.  \n- **Lead Quality Challenges:** Paid leads mostly low-quality; focus shifts to higher-value direct and enterprise contacts for better sales alignment.  \n- **Target Account Expansion:** New list of 200 Automated Facilities companies to broaden outreach; prepares for passive education campaigns to wider prospects.  \n- **Exclude Priority Contacts:** A \"do not contact\" list will be created to respect relationships and reduce outreach friction during automation.  \n- **LinkedIn Campaign Delay:** Current audience too small for ads; team will wait for list growth and improved engagement before launching campaigns.","action_items":"\n**Rob Schnitzler**\nExport blacklist contact list from CRM and coordinate with sales team on do-not-contact individuals (22:30)\nDiscuss adoption of RB2B personal identification tool internally with Derek and assess approach (26:00)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate and send suggested edits to case studies by tomorrow (01:50)\nUpload updated case study page design with left-aligned text to Rob promptly (02:00)\nUpload do-not-contact lists retroactively to Smart Lead to prevent outreach errors (23:30)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nCoordinate with Rob and Natalie to generate reports of multiple email opens from Smartly for manual outreach consideration (05:30)\nWork with team on building blacklist functionality in Clay for exclusion before sending contacts to Smart Lead (21:45)\nPrepare to test wider account list (''AF accounts'') in Clay for potential expanded ABM campaigns after initial sequence completion (18:00)\nFollow up on LinkedIn retargeting campaign readiness after audience size increases and more contact engagement data available (25:30)\n"},"duration":27.170000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":1,"name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"id":2,"name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"id":3,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Got.","index":0,"end_time":0.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can you hear us?","index":1,"end_time":3.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, just switching the Bluetooth.","index":2,"end_time":9.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, good deal.","index":3,"end_time":10.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, we''ve got.","index":4,"end_time":11.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":10.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve got Bailey here today.","index":5,"end_time":12.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Last time she was.","index":6,"end_time":14.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":13.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think she was in the air.","index":7,"end_time":15.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":14.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, last time.","index":8,"end_time":17.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":9,"end_time":18.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Good to meet you, Rob Bailey has landed, so she could join this.","index":10,"end_time":23.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"This meeting today.","index":11,"end_time":24.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, Natalie, if you want to go ahead and pull up agenda for today.","index":12,"end_time":30.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":24.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, Rob, we threw in some of the notes that you had as well.","index":13,"end_time":33.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know you also have a meeting with Demir and Natalie here in a little bit as well.","index":14,"end_time":41.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But for today, we want to go through a few outstanding items.","index":15,"end_time":45.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":41.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll cover in a second, go through some of the ABM metrics that we have, and then I know there are a few things to talk about that you sent yesterday as far as how to layer in some ads with the existing outreach you''re doing and some other things that we can kind of combine efforts on.","index":16,"end_time":64.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":46.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s what we thought we would go through today.","index":17,"end_time":66.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How''s that sound?","index":18,"end_time":67.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":19,"end_time":68.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":67.86,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":20,"end_time":68.899,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.26,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, so Natalie, let''s go to outstanding items.","index":21,"end_time":73.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So two things.","index":22,"end_time":74.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve got our staging environment that we''ve been working on.","index":23,"end_time":77.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I know, Rob, you have some structural questions or just like how to maybe shift some sections around, etc.","index":24,"end_time":86.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So you''ll have Demir today who''s really doing most of the heavy lifting if there''s any design or dev work that needs, you know, some major changes to the templates that we have on the back end.","index":25,"end_time":98.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So he''s actively doing that.","index":26,"end_time":100.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So him and Natalie will have that conversation today.","index":27,"end_time":102.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":100.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we do have the use case or case studies, the suggested edits, those already tomorrow.","index":28,"end_time":111.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that right, Natalie?","index":29,"end_time":112.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":111.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, those are the ones we sent over Slack.","index":30,"end_time":115.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":112.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we''ll have those updated for you tomorrow.","index":31,"end_time":117.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":115.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":32,"end_time":119.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then case study page design and development.","index":33,"end_time":124.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":120.68,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that is up updated design delivered today.","index":34,"end_time":128.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Natalie, I think I saw that just come through.","index":35,"end_time":130.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":128.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can probably get that to Rob pretty quickly here.","index":36,"end_time":133.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":130.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so we just.","index":37,"end_time":135.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":134.28,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The text to be more left aligned.","index":38,"end_time":137.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":135.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, good.","index":39,"end_time":142.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So anything else there, Rob?","index":40,"end_time":143.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, I know we''ll focus on the website here and when you jump on another half hour, but anything else that we left off here for you?","index":41,"end_time":151.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, it sounds perfect right now.","index":42,"end_time":153.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.81,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, so Natalie, we can go to the ABM activities.","index":43,"end_time":158.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So a couple things we wanted to go through.","index":44,"end_time":162.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Number one, smartly, we''ll start there.","index":45,"end_time":165.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the email sent the past week, so we''ve increased the number of email inbox or sorry, mailboxes that we have.","index":46,"end_time":173.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We pulled in several of the.","index":47,"end_time":175.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":173.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The folks you know that we warmed up over the holidays.","index":48,"end_time":178.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":175.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So now you have really all the folks that you identified.","index":49,"end_time":181.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We have emails going out from.","index":50,"end_time":182.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we have a velocity of about over 500 in a week that we can do.","index":51,"end_time":187.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''re getting to about 100 per business day.","index":52,"end_time":190.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We got an open rate but no replies yet.","index":53,"end_time":194.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So that''s something that, that we wanted to, to bring up.","index":54,"end_time":196.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.13,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, there''s probably at this volume, no real changes to make.","index":55,"end_time":201.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But it''s something of note.","index":56,"end_time":203.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That said, we do have Factors is like a, you know, a background data collection layer.","index":57,"end_time":211.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s where we''re able to see who''s visiting the site.","index":58,"end_time":214.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How does that line up with some of the accounts that we have in place?","index":59,"end_time":218.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":215.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we did pull in some repeat visits from sample accounts.","index":60,"end_time":222.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"These are getting ads on LinkedIn as well.","index":61,"end_time":225.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":223.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we, we just want to get your thoughts.","index":62,"end_time":228.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know we did give you access to Factors if there''s anything that you saw or want to see segmented maybe on your side based on what we do have available in Factors.","index":63,"end_time":239.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Any thoughts there, ro?","index":64,"end_time":240.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"No, I''m gonna have the team like.","index":65,"end_time":245.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.11,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Look up Coastal Mechanical Services and see how big it is as a H Vac related thing.","index":66,"end_time":251.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And if they''re doing data centers, my guess is that axis is small.","index":67,"end_time":258.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.91,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then like Suffolk, I''m pretty sure I know who Suffolk is, a customer and I''m pretty sure the person visiting from Suffolk is actually in their like technology group because he''s been bothering us about something.","index":68,"end_time":271.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I think it''s, I''m actually surprised.","index":69,"end_time":276.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"On the open rate.","index":70,"end_time":277.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.41,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like I think that''s a lot higher.","index":71,"end_time":280.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Than what we''re maybe seeing on some.","index":72,"end_time":282.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":280.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Of our manual stuff.","index":73,"end_time":283.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Obviously the replies, but the way the.","index":74,"end_time":286.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":283.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Copy''S written, it''s not really call to action.","index":75,"end_time":289.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":286.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, right.","index":76,"end_time":290.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s more like, hey, are you interested, you know, are you interested in layout and stuff like that?","index":77,"end_time":295.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.61,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I think if we could maybe.","index":78,"end_time":297.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":295.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Over time, like the people who open.","index":79,"end_time":299.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or do multiple opens, if we can.","index":80,"end_time":301.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":299.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Kind of track that and have that and then maybe we do some manual pushes on those people down the line or something like that.","index":81,"end_time":309.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yep, that''s something we can do.","index":82,"end_time":311.979,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the one thing we''re not pushing those events to HubSpot because that will be a lot of data for each contract or each contact.","index":83,"end_time":319.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.979,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But one thing that we can do, Natalie, is we can go into smartly, we can pull a report like who, you know, of this cohort that we sent emails to who had, you know, multiple opens.","index":84,"end_time":331.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then, you know, we could line that up with Some additional outreach if you wanted to do Rob, we could have like a list that we could build in HubSpot for you or something along those lines.","index":85,"end_time":341.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":342.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.549,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Because what we''re doing in the abm, we''re sending the first event.","index":87,"end_time":345.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we, we basically put a timestamp on that first email that we send so we know when the campaign started.","index":88,"end_time":351.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":345.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''re not sending every click or open event or even the substance and email events either because it would just drown HubSpot essentially with API requests.","index":89,"end_time":363.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":90,"end_time":363.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we still do have the data in the source smart lead system to pull that.","index":91,"end_time":369.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":92,"end_time":372.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then paid media components, we got two layers there.","index":93,"end_time":375.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve got Google search ads, conversions there and then LinkedIn ads and in Rob, on those form fills and such, I mean, do you all like any, anything to report there as far as leads that have, have come in or, you know, how do you all analyze those from like the source of those leads?","index":94,"end_time":396.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, how do you all evaluate things on your side?","index":95,"end_time":398.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":396.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, none.","index":96,"end_time":401.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":400.82,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So like when the leads come in.","index":97,"end_time":404.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":402.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We''Ll get an alert and then we can, we''ll reach out to them.","index":98,"end_time":407.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Nothing we''ve ever gotten from paid has been an actual lead that we like.","index":99,"end_time":412.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.18,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You know, in like SAS land or.","index":100,"end_time":415.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.57,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like MQL or like whatever that would be like a quality thing.","index":101,"end_time":419.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s usually stuff that''s like one guy.","index":102,"end_time":422.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.17,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Who''S interested in something or wants to, you know, it''s not like what we.","index":103,"end_time":427.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Would consider a quality lead.","index":104,"end_time":428.849,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.29,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we haven''t done a huge amount of like analyzing it, if that makes sense.","index":105,"end_time":434.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.849,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":106,"end_time":435.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s been throughout time.","index":107,"end_time":437.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s just like it would be like.","index":108,"end_time":439.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":437.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If like the Axxy gave us a lead on HubSpot on the website or on Google or like whatever.","index":109,"end_time":447.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":439.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We wouldn''t really consider that in our.","index":110,"end_time":450.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":448.3,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Target market right now.","index":111,"end_time":451.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.02,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we wouldn''t, you know, probably wouldn''t do anything with it.","index":112,"end_time":455.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think in theory all those things are tracked in HubSpot.","index":113,"end_time":459.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I''m not, I''m not 100% sure because like right now when I look at lead source, it''s all like outbound because the mid stuff isn''t in there.","index":114,"end_time":467.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.18,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But I did see the first contact thing that you guys were talking about.","index":115,"end_time":470.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It looks like we hit a bunch of meta people on 116.","index":116,"end_time":473.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":470.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I don''t, I don''t know.","index":117,"end_time":475.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think this is good.","index":118,"end_time":477.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":476.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"This is good data, like, and we.","index":119,"end_time":481.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Can use it and stuff like that.","index":120,"end_time":482.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":481.15,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But I don''t.","index":121,"end_time":483.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.55,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We haven''t really and I, I don''t.","index":122,"end_time":486.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.75,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"This isn''t a criticism of you guys.","index":123,"end_time":488.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or ads or anything, it just kind of shows where we are right now, which is like, hey, we have a version of.","index":124,"end_time":493.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"With our direct service model, we''re targeting a very small slice of the market.","index":125,"end_time":497.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":494.08,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then there''s a lot of kind of like noise and awareness that comes.","index":126,"end_time":501.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"In through these channels.","index":127,"end_time":502.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":128,"end_time":503.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":503.28,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We just don''t do, you know, we don''t do a lot with it or we don''t prioritize it because it''s not going to lead to.","index":129,"end_time":510.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So far, you know, hasn''t led to a lot of business or what we would consider like reoccurring customers and stuff like that.","index":130,"end_time":519.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":511.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":131,"end_time":520.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And where.","index":132,"end_time":521.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"When you do qualify things, when you do say it is a good opportunity or lead, what''s the best place for us to go and find that?","index":133,"end_time":531.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is it at the.","index":134,"end_time":532.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is it when you actually get a deal that''s created and we then look at the contacts?","index":135,"end_time":536.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because one thing that I think would be helpful for us is to really back into where deals are coming from.","index":136,"end_time":542.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":536.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s look at the context, how those were created.","index":137,"end_time":544.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s just good homework on our side to then marry up with maybe some of the traffic that''s coming in.","index":138,"end_time":550.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I''m just, just curious there.","index":139,"end_time":552.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is it deal records or.","index":140,"end_time":554.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean it''s deal.","index":141,"end_time":555.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.49,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You could look at deal records.","index":142,"end_time":557.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.61,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You could look at the thing that I posted that has like kind of the bigger companies deal records probably the easiest, but you''re not.","index":143,"end_time":565.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":557.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We probably miss like lookalike companies that.","index":144,"end_time":568.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We haven''t done projects with you yet.","index":145,"end_time":571.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":568.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So it''s kind of like I look, I know it''s not as automated as you would like, but if we, if you send me like, if we send the lists of the like 213Open or we send a list of anyone.","index":146,"end_time":585.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If we send all of the Google ones in LinkedIn people that have clicked.","index":147,"end_time":589.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":585.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"On it in the last 12 months or six months or whatever.","index":148,"end_time":592.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I can just run through it really quick and say yes, relevant to where we are right now and okay.","index":149,"end_time":599.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":592.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Type of thing.","index":150,"end_time":600.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, I think maybe we do that.","index":151,"end_time":602.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":600.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Natalie, we''ll make that a test.","index":152,"end_time":603.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just go through some of the data we do have in factors.","index":153,"end_time":606.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I look in.","index":154,"end_time":609.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":608.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I look in fact, like I''ve looked.","index":155,"end_time":610.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"In factors twice a week over the last week.","index":156,"end_time":613.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s really cool to like click and.","index":157,"end_time":615.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.82,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"See the, the people, right?","index":158,"end_time":618.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, oh, they got the ad and.","index":159,"end_time":619.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Then they went visited the website and stuff.","index":160,"end_time":621.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":619.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s a little hard because like some of them, like some of them I''ve.","index":161,"end_time":626.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":621.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Wanted to Tell the team, like, hey, we should go target this company.","index":162,"end_time":629.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But.","index":163,"end_time":630.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.45,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But it''s a little bit hard because we don''t really always target the same.","index":164,"end_time":634.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":630.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The same role.","index":165,"end_time":638.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And we have no, you know, like.","index":166,"end_time":639.769,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":638.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"No way of knowing the role.","index":167,"end_time":641.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.769,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I haven''t, I haven''t really been.","index":168,"end_time":643.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, oh, you need to reach out to this company.","index":169,"end_time":644.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":643.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They''re visiting the website because the role.","index":170,"end_time":647.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"At like a meta or, you know, even a GC could be so wide.","index":171,"end_time":652.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.97,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And we could, like someone from the.","index":172,"end_time":654.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"GC could be visiting, but they could be focused on like office projects in Chicago and we''re focused on data centers and stuff like that.","index":173,"end_time":662.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":654.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, gotcha.","index":174,"end_time":663.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":662.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There is one tool.","index":175,"end_time":665.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Are you familiar with RB2B at all?","index":176,"end_time":668.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''m not, no.","index":177,"end_time":669.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.82,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"That does personal identification.","index":178,"end_time":672.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s some thoughts as to whether you want that on your site or not.","index":179,"end_time":677.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, from a privacy standpoint, it is like GDPR compliant because it only tracks individuals in the U.S. but what this does do in cases, and we turn this on in some cases, Rob and I think, Natalie, you can check me.","index":180,"end_time":694.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think it''s like $200 a month or something.","index":181,"end_time":696.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":694.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s not like, you know, with the amount of traffic that''s coming through.","index":182,"end_time":699.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But Rob, one thing it does is it helps with accounts that have large buyer groups.","index":183,"end_time":704.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.74,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can identify, I think like 40 to 50% of the personal traffic that comes in.","index":184,"end_time":712.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so, like if.","index":185,"end_time":714.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If John Smith from Microsoft, you know, we can get that identification through our B2B.","index":186,"end_time":721.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Whereas factors is just at the Microsoft level because it''s just looking at IP addresses.","index":187,"end_time":726.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So might be something to think about.","index":188,"end_time":727.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":726.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you want to try that, then that way we can actually see.","index":189,"end_time":730.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Connect the dots a little bit on the personal.","index":190,"end_time":733.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.76,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How does it work?","index":191,"end_time":735.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"How does it work in practice?","index":192,"end_time":736.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"When you do the outreach, people kind of pretend they don''t have that information, like that kind of detailed information or.","index":193,"end_time":743.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Oh, you mean their sales team.","index":194,"end_time":745.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":195,"end_time":745.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"What''s the.","index":196,"end_time":746.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"What have you guys seen as like the.","index":197,"end_time":748.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.48,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think it''s cool.","index":198,"end_time":749.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think it''s a little creepy.","index":199,"end_time":750.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I wouldn''t like it if someone did it to me.","index":200,"end_time":752.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.6,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But help in our case.","index":201,"end_time":754.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.72,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But like, what''s the.","index":202,"end_time":756.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.88,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"How do you reach out then without sounding creepy, what have you guys Creepy.","index":203,"end_time":762.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":756.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s a good question.","index":204,"end_time":762.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And there are different schools of thought on it.","index":205,"end_time":765.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":762.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The.","index":206,"end_time":766.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.94,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The one thing that we commonly see is like, hey, it looks like you''re checking out, you know, X, Y or Z. I''m wondering where you are, you know, in.","index":207,"end_time":774.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"In the journey.","index":208,"end_time":775.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.419,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You.","index":209,"end_time":775.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You want to have a dedicated conversation.","index":210,"end_time":777.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there something that I could help or you know, I''m saying like if you notice that they went to like a specific product page or something, it''s like, yeah, you might be taking a closer look.","index":211,"end_time":788.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":777.7,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Maybe you didn''t find what you''re looking for.","index":212,"end_time":791.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":788.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Happy to jump on a quick call and help.","index":213,"end_time":793.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":791.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That tends to be the best nudge, I would say because I do feel like people on the other side, they do recognize that there is website tracking and people are like noticing there''s intent signals.","index":214,"end_time":806.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":794.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s a lot of different data providers out there.","index":215,"end_time":808.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it is somewhat common but also depends on your audience.","index":216,"end_time":811.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":808.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some people do get creeped out.","index":217,"end_time":813.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":811.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Without it, it''s just like the world we live.","index":218,"end_time":815.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":219,"end_time":816.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we did want to mention it to you.","index":220,"end_time":818.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s, it''s there some, some of our clients are like, no, we don''t want to do that.","index":221,"end_time":822.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":818.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ll be more passive.","index":222,"end_time":824.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then others are like, no, I want to know if Johnny did, you know, if I can tell if, if he or she hit the website, then maybe I do some, some one to one outreach.","index":223,"end_time":833.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":224,"end_time":833.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.05,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me, let me, let me think of, let me think about it.","index":225,"end_time":839.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":835.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I''ll probably talk to Derek.","index":226,"end_time":840.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s a little, it''s a little bit of like who do you want to be?","index":227,"end_time":842.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":843.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Type of thing.","index":229,"end_time":844.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.91,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yep.","index":230,"end_time":845.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":231,"end_time":847.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":846.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then Natalie, last piece focused in on Rob, a couple points that you had in Slack.","index":232,"end_time":854.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So one, obviously the, the account list that it''s looking like you put together.","index":233,"end_time":859.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So maybe walk us through that and, and how we can maybe add to what you''re doing there.","index":234,"end_time":864.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so, so the way that like at a holistic level, the way that I look at this is kind of.","index":235,"end_time":872.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.83,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like right now we''re doing direct targeted campaigns to trades.","index":236,"end_time":876.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.17,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And so that''s like our, our team is writing the flows in HubSpot.","index":237,"end_time":882.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.73,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They''re calling, they''re doing like their messaging.","index":238,"end_time":885.009,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''s a whole category of account and the idea is trades.","index":239,"end_time":891.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like so think electrical trade at a data center is a faster path to revenue than a systems integrator original contractor, because that scope is their scope.","index":240,"end_time":903.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":891.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They own the scope.","index":241,"end_time":904.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Etc where when you sell to the systems integrator or the general contractor, it''s multiple trades.","index":242,"end_time":909.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.41,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s more, it''s more complicated but there''s a higher probability of like it being less transactional and more like a partnership and you do more kind of like an enterprise rollout over time and you get on all the projects.","index":243,"end_time":924.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"While we''re.","index":244,"end_time":927.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Doing that trade piece, they''re not hitting these accounts.","index":245,"end_time":932.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":927.42,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Not that I bet if you looked at HubSpot like they weren''t necessarily hitting on outbound a lot of these accounts in a long time either, because when people are in that funnel of converting them to an enterprise customer, it''s a lot of handholding.","index":246,"end_time":946.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":932.9,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s a lot of like there''s a big enterprise sales component to this or change management, ROI, etc.","index":247,"end_time":954.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.82,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So this is kind of like just, I don''t know if you remember like our eight core accounts, like that''s now like seven or something like that.","index":248,"end_time":961.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But a lot of those don''t have it move through like the funnel as actually as fast as I would like, where it''s either like, yes, we''re rolling out or no, we''re not.","index":249,"end_time":969.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":961.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"They kind of are like, you know, these people move at a slower pace than a lot of like software enterprise sales or mid market software sales and things like that.","index":250,"end_time":981.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":969.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So the idea would be, I think.","index":251,"end_time":984.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.43,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If we just sent the first sequence of emails to our existing targets, it''s not something we need to do right now.","index":252,"end_time":990.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":984.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, let''s kind of run a full cycle of, of, of the five emails or whatever in the flow and then reassess and say, hey, what do we want to do?","index":253,"end_time":1000.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":990.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Do we want to go to a wider target base?","index":254,"end_time":1002.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Do we want to refine with this existing target base, our messaging, the people we, our titles, the people we go to, like, what do we want to do?","index":255,"end_time":1012.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So it''s just a wider, A wider opportunity set, if that''s where we go.","index":256,"end_time":1017.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.78,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Because I know, Tristan, we started to.","index":257,"end_time":1020.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1018.5,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, get tight on some of the clay lists and there weren''t very big sets.","index":258,"end_time":1025.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.14,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So this is just another way we can go wider.","index":259,"end_time":1028.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1025.54,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, if we want to.","index":260,"end_time":1030.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.58,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":261,"end_time":1032.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then so, and when we say so a AF accounts, like what, what does AF stand for?","index":262,"end_time":1043.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":263,"end_time":1043.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s an internal term.","index":264,"end_time":1044.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It means automated facilities.","index":265,"end_time":1045.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.63,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So it''s like, it''s like, it''s like.","index":266,"end_time":1048.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.03,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''S, I think on our list there''s some data center, general contractors, there''s some systems integrators for manufacturing and, and warehouses and stuff like that.","index":267,"end_time":1058.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Got it.","index":268,"end_time":1059.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1059.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s just kind of a, it''s.","index":269,"end_time":1061.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.8,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"A more a set of like some of the stuff that, you know, you already pulled.","index":270,"end_time":1066.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.4,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s just a wider starting point than some of the other ways that we started to get our initial list.","index":271,"end_time":1072.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1066.04,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":272,"end_time":1072.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so that looks like.","index":273,"end_time":1073.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And now if you could click on it.","index":274,"end_time":1075.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let''s look at that real quick.","index":275,"end_time":1076.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So there''s over 200 companies there, Rob.","index":276,"end_time":1079.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1076.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, and I''m.","index":277,"end_time":1080.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1079.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''m sorry, are folks Doing outreach to some of these now a little.","index":278,"end_time":1086.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1080.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Bit, but I don''t think Connor is.","index":279,"end_time":1088.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1086.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Maybe hitting some systems integrators again in warehouse, but we''re not hitting these very often.","index":280,"end_time":1094.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":281,"end_time":1096.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":282,"end_time":1096.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.1,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Right now, so.","index":283,"end_time":1097.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.46,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, got it.","index":284,"end_time":1099.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1098.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s more of just like, we''re going to see how the initial list that we put together, that cohort does, and then we would perhaps layer this in as a.","index":285,"end_time":1108.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"An additional campaign.","index":286,"end_time":1111.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Additional.","index":287,"end_time":1113.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1112.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''s.","index":288,"end_time":1113.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''s targets for additional.","index":289,"end_time":1114.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1113.47,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, obviously Google and Oracle are already on our list for hyperscaler.","index":290,"end_time":1118.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1114.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I didn''t clean those.","index":291,"end_time":1119.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1118.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I didn''t clean those up.","index":292,"end_time":1121.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But, like, something like Cardex is like a systems integrator that I''m not sure we had.","index":293,"end_time":1127.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1121.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we can rerun the stuff through Clay, do Cardex and see, you know, additional lookalikes or.","index":294,"end_time":1133.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Or do our.","index":295,"end_time":1134.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Our role set at Cardex and Vanderlay is another one.","index":296,"end_time":1139.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So it''s like another.","index":297,"end_time":1142.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1141.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s another way we can expand our list.","index":298,"end_time":1145.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.81,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I would clean this up before we did it, but just wanted to, like, if we run our initial set and you guys are like, hey, we need to add more companies, like, this is a.","index":299,"end_time":1156.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1145.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"A target list where we can do more kind of like, in theory, these companies are in our target market.","index":300,"end_time":1162.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1156.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We''re probably not hitting them with our direct sales force.","index":301,"end_time":1165.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1162.53,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So we can do this kind of like, passive education campaign.","index":302,"end_time":1169.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":303,"end_time":1170.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1169.89,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Towards some of these companies.","index":304,"end_time":1172.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right, that works.","index":305,"end_time":1174.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1172.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we''ll have this, like, in our pocket for now, it sounds like, and then we can check back in a couple of weeks and we can build those out in clay and start to fold those in if we like to.","index":306,"end_time":1186.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1175.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":307,"end_time":1186.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.29,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, next question.","index":308,"end_time":1189.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it was about question from the sales team, so walk us through that one.","index":309,"end_time":1193.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.65,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, they.","index":310,"end_time":1196.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1195.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"One person asked, like, hey, I have these priority contacts that I know really well.","index":311,"end_time":1202.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1197.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, I don''t want to reach out to them and talk to them, be talking to them.","index":312,"end_time":1207.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1202.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And then all of a sudden, they.","index":313,"end_time":1208.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.13,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Get put in an automated flow so.","index":314,"end_time":1210.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.01,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''S less like, hey, I know we.","index":315,"end_time":1212.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1210.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Talked a lot about, like, company, like, do not touch.","index":316,"end_time":1216.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1212.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Right.","index":317,"end_time":1216.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.56,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, things.","index":318,"end_time":1217.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And you''ve had clients mention that a lot.","index":319,"end_time":1220.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.96,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I wasn''t super concerned about at a company level because there''s so many people and like, whatever, but, like, they.","index":320,"end_time":1229.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.84,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Someone did ask, like, can we give you a list of people at an individual email level that would never be kind of like, touched by an ABM campaign?","index":321,"end_time":1238.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1229.44,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":322,"end_time":1239.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":323,"end_time":1239.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1239.2,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If the answer is no, like, that''s fine too.","index":324,"end_time":1242.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1239.84,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Derek and I were to kind of talking.","index":325,"end_time":1244.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1243.32,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"See the Pros and cons of both.","index":326,"end_time":1246.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"But, like, you know, my.","index":327,"end_time":1249.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1247.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"My view is if someone''s a great.","index":328,"end_time":1251.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.76,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Contact, like, it''s like someone in your network and they accidentally get, like, not like a automated email.","index":329,"end_time":1258.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1251.24,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s not like they''re going to be like, oh, I hate rugged.","index":330,"end_time":1260.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.04,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"No.","index":331,"end_time":1260.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":332,"end_time":1261.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1261.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we.","index":333,"end_time":1262.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1261.92,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We do have to consider this.","index":334,"end_time":1264.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1262.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, because it is sensitive in a lot of cases.","index":335,"end_time":1266.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1264.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what I would suggest there''s.","index":336,"end_time":1268.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1267.16,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s two ways to do it.","index":337,"end_time":1270.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1268.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can have a direct link into HubSpot on the account level to where we validate, like, hey, is this person in HubSpot already?","index":338,"end_time":1280.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1271.35,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Then don''t even bother.","index":339,"end_time":1282.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1280.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what we didn''t do with the existing campaign route because we didn''t.","index":340,"end_time":1286.669,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1282.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We didn''t necessarily care.","index":341,"end_time":1287.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1286.669,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":342,"end_time":1288.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1287.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Which is, like, almost too much.","index":343,"end_time":1291.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1289.75,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Right.","index":344,"end_time":1291.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.67,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"There''s probably a bunch of people in.","index":345,"end_time":1293.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1291.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"HubSpot that are not actually good contacts.","index":346,"end_time":1296.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1293.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We''ve never made any progress with, like, you know what I''m saying?","index":347,"end_time":1299.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1296.23,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Like, it''s almost like using a hammer to do a small screw or something.","index":348,"end_time":1304.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.57,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":349,"end_time":1305.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1304.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What.","index":350,"end_time":1305.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.57,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What we can do is we could build a list in clay, basically, a black list, essentially.","index":351,"end_time":1312.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1305.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then.","index":352,"end_time":1313.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1312.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So before we would push anyone to smart lead from clay, we would.","index":353,"end_time":1317.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1313.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We would say, hey, is this person on this list?","index":354,"end_time":1320.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.49,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Make sure they''re not in this table.","index":355,"end_time":1321.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1320.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":356,"end_time":1322.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.37,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If they''re not, then cool.","index":357,"end_time":1324.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1323.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can send them smart lead if they are in that table to do not contact, and we skip it.","index":358,"end_time":1330.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1324.69,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So the question then becomes, how do we get people on that list in clay?","index":359,"end_time":1335.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could do that automatically, whereas we.","index":360,"end_time":1340.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1335.79,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, we don''t have web hooks from HubSpot.","index":361,"end_time":1343.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t think.","index":362,"end_time":1349.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1348.35,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I don''t think the list is going.","index":363,"end_time":1350.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.39,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"To be that big, which is.","index":364,"end_time":1351.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1350.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"How frequently would that get updated.","index":365,"end_time":1354.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1353.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Would it be something where you could give us just like a CSV or we could do a list in HubSpot?","index":366,"end_time":1360.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1355.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think so.","index":367,"end_time":1361.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.9,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":368,"end_time":1362.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.86,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That would be pretty.","index":369,"end_time":1363.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Pretty straightforward to do.","index":370,"end_time":1364.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1363.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":371,"end_time":1365.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1365.22,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So before we launch the next one, we''ll just connect with your.","index":372,"end_time":1370.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Your sales team and say, hey, that''s really.","index":373,"end_time":1373.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1370.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You could all just do a list in HubSpot for us.","index":374,"end_time":1376.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1373.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll do it.","index":375,"end_time":1377.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1376.66,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I like, it''s a little bit conceptually.","index":376,"end_time":1380.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1377.38,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You want to know the answer?","index":377,"end_time":1381.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1380.7,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I think a lot of the people he''s concerned about, like, I don''t think Clark Construction is on our list anyway.","index":378,"end_time":1386.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.74,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"So I think if.","index":379,"end_time":1387.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1386.98,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I''ll do it and I''ll say, look, if.","index":380,"end_time":1390.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If there''s a.","index":381,"end_time":1391.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1390.59,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If there''s someone you really don''t want.","index":382,"end_time":1393.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1392.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Contacted, we have to you know, make.","index":383,"end_time":1398.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1393.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"A notation so we can run a.","index":384,"end_time":1400.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Report in HubSpot of the people and export the list or something like that.","index":385,"end_time":1404.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1400.31,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":386,"end_time":1404.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1405.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1404.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right.","index":388,"end_time":1406.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can work through that.","index":389,"end_time":1407.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then, Tristan, just as a double, like, layer of protection, we can also upload a Do not contact list directly to Smart Lead.","index":390,"end_time":1417.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1407.87,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So that means we could do it retroactively, too, for the campaigns that are running right now.","index":391,"end_time":1422.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1418.17,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s a good point.","index":392,"end_time":1425.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1424.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, if you do want to reach back, Rob, and just have another check on there, could do that as well.","index":393,"end_time":1430.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1425.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":394,"end_time":1434.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1433.77,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I. I think the risk is small help.","index":395,"end_time":1438.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.33,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Someone raised it as a concern.","index":396,"end_time":1440.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.65,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Appreciate it.","index":397,"end_time":1440.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.09,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"You know, all of it.","index":398,"end_time":1442.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.89,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":399,"end_time":1442.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1442.12,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll see if they even put together.","index":400,"end_time":1444.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1443.16,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"The HubSpot list of do not Contact, and then we can execute it.","index":401,"end_time":1449,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.48,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":402,"end_time":1450.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.72,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":403,"end_time":1451.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1450.68,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right.","index":404,"end_time":1452,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then the last bullet item, we have exploring LinkedIn ad campaigns.","index":405,"end_time":1457.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some of the work that you''re doing now on the outreach side from the sales team.","index":406,"end_time":1462.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1458.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1464.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What are your thoughts there?","index":408,"end_time":1465.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1464.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We can definitely turn that on.","index":409,"end_time":1466.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.36,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What does the.","index":410,"end_time":1467.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The audience size look like there?","index":411,"end_time":1469.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1467.73,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can get the audience.","index":412,"end_time":1471.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I''ll talk to George.","index":413,"end_time":1482.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.85,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"I mean, right now it looks like relatively small, like in the three hundreds or something like that.","index":414,"end_time":1490.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.81,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"How big of a list do you need?","index":415,"end_time":1492.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1490.93,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Are those contacts or companies?","index":416,"end_time":1494.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Those are contacts.","index":417,"end_time":1496.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.26,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Okay.","index":418,"end_time":1497.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1496.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s close.","index":419,"end_time":1498.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1497.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If we have to match, I mean, I think minimum 500.","index":420,"end_time":1502.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So we can maybe just you know, add in a few other roles, you know, to expand that list so that we at least have a size that''s good enough.","index":421,"end_time":1512.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1502.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We could definitely do that and just create a specific audience and then we.","index":422,"end_time":1520.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.1,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Using some of the existing creative now.","index":423,"end_time":1522.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or is that something that you would create, like a different type of ads for.","index":424,"end_time":1526.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1522.31,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For these folks?","index":425,"end_time":1527.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.55,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Let me think.","index":426,"end_time":1529.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1528.51,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Let me think about that and look.","index":427,"end_time":1531.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1529.19,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"At, like, some of the creative we have.","index":428,"end_time":1533.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1531.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"If it''s, like, racking and stuff, we could do.","index":429,"end_time":1537.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.91,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Let me think about it.","index":430,"end_time":1538.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1537.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Let.","index":431,"end_time":1539.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1538.87,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"It''s good to know we don''t have.","index":432,"end_time":1540.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1539.79,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"To execute on this now.","index":433,"end_time":1542.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.99,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Let''s table it for two weeks and hopefully this list grows a little bit.","index":434,"end_time":1545.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.07,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And they also go through more flows so they reach out to the people a couple times.","index":435,"end_time":1550.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1546.25,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"And almost.","index":436,"end_time":1551.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1551.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"We almost use this as like, okay, there was a group of people who are not.","index":437,"end_time":1554.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.57,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Maybe engaged a little bit now, not ready, and we want to, like, retarget them kind of.","index":438,"end_time":1560.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1555.69,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"Yeah, we can do the retargeting piece and that.","index":439,"end_time":1563.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1560.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1565.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1565.05,"speaker_name":"Rob Schnitzler"},{"text":"All right.","index":441,"end_time":1566.01,"speaker_i